   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_1" text:outline-level="1">Titanul</text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="P5">Theodore Dreiser</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P10">You are encouraged to reference <text:span text:style-name="T1">this</text:span> using HTTP URLs, or cite small excerpts, followed by the precise {{thisurl}} URL reference.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P6">@source <text:s text:c="2"/>EDITURA DATINA BUCURETI  1993</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P3">Traducere Victor Flor<text:span text:style-name="T15">i</text:span>an</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P4">Coperta de Aurel Radulescu</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P4">ro</text:p>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2"><text:span text:style-name="Label">Capitolul I</text:span><text:line-break/>Oraul nou</text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n ziua n care Frank Algernon Cowperwood, eliberat, <text:span text:style-name="T1">prsi</text:span> nchisoarea<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span><text:s/>din Philadelphia, i ddu seama c viaa pe care o dusese n acest<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span><text:s/>ora, din copilrie, se isprvise. Adio tineree i, o dat cu <text:span text:style-name="T1">ea</text:span>,<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span><text:s/>visurile unor afaceri mree. Trebuia s-o ia <text:s text:c="2"/>din nou de la nceput.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Ar fi de prisos s repetm acum a doua criz care a urmat falimentului<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>dezastruos al lui <text:span text:style-name="T2">Jay Cooke &amp; Comp</text:span> l-a mbogit pentru a doua var. ntr-un fel, aceast avere redobndit l mai domolise puin. Soarta prea s-i surd din nou. Se sturase, oricum, pn peste cap de<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>burs,<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>ca mijloc de existen, nici s nu mai aud de ea! Avea s-i<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>ncerce norocul ntr-alt parte, at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tea posibiliti i stteau n<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>fa, n Far West  la tramvaie, misit funciar, c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>te i mai c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>te.<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>Philadelphia nu-l mai interesa. Dei acum<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>era liber i bogat, oamenii<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>cu pretenii tot mai credeau c purtarea lui fusese scandaloas, iar<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>lumea <text:span text:style-name="T1">finan</text:span>elor i buna societate se uitau nc de sus la el.<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>Trebuia s-i croiasc singur drum n via, neajutat de ni<text:span text:style-name="T1">meni</text:span> sau<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>doar pe ascuns, iar prietenii de od<text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span>nioar s-i urmreasc,<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>ascensiunea de la distan.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">A<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>a st<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd lucrurile, ntr-o bun zi lu trenul, condus la, gar de <text:s text:c="2"/>fermectoarea sa iubit, care abia,<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>mplinise douzeci i ase de ani. O privea cu tan<text:span text:style-name="T1">dr</text:span>e<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>e, deoarece <text:s/>Aileen era chintesena <text:s/>unui anumit tip <text:span text:style-name="T1">de</text:span> trumusee <text:span text:style-name="T1">feminin.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> La revedere, scumpa mea, rosti zmbind, cnd clopoelul anun <text:s/>plecarea trenului<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Scpm noi cur<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd de oraul sta. Nu-i face inim <text:s text:c="2"/>rea. M, ntor<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span> n dou-trei sptmni, sau, dac nu, trimi<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span> dup tine. Te-a lua acum, dar nu tiu cum e pe acolo<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> S vd unde ne i<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>stalm i <text:s/>pe urm m ocup eu i de povestea asta cu banii, i atunci s te ii. <text:s/>N-o s trim mereu aa, n <text:soft-page-break/>umbr... Divorez, apoi ne cstorim, i <text:s text:c="2"/>totul o s mearg strun. Ce nu faci cu bani!</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">O privea cu ochii lui mari, reci i ptrunztori, iar ea i prinse <text:s/>capul n mini.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Vai, Frank! Ce dor o s-mi fie de tine! Eti tot ce am pe lume.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> n dou sptmni, i mai spuse zmbind n timp ce trenul pornea, i telegrafiez sau m ntor<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>. Fii cuminte, iubito.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Se uita dup el sorbindu-l din ochi, nebun de dragoste  un copil alintat, rsfata familiei, o fire ptima  tipul de fe<text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span>eie fcut s plac. nl capul, mpodobit de un pr frumos, auriu<text:span text:style-name="T1">-</text:span>rocat, i-i <text:s/>trimise a srutare. Apoi plec; cu pai mari, sigari, cu mers legnat  <text:s/>genul de femeie dup care brbaii ntorc capul.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> <text:span text:style-name="T1">U</text:span>ite-o, asta-i fata aia a lui <text:span text:style-name="T1">B</text:span>utler, spuse unui coleg un impiegat de la Cile ferate. Ce zici<text:span text:style-name="T1">? </text:span>Cred c nimeni nu-i poate dori ceva mai <text:s/>bun.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Asta era tributul firese pe care totdeauna pasiunea i invidia l pltete frumuseii i vitalitii<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Aa fost de cnd e lumea. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Pentru prima dat n viaa lui, Cowperw<text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span>od fcea o cltorie mai lung dec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n la Pittsburg<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Aventurile sale din viaa comercial, dei <text:s text:c="2"/>strlucite, nu depiser hotarele lumii plicticoase i grave din <text:s text:c="2"/>Philadelphia  o lume cu oameni convenionali i plicticoi, n care <text:s text:c="2"/>unii nzuiau la supremaie n <text:span text:style-name="T1">so</text:span>cietatea american cu aceleai<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>pretenii cu care a aspirau la tradiionala conducere a vieii <text:s text:c="2"/>comerciale, <text:span text:style-name="T1">cu</text:span> istoria ei, cu spiritul ei plutocrat, conser<text:span text:style-name="T1">vator, cu o </text:span><text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T1">r</text:span>espectabilitate onc<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>uoas <text:span text:style-name="T1">i, n fine cu toate pre</text:span>ferinele i pasiunile care decurg de aici. <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i aducea ami<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>te cum <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>naintea prbuirii sale ajunsese aproape stpnul acestei lumi <text:s text:c="2"/>spilcuite, cu principii de fier, pe care atunci o credea a lui. De fapt <text:s text:c="2"/>fcea parte din ea. Acum ns, <text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>ra un proscris, un fost pucria, dei <text:s text:c="2"/>milionar. Dar ateapt! i repeta el mereu. Cursa o ctig cel care <text:s text:c="2"/>alearg mai iute. Da, iar victoria va fi de partea celui mai <text:soft-page-break/>tare. O <text:s text:c="2"/>s vad el dac lumea are s cuteze s-l calce n picioare.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">n sfirit, dup o cltorie de dou zile, o dat cu zorile, Chicago i <text:s text:c="2"/>apru naintea ochilor. Petrecuse dou nopi ntr-un tren Pullman de un <text:s text:c="2"/>lux ostentativ  ntr-un vagon care voi<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span> s compenseze lipsa de <text:s/>confort printr-un rafinament de prost gust, cu mare risip de plu i <text:s text:c="2"/>cristaluri  cnd ncepur  s apar primele cantoane, singuratice, <text:s/>din metropola preriei. inele pe ling care mergea trenul se <text:s text:c="2"/>nmuleau, silpii de telegraf erau tot mai ncrcai de brae i <text:s text:c="2"/>s<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rme, ca un pienjeni. Departe, nspre ora, aprea ici-colo cte o <text:s text:c="2"/>csu stingher de muncitori, locuina unui suflet aventuros care <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i cldise la aa mare distan o colib pipernicit ca s poat astfel <text:s text:c="2"/>s se bucure de avantajele mici dar sigure care apar din continua dezvoltare a oraului.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">esul  ntins ca o mas  era acoperit cu iarb veted, pm<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntie, <text:s text:c="2"/>rmas de anul trecut, btut uor de adierea dimineii. Dedesubt <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ncepea s mijeasc iarba t<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nr, verde, stindardul prevestitor al <text:s text:c="2"/>noului an. O atmosfer cristalin mbrca, nu se tie de ce, conturul <text:s text:c="2"/>ceos al oraului, prins ca o musc n chihlimbar, i-i ddea un fel de <text:s text:c="2"/>subtilitate artistic, care-l emoiona pe Frank. De mult vreme ahtiat <text:s text:c="2"/>de art i cunosctor ambiios  colecia sa din Philadelphia, strns <text:s text:c="2"/>i apoi irosit, i formase gustul i-i oferise prilej de desftare, <text:s text:c="2"/>iar mai trziu i de mult tristee, el aprecia orice tablou nc<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nttor pe care-l descoperea n natur.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">inele, una l<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ng alta, se nmulea<text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span> din ce n ce<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Vagoane de marf <text:s/>adunate aici, cu sutele, din toate colurile rii  galbene, roii, albastre, verzi, albe... (i aduse aminte c Chicago era punctul <text:s text:c="2"/>terminus <text:s text:c="2"/>pentru treizeci de linii de cale ferat, ca i cum aici ar <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>i fost captul lumii). Csuele joase cu unul sau dou etaje, dei din <text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span>emn <text:s text:c="2"/>nou, erau nespoite i afumate, mohor<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>te. La bariere ateptau tramvaie, <text:s text:c="2"/>cruele <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i cabrioletele cu roile pline de noroi. Bg de aseam ce drepte i ntinse erau strzile, ce prost pavate erau trotuarele i cum <text:s/>urcau i coborau mereu  ici un ir de trepte, colo un <text:soft-page-break/>adevrat peron <text:s text:c="2"/>n faa unei case i mai departe un drumeag lung de scnduri ntinse <text:s/>direct pe glodul preriei. Ce mai ora ! Iat i un bra al r<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ului <text:s text:c="2"/>Chicago, murdar i ano, cu apa lui neagr i plin de pcur, purt<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd puzderie de remorchere care g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>f<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>iau, cu silozuri nalte, roii, cafenii sau verzi, cu depozite de crbuni sau de cherestea de un <text:s text:c="2"/>ga<text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span>ben-cafeniu, imense i nnegrite de fum.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Aici era via; vzu asta din prima clip. Aici clocotea un, mare ora <text:s text:c="2"/>n devenire. Ceva trepidant n atmosfer l atrgea. C<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t de diferit era <text:s text:c="2"/>de Philadelphia, n unele privine! i Philadelphia i se pruse un <text:s text:c="2"/>ora fremttor, c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndva i se pruse minunat chiar o ntreag lume. Chicago, evident mai puin dezvoltat, promitea s-l depeasc. Aici <text:s text:c="2"/>simea mai mult tineree, avea ndejdi mai mari. ntr-o explozie de <text:s text:c="2"/>soare matinal care se revrsa ntre dou depozite de crbun<text:span text:style-name="T1">i </text:span>i <text:s text:c="2"/>pentru c trenul se oprise ca s dea voie unui pod mobil s ge retrag, <text:s text:c="2"/>ls<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd vaselor mari, ncrcate cu cherestea i grne cale liber  n <text:s text:c="2"/>am<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndou direciile  se uit la un grup de docheri irlandezi, <text:s text:c="2"/>tr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndvind pe marginea unui depozit de lemne, ntr-o curte al crei <text:s text:c="2"/>zid mergea de-a lungul apei. Brbai voinici, n cmi albastre sau <text:s text:c="2"/>roii, ncini la bru cu o curea, specimene umane frumoase, cu pipe <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n <text:s text:c="2"/>gur, a<text:span text:style-name="T1">r</text:span>i de soare, plini de ndrznezl. De ce erau oare at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t de <text:s text:c="2"/>chipei se ntreb. Acest ora primitiv, murdar, prea a fi fcut s <text:s/>dezvluie tot felul de priveliti, care mai de care mai pitoreti i <text:s text:c="2"/>mai emoionante. Prea pur i simplu un cntec ! Aici era o lume <text:s text:c="2"/>t<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nr, viaa crea ceva nou. Ar <text:span text:style-name="T1">fi</text:span> mai bine poate pentru ei <text:s/>s nu se mai duc delo<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span> n nord-vestul rii; dar botrirea o va lua <text:s text:c="2"/>mai trziu.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Deocamdat avea nite scrisori de recomandaie adresate unor persoane <text:s text:c="2"/>simandicoase din Chicago. Voia s stea de vorb cu civa bancheri, cu <text:s text:c="2"/>doi-trei reprezentani ai formelor de agentur i comision. <text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span> interesa <text:s text:c="2"/>de asemenea bursa din Chicago, nu de alta, dar cunotea i pe fa i <text:s text:c="2"/>pe dos toate chiibuurile afacerilor, aici se ncheiau nite <text:s text:c="2"/>tranzacii cu cereale <text:soft-page-break/>foarte importante.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Trenul trecu n sf<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rit pe l<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ng un ir de calcanuri de case ca vai de <text:s text:c="2"/>lume, intr pe peronul lung, cu acoperiul prginit  andramale din <text:s text:c="2"/>care rmsese intact doar partea, de sus  i fc<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndu-i loc printre <text:s text:c="2"/>crucioarele de bagaje clmpnind de zor, pe ling locomotivele care <text:s text:c="2"/>s<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>uipau aburi i prin forfota, cltorilor, mergnd grbii ncoace i <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ncolo, Frank iei din gar, i croi drum pn la Canal Street i <text:s text:c="2"/>chem o trsur  una din irul lung de vehicule care trdau spiritul <text:s text:c="2"/>de organizare al unei metropole. Hotrit s trag la hotelul <text:span text:style-name="T2">Grand <text:s text:c="2"/>Pacific</text:span>, cel mai mare i cel mai bine cotat din ora; acolo spuse <text:s text:c="2"/>birj<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>rului s-l duc. n drum spre hotel studia aspectu<text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span> strzilor <text:s text:c="2"/>exact cum ar <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>i fcut cu un tablou care l-ar fi interesat. l emoionau <text:s text:c="2"/>micile tramvaie galbene, albastre, verzi, albe i cafenii, care strbteau strzile, i caii numai ciolane, istovii, cu zur<text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span>li l<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span> g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t. <text:s text:c="2"/>Tramvaiele astea parc erau ubrede, fcute doar din lemne de foc, <text:s text:c="2"/>frumos vopsite i din :oc n loc cu buci de sticl i de alam <text:s text:c="2"/>lucioas ; totui i ddea seama ce avere puteai s scoi din e<text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span>e, <text:s text:c="2"/>dac bine<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ne<text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span>es oraul ar <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>i continuat s se dezvolte n acelai ritm. <text:s text:c="2"/>Avea, i asta o tia prea <text:span text:style-name="T1">b</text:span>ine, o adevrat vocaie pentru tramvaie. <text:s text:c="2"/>Mai presu<text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span> de tranzaciile de burs, de banc, l fascina g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndul <text:s text:c="2"/>tramvaielor i vastele perspective de <text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>tiguri pe care le sugerau.</text:p>
