   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2"><text:span text:style-name="Label">Capitolul II </text:span><text:line-break/>n re<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>unoatere</text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Oraul Chicago! Oraul de a crei dezvoltare numele lui Frank Algernon <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood va fi c<text:span text:style-name="T1">ur</text:span>nd indisolubil legat! Cine va <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>i ctigtorul <text:s text:c="2"/>laurilor acestei Florene a vestului? Acest ora ca o <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>lacr care <text:s text:c="2"/>c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nt, inima Americii, acest poet n pantaloni de <text:span text:style-name="T2">cow-boy</text:span> i n piele <text:s text:c="2"/>de<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>ap, acest titan necioplit i primitiv, acest Burns citadin. Aezat <text:s text:c="2"/>la marginea unui lac strlucitor, un rege zdrehros, un rnoi <text:s text:c="2"/>cerind cu o epopee pe buze, un vagabond, un ora haimana cu mintea <text:s text:c="2"/>unui Cezar i n suflet cu fora dramatic a unui Euripide ! Oraul <text:s text:c="2"/>bard, care cnt fapte mree i mari nzuine, cu bocancii greoi, <text:s text:c="2"/>cufundai ad<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span> n mocirla vremii. Fie Atena venic a ta, o, Elad, iar <text:s text:c="2"/>tu Italie, fii deapururi stp<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>na Romei ! Chicago este Babilonul, Troia, <text:s text:c="2"/>Ninive, al unei lumi mai tinere. Aici se ntilnesc vestul uluit <text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span> estul <text:s text:c="2"/>plin de sperane. Aici oameni flmnzi venii din uzine i de pe <text:s text:c="2"/>ogoare, romantici i cu mintea plin de poezie, i-au durat un imperiu, <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>lvind <text:s text:c="2"/>gloria din mocirl. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">O mulime bizar, venit din New York, Vermont, <text:s text:c="2"/>New Hampshire, Maine, oameni serioi, rbdtori, hotr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i, <text:s text:c="2"/>necizelai, c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tui de puin, ahtiai s cucereasc un lucru pe care <text:s text:c="2"/>cnd l dobindesc nu snt nici mcar n stare s-i ghiceasc sensul, <text:s text:c="2"/>oameni dornici de a fi considerai mari, hotr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i s ajung <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>r s <text:s text:c="2"/>tie cum. Aici vine proprietarul vistor din Sud, prdat de<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>avuiile <text:s text:c="2"/>sale; studentul plin de sperane de la Yale, de la Harvard i <text:s text:c="2"/>Princeton; minerul rzvrtit din California sau din Munii St<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ncoi, cu pungile doldora de aur i argint. Aici se afl strini <text:s text:c="2"/>dezorientai, zpcii de o limb pe care n-o cunose  unguri, <text:s text:c="2"/>polonezi, suedezi, nemi, rui  cut<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndu-i compatrioii, ferindu-se <text:s text:c="2"/>de vecinii de <text:span text:style-name="T1">alt</text:span> neam. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:soft-page-break/></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:span text:style-name="T1">Aic</text:span>i nt<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>l<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>eti negri, prostituate, sprgtori de <text:span text:style-name="T1">greve, </text:span>cartofori i <text:s text:c="2"/>aventurieri, romantici prin excelen. Un ora cu o minoritate de b<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tina<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i ; un ora <text:s text:c="2"/>ticsit cu pleava a o mie de orae. Lumina caselor <text:s text:c="2"/>de prostituie se zrete de departe, n crciumi auzi muzic de banjo, <text:s text:c="2"/>de iter i de mandolin; n aceast via minunat a noii metropole <text:s text:c="2"/>din vest s-au str<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ns toate visurile i brutalitatea vremii, cu gndul <text:s text:c="2"/>s trag de aici maximum de plcere  i cu siguran c vor izbuti.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Primul om important din Chicago la care s-a; dus Cowperwood a fost <text:s text:c="2"/>preedintele bncii naionale din <text:span text:style-name="T2">Lake City</text:span>, cea m<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>i mare organizaie <text:s text:c="2"/>financiar din ora, cu drepturi de peste paisprezece milioane de dolari, Banca se afla la Munroe, pe Dearborn Street, la c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>teva strzi <text:s text:c="2"/>de hotelul lui.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Vezi ce poi s afli despre omul sta, porunci domnul Judah Addison, <text:s text:c="2"/>preedintele bncii, cnd l vzu pe Cowperwood c intr n anticamera <text:s text:c="2"/>lui<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">n biroul lui Addison erau aezate <text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>ite geamuri care-i permiteau, dac <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i ntindea g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tul, s vad pe toi cei care intrau n camera sa de <text:s text:c="2"/>primire, nainte ca acetia s-l observe pe el, i din primul moment a <text:s text:c="2"/>fost izbit de nfiarea i fora noului venit. Pentru c era foarte <text:s text:c="2"/>familiarizat cu lumea bancar i cu marile afaceri, n general, <text:s text:c="2"/>cptase calmul i stpnirea de sine, caliti pe care ns <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowper<text:span text:style-name="T1">w</text:span>ood le avea din fire.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">La cei treizeci i ase de ani ai si Cowperwood avea o neateptat <text:s text:c="2"/>siguran<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> de sine : era binevoit<text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span>r, abil, incisiv, cu o cuttur<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> de <text:s text:c="2"/>cine Tera Nova sau ciobnesc, la, fel de nevinovat i de atrgtor. <text:s text:c="2"/>Avea nite ochi minunai, uneori bl<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nzi i vioi, lumina de o inteligen <text:s text:c="2"/>ad<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nc i uman, care puteau brus<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span> : s devin duri i fulgertori. <text:s text:c="2"/>Ochi amgitori i de neptruns, care ispiteau att brbaii ct i <text:s text:c="2"/>femeile de toate condiiile sociale. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Secretarul cu care vorbise preedintele se ntoarse cu scrisoarea de <text:s text:c="2"/>recomandaie a lui Cowperwood,<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>i imediat intr i acesta<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:soft-page-break/></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Domnul Addison se scul instinctiv n picioare, <text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span>ucru pe care l f<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>c<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>a <text:s text:c="2"/>rar.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> snt <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ncntat s te cunosc, domnule Cowp<text:span text:style-name="T1">er</text:span>wood, spuse el politicos.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Te-am vzut intr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n<text:span text:style-name="T1">d.</text:span> Vezi geamurile mele? snt aa fcute ca s <text:span text:style-name="T1">pot</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>trage cu ochiul la tot ce se petrece n afar. Te <text:span text:style-name="T1">rog</text:span> ia loc. Nu vrei s <text:s text:c="2"/>iei un mr? Deschise sertarul di<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span> st<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nga i scoase c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>teva mere roii, <text:s text:c="2"/>lucioase i <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntinse unul lui Cowperwood. Eu ntotdeauna mn<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nc un mr <text:s text:c="2"/>la ora asta.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Mulumesc, n<text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span>... rspunse Cowperwood, amabil, <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntre timp c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntrind <text:s text:c="2"/>inteligena i firea bancherului, nu iau niciodat nimic intre mese, <text:s text:c="2"/>dar v<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> mulumesc pentru amabilitate. snt n trecere pri<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span> Chicago i <text:s text:c="2"/>m-am gndit c ar fi bine s nu mai atep<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span> i s aduc scrisoarea de <text:s text:c="2"/>recomandaie acum. A<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> dori c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>teva informaii despre investiiile care <text:s text:c="2"/>se po<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span> face n acest ora.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Addison, un om scund, gras i rou la fa, cu f<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>vorii cruni care <text:s text:c="2"/>coborau p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n la lobul urechii i ni<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>te ochi cprui-cenuii, ageri, <text:s text:c="2"/>strlucitori  un o<text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span> m<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndru, vesel i m<text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span>l<text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span>mit de sine  molf<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ia mrul <text:s text:c="2"/>pe care-l luase i-l privea pe Cowperwo<text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span>d care vorbea. Dup cum se <text:s text:c="2"/>nt<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>mpl des n via, <text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span>ui Addison i plcea sau i displcea cineva la<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>prima, vedere i avea foarte mult ncredere n judecata sa asupra <text:s text:c="2"/>oamenilor. Pentru un conservatur ca Addison era aproape absurd felul <text:s text:c="2"/>n care, de la nceput, se simea atras de Cowperwood  un vin superior <text:s text:c="2"/>lui n toate privinele  nu at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t din cauza scrisorii de la Drexel, <text:s text:c="2"/>care sublinia geniul su financiar indiscutabil i avantajul pe care <text:s text:c="2"/>l-ar reprezenta pentru Chicago stabilirea t<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nrului n ora, dar mai <text:s text:c="2"/>ales din cauza privirii irezistibile a acestuia. Rezerva pe care <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood o meninea inflexibil avea ceva profund uman, care-l mica <text:s text:c="2"/>pe colegul su mai vrstnic. Fiecare n felul su era o adevrat <text:s text:c="2"/>enigm, t<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nrul din Philadelphia ns, desigur, o enigm mult mai <text:s text:c="2"/>sub<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>il, Addison, pentru toat lumea trecea drept ceteanul model, <text:s text:c="2"/>care se duce<text:span text:style-name="T1">a r</text:span>egulat la bise<text:span text:style-name="T1">r</text:span>ic ; el reprezenta un punct de vedere <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1">la c</text:span>are <text:span text:style-name="T1">Cowperwood </text:span>nu s-ar fi cobor<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t niciodat<text:span text:style-name="T1">. Amndoi oameni aprigi, avizi s obin tot ce se </text:span><text:s text:c="3"/>poate <text:soft-page-break/>obine de la via  dar Addison nu avea fora lui Cowperwood, <text:s text:c="2"/>fiindu-i team, foarte te<text:span text:style-name="T1">am</text:span> de rul pe care viaa ar fi putut s i-l <text:s text:c="2"/>pricin<text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span>ia<text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>c, O<text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span>ul din faa lui ns nu tia ce-i frica. Addi<text:span text:style-name="T1">so</text:span>n, <text:s text:c="2"/>cump<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tat, filantrop, aproba de form plicticoase conveniene sociale, <text:s text:c="2"/>ddea impresia c-i iube<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>te nevasta, de care se sturase p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n peste <text:s text:c="2"/>cap, si se desfta, in tain, aiurea. Omul dinaintea lui nu prea era <text:s text:c="2"/>dus la biseric, nu se destinua decit <text:span text:style-name="T1">prie</text:span>tenilor intimi, pe care <text:s text:c="2"/>i domina prin inteli<text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span>en, i fcea exact ce-i plcea.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Ei bine, uite, domnule Cowperwo<text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span>d, relu Addison. Noi, cei din <text:s text:c="2"/>Chicago, avem o prere <text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>t<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t de bun despre noi nine nct uneori ne e <text:s text:c="2"/>fric s spunem tot ce g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndim de team s nu fim luai puin drept <text:s text:c="2"/>ludro<text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span>. S<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntem ca mezinul fa<text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span>iliei, care tie c ar putea s-i <text:s text:c="2"/>snopeasc-n bti pe ceilal<text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>rai, dar n-o face pentru c nu vrea <text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>orice caz nu <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nc<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Deocamdat nu prea s<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntem frumo<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i, dar cine a <text:s text:c="2"/>pomenit biat <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>rumos n perioada de cretere? Nici o grij, p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n la <text:s text:c="2"/>urm tot o s fim. Pantalonii, pantofii, hainele i plriile ne rm<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n <text:s text:c="2"/>mici din ase n ase luni i de aceeea avem un aer puin demodat, dar <text:s text:c="2"/>hainele astea ur<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>te, domnule Cowperwood, ascund muchi i oase solide, <text:s text:c="2"/>i cnd ncepi s cunoti oraul, n-o s te mai uii at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t de mult la <text:s text:c="2"/>haine. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Domnul Addison <text:span text:style-name="T1">nc</text:span>hise puin ochii si rotu<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>zi i oneti care acum <text:s text:c="2"/>aveau o privire sever. Vocea i se <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n<text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>pri i brus<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span> cptase<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>un sunet <text:s text:c="2"/>metalic. <text:span text:style-name="T1">Cow</text:span>perwood<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>i ddea bine seama c interlocutorul <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>u er<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span> sincer ndrgostit de oraul lui de adopiune. Chicago era me<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>resa lui <text:s text:c="2"/>adorat. Dup o <text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>li<text:span text:style-name="T1">p</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1">,</text:span> pielea din jurul o<text:span text:style-name="T1">ch</text:span>ilor i se ncrei, expresia <text:s text:c="2"/>gurii se <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>m<text:span text:style-name="T1">bun</text:span> i zmbi.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> A vrea s-i spun ct mai mult, <text:span text:style-name="T1">continu </text:span>Ad<text:span text:style-name="T1">d</text:span>is<text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span>n. snt at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tea lucruri <text:s text:c="2"/>interesante de spus.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:span text:style-name="T1">Cowp</text:span>erwood l incuraj cu o privire bl<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n<text:span text:style-name="T1">d</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1">,</text:span> ceru <text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T1">am</text:span>nunte <text:span text:style-name="T1">despre </text:span>o anumit <text:span text:style-name="T1">industrie, apoi despre alta, despre o meserie sau alta</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">i despre </text:span><text:soft-page-break/><text:span text:style-name="T1">diferite profesiuni. Aici era o atmosfer care nu semna cu</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>cea din Philadelphia  mai aerisit, mai generoas<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Tendina de <text:s text:c="2"/>parvenire i de a trage ct mai multe foloase din resursele locale, <text:s text:c="2"/>caracteristic Vestului, lui Cowperwood i plcea, era un aspect al <text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T1">v</text:span>ieii, <text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span>ndiferent dac lui <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i va sluji sau nu. Are s-i foloseasc <text:s text:c="2"/>n carier, cine tie. <text:span text:style-name="T1">T</text:span>rebuia s-i tearg <text:span text:style-name="T1">trec</text:span>utul de fost <text:s text:c="2"/>pucria; avea deocamdat o nevast i doi copii  cel puin n faa <text:s text:c="2"/>legii  de care era hotr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t s se descotoroseasc (din punct de vedere <text:s text:c="2"/>financiar, ns, dorea s le dea tot sprijinul). Va avea nevoie de <text:s text:c="2"/>aceast atitudine entuziast i fr prejudeci a Vestului, ca s i se <text:s text:c="2"/>ierte indiferena i curajul cu care refuzase totdeauna s se supun <text:s text:c="2"/>convenienelor sociale. <text:span text:style-name="T2">Fac ce-mi place</text:span> era legea dup care se <text:s text:c="2"/>conducea, dar pentru asta trebuie s potoleasc i s nfr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ng <text:s text:c="2"/>prejudecile celorlali. Bancherul, dei nu prea maleabil, putea <text:s text:c="2"/>totui deveni un prieten de ndejde i util.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Oraul, domnule Addison, mi-a fcut o impresie ct se poate de <text:s text:c="2"/>bun, spuse Cowperwood, dup un timp, dei n sufletul lui recunotea <text:s text:c="2"/>c asta nu era dect in parte adevrat ; nu-i venea de loc s cread c <text:s text:c="2"/>p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n la urm se va resemna s triasc ntr-un loc plin de h<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rtoape i <text:s text:c="2"/>schele, cum era pe atunci Chicago. Din tren n-am vzut dec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t o parte <text:s text:c="2"/>din ora. mi place iureul vieii de aici. Cred c-i un ora de <text:s text:c="2"/>viitor. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Ai venit, cred, prin Fort-Wayne, spuse Addison, superior, i ai <text:s text:c="2"/>vzut partea cea mai ur<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t. Trebuie s-i art cartierele mai frumoase.</text:p>
