   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Perfect, zise simplu financiarul din Philadelphia. S<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntei ct se <text:s text:c="2"/>poate de amabil. Ar mai fi civa oameni pe care vreau s-i cunosc, <text:s text:c="2"/>adug Cowperwood, ridicndu-se i <text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span>it<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndu-se la ceas. Dau eu de clubul <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T2">Union</text:span> i singur. Unde se afl biroul lui <text:span text:style-name="T2">Arnee</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">l</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2"> &amp; Comp</text:span>?</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">C<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd l auzi pomenind de marea Societate a conservelor de carne, unul <text:s text:c="2"/>din depuntorii cei mai importani ai bncii sale, Addison schi un <text:s text:c="2"/>gest de ncuviinare. Acest <text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>nr, cu cel puin opt ani mai mi<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span> dec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t <text:s text:c="2"/>el, i ddea inpresia unui viitor <text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span>agnat al finanei.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">La dejunul de la <text:span text:style-name="T2">Union Club</text:span>, dup ce discut cu Arneel, un conservator <text:s text:c="2"/>corpolent i agresiv, i cu <text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span>scusi<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>ul preedinte al bursei, Cowperwood <text:s text:c="2"/>fcu cunotina unui grup eterogen de oameni ntre treizeci i cinci i <text:s text:c="2"/>aizeci i cinci de ani, str<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ni <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n jurul mesei, <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntr-un cabinet <text:s text:c="2"/>particular, cu mobil grea, de nuc negru sculptat, pe perete <text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>u <text:s text:c="2"/>portretele unor vechi ceteni ai oraului, i cu o tentativ artistic <text:s text:c="2"/>n vitrourile pestrie care mpodobeau ferestrele<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Asistena se <text:s text:c="2"/>compunea din oameni nali, scunzi, slabi sau obezi, bruni sau blonzi, <text:s text:c="2"/>cu ochi i flci care variau de la tipul tigru,<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>r<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>s i urs la tipul <text:s text:c="2"/>vulpe, dulu domesticit i buldog morocnos. n aceast societate <text:s text:c="2"/>aleas fiecare era cineva.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Lui Cowperwood i plcea <text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>t<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t domnul Addison c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t i domnul Arneel i-i <text:s text:c="2"/>considera <text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span>scusii i serioi. Anson Merrill, de asemenea, i pru <text:s/>interesant, un om mrunt, amabil i ngrijit, care su<text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span>era palate, <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>eciori i n general via luxoas de pe vremuri ; Addison <text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span>-l <text:s text:c="2"/>prezentase drept faimosul prin al colonialelor, negustorul de <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>run<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>e, cu ridicata i n detaliu, din Chicago.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Mai era i un anume domn Rambaud, unul din fondatorii societilor de <text:s text:c="2"/><text:soft-page-break/>cale ferat<text:span text:style-name="T1">;</text:span> Addison i se adres cu un zmbet jovial:</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Domnul Cowperwood a sosit de la Philadelphia i nu este nc singur<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>dac dorete Bau nu s piard <text:s text:c="2"/>ceva bani aici, la noi. N-ai <text:span text:style-name="T1">v</text:span>rea s-i vinzi o bucat, din pmntul la <text:s text:c="2"/>prost, pe care-l ai n nord-vest<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Rambaud  un om slab, palid, cu o barb neagr, un om cu mult for <text:s text:c="2"/>interioar, mbrcat, dup cum observase Cowperwood de la nceput, cu <text:s text:c="2"/>mai mult bun gust dec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t majoritatea celorlali  i arunc lui <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood o privire perspicace, dar rezervat, cum i <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ade bine unui <text:s text:c="2"/>om bine crescut; avea un z<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>mbet eni<text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span>mati<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>, dar binevoitor. Cowperwood i rspunse printr-o privire pe care Ram<text:span text:style-name="T1">b</text:span>aud n-a putut-o uita niciodat. Ochii lui Cowperwood exprimau mai <text:s text:c="2"/>mult dec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t ar fi putut exprima orice cuv<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nt. n loc s-i piard timpul <text:s text:c="2"/>cu glume uoare, domnul Rambaud prefer s-i explice anumite lucruri <text:s text:c="2"/>n legtur cu nord-vestul. Asta  i zicea el  l-ar putea interesa <text:s text:c="2"/>pe t<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nrul din Philadelphia.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Pentru un om care a dus o lupt cr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ncen ntr-una din marile metropole <text:s text:c="2"/>unde a avut de-a face cu tot felul de situaii, unele dubioase, altele <text:s text:c="2"/>plcute, cunoscnd fel de fel de oameni de la cei deceni, cumsecade i nelegtori, pn la, pislogi, pe care, cel puin n <text:s text:c="2"/>America i nt<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>lneti, fr doar i poate, n v<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rful piramidei sociale, <text:s text:c="2"/>n orice ora, mentalitatea, i semnificaia unui alt grup, din alt <text:s text:c="2"/>ora, nu se deo<text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>ebea prea, tare de ce cunotea el; i totui, dac te <text:s text:c="2"/>g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndeti bine, se deosebea.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Cowperwood tia acum c lumea se deosebete totdeauna ntruc<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tva, <text:s text:c="2"/>indiferent de perspectiva i mprejurrile din care o priveti, <text:s text:c="2"/>indiferent de clim sau de altceva. Pentru e<text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span>, trstura cea mai <text:s text:c="2"/>c<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>racteristic a omului o consti<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>uie firea lui ciudat, care-l poate <text:s text:c="2"/>face s devin orice sau l poate reduce la nimic, dup cum hotrsc <text:s text:c="2"/>timpul i condiiile exterioare date. n clipele lui de rgaz  cnd <text:s text:c="2"/>nu era prins de a<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>aceri i socoteli, de altminteri rare <text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>Cowperwood <text:s text:c="2"/>medita adeseori la sensul real al vie<text:span text:style-name="T1">ii.</text:span> Dac n-ar fi fost un mare <text:s text:c="2"/>financiar i, mai presus de an minunat organizator, ar fi putut <text:soft-page-break/>deveni <text:s text:c="2"/>un <text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T1">filozof</text:span> i<text:span text:style-name="T1">ndividuali</text:span>st remarcabil  o vocaie la, care<text:span text:style-name="T1"> dac s-ar fi gndit atunci </text:span>c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t de puin, i-ar <text:span text:style-name="T1">fi prut </text:span>absurd. Cariera lui, aa cum nelegea e<text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span>, trebuia, s fie legat<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> de aspectul material al vieii, ori mai degrab de o teorem de <text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span>radul trei i patru, sau de acele <text:s text:c="2"/>silogisme n legtur cu lucruri materiale care reprezentau <text:s text:c="2"/>bogia.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Venise aici s studieze cerinele generale i urgente din Middle Vest  <text:s text:c="2"/>s pun m<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>na, dac va <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>i n stare, pe fr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nele puterii i ale bogiei <text:s text:c="2"/>i<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>s se ridice la o faim unanim recunoscut. Din conversaiile pe <text:s text:c="2"/>care le avusese n dimineaa aceea aflase des<text:span text:style-name="T1">p</text:span>re natura i <text:s text:c="2"/>semnificaia abatoarelor, despre posibilitatea de extindere a cilor<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>ferate i a tran<text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>portului maritim i fluvial, despre ponderea uria a <text:s text:c="2"/>tranzaciilor imobiliare, a speculaiilor de cereale a ho<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>elurilor <text:s text:c="2"/>i a comerului de fierrie. Aflase despre existena unor fabrici care <text:s text:c="2"/>furnizau orice <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>el de maini  pentru automobile, pentru ascensoare, <text:s text:c="2"/>pentru maini de legat snopi, pentru mori de vint i aa, mai departe. <text:s text:c="2"/>n Chicago, orice nou industrie prea prosper. ntr-o discuie <text:s text:c="2"/>purtat cu prese dintele bursei din Chicago, pentru care avusese o <text:s text:c="2"/>scrisoare de recomandaie, aflase c foarte puine <text:s text:c="2"/>aciuni din Chicago se negociau la burs. Se fceau <text:s text:c="2"/>speculaii mai ales n legtur cu gr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ul, porumbi i tot soiul de <text:s text:c="2"/>cereale. La New <text:span text:style-name="T1">Y</text:span>ork se primeau dispoziii telegrafice din Chicago <text:s text:c="2"/>pentru jocul de burs <text:s text:c="2"/>al aciunilor mportante din Est  i nu se proceda niciodat altfel.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Privea aceti oameni, simpatici i politicoi, care discutau numai <text:s text:c="2"/>generaliti fr s-i destinuiasc planurile, i se ntreba cum o s <text:s text:c="2"/>rzbeasc el n aceast lume<text:span text:style-name="T1">. </text:span>Avea at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tea probleme de rezolvat! Nici <text:s text:c="2"/>unul din oamenii tia, care din punct de vedere social i profesional, <text:s text:c="2"/>erau agreabili, nu tia c fusese eliberat din nchisoare abia de <text:s text:c="2"/>cur<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd. Atitudinea lor fa de el, dac vor afla acest lucru, se va <text:s text:c="2"/>schimbat <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i mai era un lucru pe care nu-l tiau: c dei nsurat i <text:s text:c="2"/>tat a doi copii, avea de pn s divoreze i s se nsoare cu fata <text:s text:c="2"/>care acum luase locul nevestei lui<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"><text:soft-page-break/> Te in<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>ereseaz ntr-adevr Nord-Vestul? <text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span> ntreb domnul Rambaud <text:s text:c="2"/>spre sf<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>r<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>itul dejunului <text:span text:style-name="T1">:</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>prea interesat. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Dup ce termin aici, asta a vrea s fac. Cred <text:s text:c="2"/>c am s m reped pn acolo. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> <text:span text:style-name="T1"><text:s/></text:span>Nu vrei s te prezint unor oameni <text:s text:c="2"/>interesani, ca<text:span text:style-name="T1">r</text:span>e tocmai se duc la Fargo i Duluth ? Pleac joi o<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>main cu mai muli ceteni din Chieago i civa din Est. Mi-ar face <text:s text:c="2"/>plcere s vii cu noi. Eu nu merg dec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n la Minneapolis. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Cowperwood accept i-i mulumi. Urm apoi <text:s text:c="2"/>o<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>lung conversaie despre Nord-Vest, <text:s text:c="2"/>despre cherestea, gr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>u, v<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nzri de pmint, vite i despre viitoarele uzine<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Soarta <text:s text:c="2"/>oraelor Fargo, Minneapolis i Duluth, att din punct de vedere <text:s text:c="2"/>financiar c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t i ca municipii, forma subiectul principal al conversaiei. Firete, domnul Rambaud, directorul unor ntinse reele <text:s text:c="2"/>de cale ferat, care ptrunseser n aceast regiune, avea mari <text:s text:c="2"/>sperane pentru viitor. Cowperwood simea instincti<text:span text:style-name="T1">v</text:span> interesul pe <text:s text:c="2"/>care-l prezentau aceste probleme; gazul aerian, tramvaiele, <text:s text:c="2"/>tranzaciile de bunuri funciare, bncile, indi<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>erent n ce localitate <text:s text:c="2"/>se gseau constituiau preocuparea lui principal.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">n cele din urm <text:s text:c="2"/>prsi clubul ca s se nt<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>lneasc cu alte persoane, lsnd n urm <text:s text:c="2"/>puin din puternica lui personalitate. At<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t domnul Addison c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t i <text:s text:c="2"/>domnul Rambaud, printre alii, erau sincer convingi c acest t<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nr <text:s text:c="2"/>venit din Philadelphia era unul din oamenii cei mai remarcabili din <text:s text:c="2"/>c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i cunoscuser vreodat. i, de fapt, Cowperwood tcuse aproape tot <text:s text:c="2"/>timpul  <text:s text:c="2"/>se mulumise s asculte.</text:p>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2"><text:span text:style-name="Label">Capitolul III </text:span><text:line-break/>O sear la Chicago</text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">D<text:span text:style-name="T1">up </text:span>prima <text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span>ui vizit la banca prezidat de <text:span text:style-name="T1">Addison</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">i </text:span>dup <text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span> mas intim n <text:s/>casa acestui<text:span text:style-name="T1">a,</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">Cowperwood </text:span>hotr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> n-ar fi fost frumos din partea <text:s text:c="3"/>lui s-i ascund adevrul. Addison era u<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span> om prea influent i cu multe <text:s text:c="2"/>relaii i, afar de asta, lui Cowperwood i plcea foarte mult <text:s text:c="2"/>bancherul. D<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndu-i seama <text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span> acest om ine la el, c pare fascinat, i <text:s text:c="2"/>fcu o mic vizit matinal, dup<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>ce se intoarse de la Fargo unde se <text:s text:c="2"/>dusese la sugestia domnului Rambaud. nainte de a se <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntoarce la <text:s text:c="2"/>Philadelphia <text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span>sise de cuviin s mai mearg o dat la domnul Addison, <text:s text:c="2"/>hotr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t s-i ofere o versiune atenuat<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> a nenorocirilor sale anterioare, <text:s text:c="2"/>cont<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd c simpatia pe care i-o arta noul su prieten o s-l fac s-i <text:s text:c="2"/>judece cazul cu mai puin asprime<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> i spuse toat povestea : cum <text:s text:c="2"/>fusese condamnat, la Philadelphia, pentru delapidare, i cum i <text:s text:c="2"/>ispise pedeapsa la <text:span text:style-name="T1">E</text:span>astern Penitenciary. i spuse de asemenea c vrea <text:s text:c="2"/>s divoreze i c inteniona s se recstoreasc<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Addison, dei nu avea fora lui Cowperwood, era totui n felul su un <text:s text:c="2"/>om tare; i plcu curajul lui Cowperwood i mrturisirea fcut era cu <text:s text:c="2"/>siguran un lucru pe care el n-ar fi fost n atare s-l fac. <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i flata <text:s text:c="2"/>i gustul su pentru senzaional. n faa lui se <text:span text:style-name="T1">af</text:span>la, un om care <text:s text:c="2"/>cobor<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>se ultima treapt a decderii, fusese t<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>r<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n noroi i care <text:s text:c="2"/>acum se ridica din nou, puternic, plin de sperane i de d<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rzenie. La <text:s text:c="2"/>Chicago, Addison cunotea muli oameni foarte respectabili, al cror <text:s text:c="2"/>debut n-ar fi rezistat la o examinare mai amnunit. i totui asta <text:s text:c="2"/>nu supra pe nimeni. Unii duceau o via monden, alii ins nu, dar <text:s text:c="2"/>toi erau oameni puternici. De ce oare n-ar avea i Cowperwood dreptul <text:s text:c="2"/>s-o ia de la <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nceput? <text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span> privi cu luare aminte  se uit la ochii lui, <text:s text:c="2"/>la trupul lui puternic, la chipul neted, frumos, umbrit de o <text:s text:c="2"/><text:soft-page-break/>mustcioar. Apoi i <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntinse <text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span>na.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Domnule Cowperwood, rosti n cele din urm, cutnd cuvintele cele <text:s text:c="2"/>mai potrivite, e inutil s-i spun c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t de mult apreciez mrturisirea <text:s text:c="2"/>dumitale. M-a miscat i mi-a prut bine c mi te-ai destinuit. Nu <text:s text:c="2"/>trebuie s mai vorbeti despre asta. Din clipa <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n care ai intrat la <text:s text:c="2"/>mine am avut impresia c eti un om cu totul deosebit; acum snt <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>igur<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>N-ai <text:s text:c="2"/>nevoie s te ascu<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>zi n faa mea. N-am trit cincizeci i mai bine de <text:s text:c="2"/>ani aici fr s cunose lumea ! Eti binevenit n aceast banc i <text:s text:c="2"/>n casa mea atta timp <text:s/>c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t asta, i va face plcere. Pe viitor <text:s text:c="2"/>ne vom mrgini s ne supunem cerinelor de moment. A vrea foarte mult <text:s text:c="2"/>s te instalezi la Chicago, pentru c mie<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>personal mi placi. Dac te <text:s text:c="2"/>hotrti s te stabileti aici, snt sigur c-i voi putea fi de folos <text:s text:c="2"/>i dumneata mi vei putea fi de folos mie. Nu te mai gindi la ce mi-ai <text:s text:c="2"/>spus, iar n ceea ce m privete, am nchis acest subiect pentru <text:s text:c="2"/>totdeauna. Dumneata ai de dat o btlie. i urez succes. Vei avea de <text:s text:c="2"/>la mine tot sprijinul pe care, n mod cinstit, i-l pot da. Uit, ce <text:s text:c="2"/>mi-ai spus i de ndat ce-i rezolvi chestiunile dumitale familiale, <text:s text:c="2"/>adu-i nevasta aici.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Dup care Cowperwood lu trenul i plec na<text:span text:style-name="T1">p</text:span>oi <text:s text:c="2"/>la Philadelphia.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Aileen, i spuse cnd o ntilni  fata venise s-l atepte la gar  <text:s text:c="2"/>cred c viitorul nostru este n vest. Am vizitat Fargo i <text:s text:c="2"/>mprejurimile, dar nu cred c e nevoie s mergem atit de departe. <text:s text:c="2"/>Acolo, ct vezi cu ochii e numai iarb, c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>mp i indieni. Cum te-ai <text:s text:c="2"/>simit ntr-o cas din scnduri ? o ntreb n glum, iar la gustarea <text:s text:c="2"/>de diminea s n-ai altceva, dec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t erpi cu clopoei prjii i cini <text:s text:c="2"/>de prerie? Crezi c ai rezista ?</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Da! exclam Aileen vesel, str<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ng<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndu-i de bra, dup ce se <text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span>rcaser <text:s text:c="2"/>ntr-o trsur nchis. Eu rezist dac reziti i tu. Cu tine merg <text:s text:c="2"/>oriunde. Am s-mi fac o rochie de indian frumoas, acoperit de <text:s text:c="2"/>mrgele, cu buci de piele, o plrie cu pene ca a lor, i...</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Da, sigur! Rochii frumoase ntr-o colib de <text:span text:style-name="T1">mi</text:span>neri ! Aa crezi tu.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:soft-page-break/></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"><text:span text:style-name="T1"> Dac </text:span><text:s text:c="2"/>n-a ine at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t la rochii, i-ar trece repede <text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span>ubirea pentru mine, <text:s text:c="2"/>zise ea cu voioie. Vai, ce <text:span text:style-name="T1">b</text:span>ine-mi pare c te-ai ntors ! </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Pcat n<text:span text:style-name="T1">umai c a</text:span>colo n-am cine <text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>ie ce pers<text:span text:style-name="T1">pective la Chi</text:span>cago. Cred c s<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntem <text:s text:c="2"/>sortii <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span> <text:s/>trim la Chicago. Am investit capital la Fargo i o s fim nevoii s <text:s text:c="2"/>mergem i acolo din cnd n cnd dar cred c tot la Chicago o s ne <text:s text:c="2"/>stabilim. N-a<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>vrea s m mai duc singur. Nu-mi p<text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span>ace... i str<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n<text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>e <text:s text:c="2"/>m<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>na. Dac nu putem pune totul la punct numaidec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t, va trebui la <text:s text:c="2"/>nceput s te prezint drept nevasta mea<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Ce se aude cu domnul Steger? i aminti ea. Se<text:span text:style-name="T1"> g</text:span>ndea la eforturile <text:s text:c="2"/>lui Steger pentru a o convinge pe doamna Cowperwood s accepte <text:s text:c="2"/>divorul.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Absolut nimic.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Pcat ! oft Ailee<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> <text:span text:style-name="T1">E</text:span>i, nu te mai necji, se poate i mai ru.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">i venise n minte perioada nchisorii  i ea tot la asta se gind<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>a.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Dup o examinare <text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span> condiiilor din Chicago, Frank hotr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> de comun acord <text:s text:c="2"/>cu ea s se mute ntr-un ora din Vest de ndat ce<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>va fi posibil.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Ar fi inu<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>il s insistm asupra primilor trei ani n care ncetul cu <text:s text:c="2"/>ncetul, Cowperwood se desprinse total de Philadelphia i ncepu o nou <text:s text:c="2"/>via la Chicago. O bucat de vreme se mulumi s se duc din cnd n <text:s text:c="2"/>cnd la Fargo i n special la Chicago unde Walter <text:span text:style-name="T1">W</text:span>helpley, <text:s text:c="2"/>secretarul su, conform directivelor lui, se ocupa de construirea <text:s text:c="2"/>unor cldiri comerciale n oraul Fargo, a unei mici linii de tramvai i de amenajarea unui teren pentru un mare <text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>rg<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Aceast foarte <text:s text:c="2"/>interesant iniiativ se chema <text:span text:style-name="T2">Societa</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">t</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">ea de Construcii i <text:s text:c="2"/>Transport din Fargo</text:span>, sub preedinia lui Frank A. Cowperwood. Asociatul <text:s text:c="2"/>lui din Philadelphia, domnul Harper Steger, era atunci nsrcinat cu <text:s text:c="2"/>supravegherea contractelor.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:soft-page-break/></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Pentru o scurt bucat de vreme locuise la hotelul <text:span text:style-name="T2">Tremont</text:span> din Chicago, <text:s text:c="2"/>mrginindu-se, din cauza prezenei lui Aileen, s salute oamenii <text:s text:c="2"/>importani, pe care-i cunoscuse cu ocazia primei sale vizite acolo, <text:s text:c="2"/>d<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd pur i simplu din cap, deoca<text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span>dat. Se g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndea serios s <text:s text:c="2"/>organizeze un birou de schimb  s se asociez<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span> cu un agent bine <text:s text:c="2"/>cunoscut, care, fr prea mari ambiii personale, s-l pun la curent</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">cu tranzaciile <text:s text:c="2"/>bursei din Chicago i s-i-spun care erau persoanele i afacerile</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">importante din ora. O dat o lu pe Aileen cu el ia Fargo, unde, <text:s text:c="2"/>aceasta, cu un a<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>r plictisit de nepsare superioar, urm<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rise, <text:s text:c="2"/>alturi de el, <text:s text:c="2"/>aspec<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>ul oraului n dezvoltare. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Vai, Frank! exclam Aileen, vz<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd <text:s text:c="2"/>hotelul <text:s text:c="2"/>de lemn, simplu, cu patru etaje, strada lung i <text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span>rt, fortotind cu <text:s text:c="2"/>lume, prvliile blate, din lemn i crmid, irurile de cldiri <text:s text:c="2"/>triste, i peste tot numai strzi nepavate. Aileen ntr-un frumos <text:s text:c="2"/>costum taior, <text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>ochet, sigur de sine, plin de vioiciune, vanitoas i <text:s text:c="2"/>cu o tendin<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> pronunat ctre a elegan ostentativ, forma un <text:s text:c="2"/>contrast izbitor cu modestia aspr, cu indiferena oamenilor din acea, <text:s text:c="2"/>nou metropol fa de farmecul lor personal. Cred c nu te-ai g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndit <text:s text:c="2"/>serios c am putea tri aici.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Se ntreba, ce relaii ar putea s-i fac i ce posibiliti avea s <text:s text:c="2"/>strluceasc ntr-o astfel de, societate. Chiar dac Frank ar deveni <text:s text:c="2"/>un om foarte bogat, mult mai bogat dec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t fusese n trecut  la ce i-ar <text:s text:c="2"/>servi toate astea aici?  la Philadelphia, naintea, falimentului lui <text:s text:c="2"/>i nainte ca legtura secret dintre ei s <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>i fost bnuit, ncepuse <text:s text:c="2"/>(mcar at<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>) s primeasc foarte bine. Dac <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n momentul acela ar fi <text:s text:c="2"/>fost nevasta lui, i-ar fi fost foarte uor s ptrund n lumea bun <text:s text:c="2"/>din Philadelphia. Aici ns, dumne<text:span text:style-name="T1">z</text:span>eule ! Aileen strimb din nsucul <text:s text:c="2"/>ei frumos.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Ce loc groaznic, fu singurul ei comentariu n legtur cu acest ora <text:s text:c="2"/><text:soft-page-break/>agitat, unul din cele m<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>i promitoare din Vest.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Chicago, ns, cu v<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rtejul ameitor al dezvoltrii sale, st<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rni imediat <text:s text:c="2"/>interesul lui Aileen. Dei <text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>ra prins cu numeroase <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nt<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>lniri de afaceri, <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood avea grij ca Aileen s nu se plictiseasc<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> O trimitea s<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>fac cumprturi la magazinele din preajm i seara o punea s-i <text:s text:c="2"/>povesteasc pe unde <text:span text:style-name="T1">fusese.</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>Aileen i urma sfatul i ieea ntr-o trsur deschis <text:s text:c="2"/>elegant mbrcat, cu <text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span> plrie mare de cu<text:span text:style-name="T1">loare</text:span> cafenie <text:span text:style-name="T1">care-i </text:span>accentua, <text:s text:c="2"/>tenul tra<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>dafiriu, i p<text:span text:style-name="T1">rul</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>auriu rocat<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> De mai multe ori, dup mas, se plimba cu trsura pe <text:s text:c="2"/>strzile principale ale oraului,</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">C<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd Ail<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>en avu pentru prima oar prilejul s a<text:span text:style-name="T1">d</text:span>mire frumuseea i <text:s text:c="2"/>luxul din Prairie Avenue, North Shore Drive, Michigan Avenue i din <text:s text:c="2"/>noile i somptuoasele locuine din Ashland Boulevard, nconjurat de <text:s text:c="2"/>grdini, atmosfera, nzuinele, spe- ranele i savoarea viitorului <text:s text:c="2"/>ora o tuiburar exact cum l tulburaser i pe Cowperwood.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Toate aceste case luxoase fuseser doar de puin vreme ridicate. n Chicago oamenii cu faim se <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>mbogiser<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>, ca i ei, de cur<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd. Aileen <text:s text:c="2"/>uita c nu era nc soia lui Cowperwood ; n <text:span text:style-name="T1">sinea </text:span>ei se socotea ca atare. Majoritatea strzilor de culoare brun-deschis aveau un aspect <text:s text:c="2"/>plcut, tivite cu pomi tineri, nu demult rsdii, <text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>u peluze verzi <text:s text:c="2"/>frumos tunse, ferestrele caselor mpodobite cu umbrare i perdele n <text:s text:c="2"/>culori vii, cu dantel la captul de jos, prin, care sufla o adiere de <text:s text:c="2"/>iunie, un drum cenuiu de macadam z<text:span text:style-name="T1">d</text:span>r<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>nuros  toate astea o atrgeau<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>ntr-una din plimbri s-au dus mpreun de-a lungul lacului pe North <text:s text:c="2"/>Shore Drive, iar Aileen, privind apa de u<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span> verde albstrui, p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nzele <text:s text:c="2"/>br<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>ilor din deprtare, pescruii i apoi casele noi i luminoase, se <text:s text:c="2"/>g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndea c odat va fi cu sigurun stp<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>na uneia din aceste splendide <text:s text:c="2"/>locuine. Ce m<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndr va fi atunci! Ce <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>rumos se va <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>mbrca! Vor avea, <text:s text:c="2"/>desigur, o <text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>as i mai frumoas ca cea a lui Frank de la Philadelphia, <text:s text:c="2"/>cu saloane imense i o sufragerie unde va putea da baluri i mese, n <text:s text:c="2"/>care va <text:soft-page-break/>primi, mpreun cu Frank, lumea bogat din Chicago ca pe e<text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span>alii <text:s text:c="2"/>lor<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Frank, crezi c o s ajungem s avem i noi odat o cas frumoas ca <text:s text:c="2"/>astea? ntreb Aileen, r<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>vnind la ceea ce vedea.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> tii ce m-am g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndit? i spuse Frank. Dac-i place cartierul sta, o <text:s text:c="2"/>s cumprm un teren aici i-o s-l pstrm. Cum <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>mi fac ceva relaii <text:s text:c="2"/>printre oamenii de care am nevoie i vd cum m descurc, <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>o<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>strui<text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span> o cas  ceva ntr-adevr frumos, n-avea <text:s text:c="2"/>grij. nt<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i s aranjez cu divorul i pe urm ncepem. <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntre timp, dac-o fi s ne stabilim aici, n-ar s<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>rica s procedm mai <text:s text:c="2"/>cu discreie. Ei, ce zici ?</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Se fcuse cin<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>i i jumtate, momentul cel mai plcut al unei zile de <text:s text:c="2"/>var<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Fusese foarte cald, acum ns se rcorise. oseaua umbrit de <text:s text:c="2"/>casele din pariea de vest a s<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>rzii prea mbibat de un aer <text:s text:c="2"/>a<text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span>eitor, n care dansau firele de praf. C<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t vedeai cu ochii numai <text:s text:c="2"/>trsuri, singura distracie monden la Chicago, unde oamenii bogai <text:s text:c="2"/>aveau at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t de puin prilejul s-i etaleze bogia. Ierarhia social nu <text:s text:c="2"/>era <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nc r<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nduit clar i armonios. Zngnitul harnaamentului de <text:s text:c="2"/>nichel, argint, uneori chiar aurit, era simbolul material al <text:s text:c="2"/>aspiraiilor pe scara societii, dac nu chiar al realizrilor<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Aici,<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>oamenii venind de la treburi  de la birou sau de la uzin  se <text:s text:c="2"/>grbeau spre cas, de-a lungul acestei osele excepionale din sudul <text:s text:c="2"/>oraului Via Appia din South Side, toi aspirani grbii la mari <text:s text:c="2"/>averi. Oameni bogai care se cunoscuser ntmpltor n afaceri, aici <text:s text:c="2"/>se salu<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>au<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Fete elegante, biei cu educaie aleas, femei <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>rumoase <text:s text:c="2"/>se duceau n ora n docare, trsuri, n echipaje de ultimul tip <text:s text:c="2"/>i-i conduceau acas, dup plictiseala ocupaiilor zilnice, taii i <text:s text:c="2"/>fraii, rudele i prietenii. Atmosfera era plin, de aspiraii mondene, optimiste, plin de tineree, de afeciune i de o nfloritoare <text:s text:c="2"/>via material care se recrea aci n desftare. Cai ageri, frumoi, <text:s text:c="2"/>rasai, c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>te unul sau c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>te doi, cu hamuri zornitoare, se ntreceau <text:s text:c="2"/>de-a lungul oselei largi, tivit cu iarb; casele sclipeau ca o <text:s text:c="2"/>mrturie a bogie<text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span> i a mulumirii fericiilor proprietari.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"><text:soft-page-break/> O ! exclam Aileen brusc, privind brbaii nali i viguroi, <text:s text:c="2"/>femeile frumoase, fetele i bieii, observ<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd saluturile i <text:s text:c="2"/>plecciunile schimbate ntre ei, emoionat i ui<text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span>it de tot acest <text:s text:c="2"/>romantism, tare-a <text:span text:style-name="T1">vr</text:span>ea s triesc n Chicago. Cred c c e mai plcut <text:s text:c="2"/>ca <text:s text:c="2"/>n Philadelphia. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"><text:span text:style-name="T1">Cowperwood, c</text:span>ruia ajunsese s-i mearg at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t de <text:span text:style-name="T1">ru la Philadelphia, </text:span>cu toate ca<text:span text:style-name="T1">liti</text:span>le <text:s text:c="2"/>lui imens<text:span text:style-name="T1">e, strnse din buze. Mustaa lui frumoas parc i</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>accentua i mai mult expresia sfidtoare<text:span text:style-name="T1">. Caii pe</text:span> care-i m<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>na erau <text:s text:c="2"/>desv<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rii, zveli i nrva<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i  animale rsfate. N-ar fi tolerat <text:s text:c="2"/>nici n ruptul capului o m<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>roag. M<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>na cum numai un om care iubete <text:s text:c="2"/>caii putea s-o fac, comunicindu-le temperamentul i energia sa. <text:s text:c="2"/>Aileen sta l<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ng ei, m<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i cu capul sus.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Uite ce frumoas e, remarcau femeile care treceau pe l<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ng ea. Ce <text:s text:c="2"/>fat! Praf te face, ziceau sau g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndeau brbaii.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Ai vzut-o? <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntreb un biat pe sora lui.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Nu-i lua, n seam, Aileen, spuse Cowperwood, cu o hotr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>re care se <text:s text:c="2"/>mpotrivea nfr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ngerii. O s facem parte din lumea lor. N-avea nici 0 <text:s text:c="2"/>grij. Ai s capei tot ce vrei, ba chiar mai mult.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Degetele lui comunicau o vibraie <text:span text:style-name="T1">h</text:span>amurilor i cailor, un curent <text:s text:c="2"/>misterios izvor<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t dinluntrul lui<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>Remarcabilul su dinamism insufla cailor o <text:span text:style-name="T1">v</text:span>ioiciune copilreasc. Se <text:s text:c="2"/>nflcraser, ridicau capetele gi <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>fneau. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Aileen ardea de nerbdare <text:s text:c="2"/> plin de speran<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>e, vanitoas  s <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>ie doamna Frank Algernon Cowperwood, aici, n Chicago, s aib o locuin superb, s trimit <text:s text:c="2"/>oamenilor invitaii, care s <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>ie considerate porunci i crora s le <text:s text:c="2"/>rspund lumea ntreag ! </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Doamne, doamne, o<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>t ea, ce mult a vrea <text:s text:c="2"/>ca toate astea s se ndeplineasc acum, imediat. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Viaa nu te cru de <text:s text:c="2"/>frm<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntri i zbucium nici chiar cnd atingi culmile cele mai nalte. <text:s text:c="2"/>Dincolo de ele va exista totdeanna tentaia, mirajul infinitului cu <text:s text:c="2"/><text:soft-page-break/>n<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>sf<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rita sa durere. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="lg">O, <text:span text:style-name="T1">v</text:span>ia<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>! o tinere<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>e <text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span> ndejdi! o, timp!<text:line-break/>O, iluzii de durere <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n<text:span text:style-name="T1">ar</text:span>ipa<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>e, crora te<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>ma le d g<text:span text:style-name="T1">h</text:span>es!</text:p>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2"><text:span text:style-name="Label">Capitolul IV</text:span> <text:line-break/>Peter Laughlin &amp; Comp.</text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Cowperwood era foarte mulumit de asociaia pe care o realiz cu un <text:s text:c="2"/>fost agent la bursa din Chicago, Peter Laughlin. Laughlin, un om nalt <text:s text:c="2"/>i slab, juca la burs i trise cea mai mare parte a vieii lui la <text:s text:c="2"/>Chicago, venit din Missouri de pe cnd era copil. Agentul de burs <text:s text:c="2"/>tipic, de coal veche. Semna la chip cu Andrew Jackson<text:note text:id="ftn1" text:note-class="footnote"><text:note-citation>1</text:note-citation><text:note-body>
      <text:p text:style-name="Footnote"><text:span text:style-name="T2">Andrew Jackson </text:span>(1767-1845) preedinte al Statelor Unite. </text:p></text:note-body></text:note>, iar la trup cu Henry Clay<text:note text:id="ftn2" text:note-class="footnote"><text:note-citation>2</text:note-citation><text:note-body>
      <text:p text:style-name="Footnote"><text:span text:style-name="T2">Henry <text:s text:c="2"/>Clay </text:span>(1771<text:span text:style-name="T1">-</text:span>1852)om de stat american<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p></text:note-body></text:note>... Davy Crockett<text:note text:id="ftn3" text:note-class="footnote"><text:note-citation>3</text:note-citation><text:note-body>
      <text:p text:style-name="Footnote"><text:span text:style-name="T2">David Croke</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">t</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">t </text:span>(1786 1836) grnicer american, a murit apr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd <text:s/>fortreaa Alamo din Texas<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p></text:note-body></text:note> ..<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Long John Wentworth<text:note text:id="ftn4" text:note-class="footnote"><text:note-citation>4</text:note-citation><text:note-body>
      <text:p text:style-name="Footnote"><text:span text:style-name="T2">Sir John </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">W</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">ent</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">w</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">orth </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T10">(1737-1820)</text:span>  <text:s/>guvernator colonial <text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>New <text:span text:style-name="T1">H</text:span>ampshire,</text:p></text:note-body></text:note>.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Lui Cowperwood <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i plceau nc de foarte t<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nr oamenii originali, care <text:s text:c="2"/>i ei l plceau. Putea, dac-i ddea osteneala, s neleag i s <text:s text:c="2"/>fie neles de orice om, indiferent de psihologia fiecruia. n timpul <text:s text:c="2"/>primelor sale peregrinri n La Salle Street lu informaii despre cei <text:s text:c="2"/>mai buni ageni de burs, pe care-i punea s fac, ca s-i ncerce i <text:s text:c="2"/>s-i cunoasc mai bine, mici treburi pentru el. i astfel, ntr-o bun <text:s text:c="2"/>zi, ddu peste btr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nul Peter Laughlin, comerciant de gr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>u i porumb <text:s text:c="2"/>care-i avea biroul n <text:s text:c="2"/>La Salle Street lng Madison Street i care fcea nite afaceri <text:s text:c="2"/>modeste, specul<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd, pentru el i pentru alii, cereale i aciuni de <text:s text:c="2"/>ci ferate din Est. Laughlin era un american ager i prudent, <text:s text:c="2"/>probabil de origine scoian, i care avea toate defectele tradiionale americane  st<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ngcia, mania de a <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>njura, de a mesteca foi de <text:s text:c="2"/>tutun i alte mici metehne. <text:s text:c="2"/>Lui Cowperwood i fu de ajuns s se uite la el ca s-i dea, seama c <text:s text:c="2"/>Peter Laughlin e o surs inepuizabil de informaii despre fiecare <text:s text:c="2"/>locuitor cu vaz <text:s text:c="2"/>din Chicago  <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i nu<text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span>ai acest lucru era de mare importan. i unde mai <text:s text:c="2"/>pui c Peter Luughilin era un om <text:soft-page-break/>deschis, simplu i<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>fr pretenii, <text:s/>caliti pe care Cowperwood le socotea de nepreuit.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">n ulimii trei ani Laughlin pierduse, o dat sau de dou ori, muli <text:s text:c="2"/>bani n tot soiul de tentative infructuoase de acaparare, n urma <text:s text:c="2"/>crora credea c a devenit mai prudent sau n tot cazul nce<text:span text:style-name="T1">p</text:span>use<text:span text:style-name="T1"> s</text:span>-i <text:s text:c="2"/>fie fric.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Exact omul de care am nevoie, i zise Cowperwood. i astfel, <text:s text:c="2"/>ntr-o bun zi se duse la Laughlin, hotr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t s deschid un cont, nu <text:s text:c="2"/>prea mare, la el.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Henry, l auzi pe Laughlin  cnd intr n biroul spaios, dar cam <text:s text:c="2"/>prfuit al acestuia  adre<text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>ndu-se unui t<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nr funcionar care avea un <text:s text:c="2"/>a<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>r solemn, un secretar perfect pentru Peter Laughlin, adu-mi te rog <text:s text:c="2"/>aciunile alea din Pittsburg i Lake Erie. Vz<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndu-l pe Cowperwood care <text:s text:c="2"/>atepta, adug : Cu ce v pot fi de folos?</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Cowperwood zmbi. Ce curios pronun cuvntul <text:span text:style-name="T2">aciuni</text:span>, i spuse el. <text:s/>Ei bravo, mi p<text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span>ace omul sta<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Se prezent ca venind din Philadelphia i i mrturisi c-l interesau <text:s text:c="2"/>foarte mult iniiativele financiare din Chicago, c era gata s <text:s text:c="2"/>investeasc bani n orice aciuni care promit s creasc i mai cu <text:s text:c="2"/>seam c era dornic s intre n asociaii, de preferin n cele de <text:s text:c="2"/>utilitate public, destinate s se dezvolte o dat cu oraul. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Btr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nul Laughlin  om de aizeci de ani, avea, fotoliul su la burs <text:s text:c="2"/>i o avere de aproximativ dou sute de mii de dolari  i arunc lui <text:s text:c="2"/>Frank o privire amuzat. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Dac ai fi venit aici acum zece sau <text:s text:c="2"/>cincisprezece ani, ai fi putut c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tiga bani n multe afaceri. De <text:s text:c="2"/>pild<text:span text:style-name="T1">,</text:span> existau atunci nite societi de gaze unde s-au bgat biei ca<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>Otway i Apperson ; sau liniile de tramvaie. Eu snt acela c<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>re i-a <text:s text:c="2"/>spus lui Eddie Parkinson<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>c poate scoate bani buni dac organizeaz, <text:s/>Linia <text:span text:style-name="T2">North State Street</text:span>. n schimb mi-a, promis c dac afacerea <text:s text:c="2"/>reuete <text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span>i d i mie un pachet d<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>aciuni: de dat nu mi-a dat <text:soft-page-break/>niciodat nimic, dar nici nu mi-am pus mare <text:s text:c="2"/>ndejde n el, adug Lau<text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span>hlin cu resemnare i cu un z<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>mbet <text:s text:c="2"/>indulgent. <text:span text:style-name="T1">S</text:span>nt un om de afaceri care a vzut prea multe... De altfel, <text:s text:c="2"/>acum tot nu mai e acolo. L-au distrus oamenii l<text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span>i Michaels i ai lui <text:s text:c="2"/>Kennelily. De, dac erai aici acum zece-cincisprezece ani puteai <text:s text:c="2"/>ctiga i dumneata ceva. Da<text:span text:style-name="T1">&apos;</text:span> ce rost mai are s ne <text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span>ndim la asta? <text:s/>Azi, aciunile se v<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd la aproape o sut aizeci bucata<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Cowperwood zmbi.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Vd, domnule Laughlin, c lu<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>rezi de mult la bursa de aici. Am <text:s text:c="2"/>impresia c tii multe despre felul n care s-a lucrat pe aici n <text:s text:c="2"/>trecut.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Da, din 1852, preciz btr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nul<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Avea un smo<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span> de pr des care-i edea <text:s text:c="2"/>n sus, ca o creast de coco, brbia proeminent i un nas uor <text:s text:c="2"/>acvilin, pomeii<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>ieii i obrajii subiri, cu pielea de culoare nchis, privirea <text:s text:c="2"/>limpede i ptrunztoare, ca de r<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>s. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> La drept vorbind, domnule <text:s text:c="2"/>Laughlin, continu Cowperwood, motivul adevrat pentru care m aflu <text:s text:c="2"/>n Chicago este c vreau s gsesc un asociat <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n afacerile de burs. <text:s text:c="2"/>Deocamdat eu snt bancher i agent de schimb n Est. Am firm la <text:s text:c="2"/>Philadelphia ai fotoliu att la bursa de acolo c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t i la cea din New <text:s text:c="2"/>York. Mai am unele afaceri i n oraul Fargo. Toate ageniile m <text:s text:c="2"/>cunosc. Dumneata ai aici un fotoliu la burs i fr ndoial c <text:s text:c="2"/>lucrezi cu New York-ul sau cu Philadelphia. Noua noastr firm, dac <text:s text:c="2"/>bineneles vei voi s te asociezi cu mine, <text:span text:style-name="T1">v</text:span>a putea trata direct cu <text:s text:c="2"/>aceste dou orae. <text:span text:style-name="T1">C</text:span>eea ce- m privete am multe relaii bune n afar. <text:s text:c="2"/>M g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndesc s m stabilesc definitiv la Chicago. N-ai vrea s lucrm <text:s text:c="2"/>mpreun? Nu crezi c ne-am nelege? </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Cowperwood avea obiceiul, c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd <text:s text:c="2"/>voia s-i seduc interlocutorul, s-i ciocneasc degetele celor dou <text:s text:c="2"/>m<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ini, deget cu deget i n acelai timp s z<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>mbeasc radios, av<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n <text:s text:c="2"/>ochi o lumin cald, magnetic i aparent afectuoas. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"><text:span text:style-name="T1">D</text:span>e fapt <text:s text:c="2"/>btr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nul Peter Laughlin ajunsese la <text:span text:style-name="T1">momentul </text:span>psihologic n care <text:soft-page-break/>dorea s se <text:s text:c="2"/>iveasc o <text:s text:c="2"/>ast<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>el de ocazie. <text:span text:style-name="T1"><text:s/>T</text:span>ria singur, nu fusese niciodat nsurat. Nu gsise <text:s text:c="2"/>femeia, care s se <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>mpace cu firea lui ciudat. De fapt, nu prea <text:s text:c="2"/>cunotea femeile, leg<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>urile lui se mrgineau la acele relaii triste <text:s text:c="2"/>i ieftine pe care le putea dob<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndi prin banii oferii, de altfel cu <text:s text:c="2"/>mult zg<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rcenie. Locuia n trei ncperi mici <text:span text:style-name="T1">p</text:span>e West Harrison Street, <text:s text:c="2"/>l<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ng Throup i uneori ii gtea singur m<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ncarea. Unicul su prieten <text:s text:c="2"/>era <text:span text:style-name="T1">pre</text:span>pelicarul afectuos i bl<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd <text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>o ce<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span> pe car<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span> o chema Jennie <text:s text:c="2"/>i care dormea n odaia lui. Je<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>nie era docil i iubitoare, l <text:s text:c="2"/>atepta la birou pn termina treaba i se ntorceau seara acas.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Lau<text:span text:style-name="T1">gh</text:span>lin vorbea<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>cu c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>inele su cum ar fi vorbit cu un <text:span text:style-name="T1">om</text:span> (poate <text:s text:c="2"/>chiar cu mai puine rezerve), lu<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd privirile, guduratul i alte semne <text:s text:c="2"/>drept rspunsuri. Dimineaa cnd se scula la patru i jumtate i <text:s text:c="2"/>uneori mai devreme chiar, la patru  dormea puin  i trgea <text:s text:c="2"/>pantalonii (rareori se mai <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>mbia acum, doar la <text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span> frizerie din centru) <text:s text:c="2"/>i ncepea o conversaie cu Jennie.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Hai, Jennie, scoal-te... e timpul s te scoli. Trebuie s facem <text:s text:c="2"/>cafeaua i s lum gustarea de diminea. Te vd eu cum stai aici i te <text:s text:c="2"/>faci c dormi. Scoal ! Ai dormit de-ajuns. Ai dormit c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t mine. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Jennie, din pat, l p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndea afectuos cu un ochi, d<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd din coad, i mica urechea liber n sus i n jos. Laughlin se mbrca, dup ce se <text:s text:c="2"/>spla pe fa i pe m<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ini, i i p<text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span>nea o cravat veche n form de <text:s text:c="2"/>s<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>oar, le<text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span>at larg i comod, i-i peria prul n sus. Jennie se scula <text:s text:c="2"/>i se nvirtea iubitoare n jurul lui de parc spunea : <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>Vezi cum m-am <text:s text:c="2"/>grbit?</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Aa i trebuie, rostea ntotdeauna btrinul, te scoli mereu ultima, <text:s text:c="2"/>niciodat prima, aa-i Je<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>nie? Tata trebuie s tie primul ntotdeauna<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:span text:style-name="T1">I</text:span>arna, cnd roile tramvaiului sc<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>r<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>iau i degetele i urechile <text:s text:c="2"/>ameninau s nghee, btrnul Laughlin, ntr-un palton cenuiu gros, <text:s text:c="2"/>vechi, ponosit i o plrie ptrat, o bga pe Jennie ntr-un geamantan <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1">ne</text:span>gru-verzui i ast<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>el o transporta n ora mpreun <text:span text:style-name="T1"><text:s/>cu c</text:span>teva, din <text:s text:c="2"/>preioasele aciuni n care i pusese <text:s text:c="2"/>mari ndejdi<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Numai aa o putea lua pe Jennie cu el <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n tramvai. C<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd <text:soft-page-break/>nu <text:s text:c="2"/>era prea <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>rig mergeau pe jos cci lui i plcea s umble. De obicei <text:s text:c="2"/>ajungea la birou pe la apte jumtate-opt, dei treaba nu ncepea <text:s text:c="2"/>dec<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span> dup nou, i rm<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nea acolo p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n la, patru jumtate-<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>inci, citind <text:s text:c="2"/>jurnalele, fcnd socoteli cnd nu era ocupat cu clienii. Pe urm, tot <text:s text:c="2"/>cu Jennie, pleca s se plimbe sau se nt<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>lnea cu vreun om de afaceri. <text:s/>Nu-l interesau dec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t locuina sa, gazetele, bursa, biroul lui i <text:s text:c="2"/>strada. Teatrul, crile, tablourile, muzica nu-l atrgeau  iar <text:s text:c="2"/>femeile numai dintr-un singur punct de vedere, i sta destul de <text:s text:c="2"/>limitat. Cerea at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t de puin de la via nct pentru Cowperwood, <text:s text:c="2"/>cruia i plceau oamenii, btr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nul <text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>ra fascinant. T<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nrul bancher se <text:s text:c="2"/>folosea doar de o<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>meni, nu se <text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span>prea s-i studieze cum ar face u<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>artist.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Cowperwood <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i ddu i<text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span>ediat seama c btr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nul <text:span text:style-name="T1">L</text:span>aughlin tia n <text:s text:c="2"/>legtur cu finanele, tranzaciile, posibilitile i oamenii din <text:s text:c="2"/>Chicago tot ce merita s <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>ie tiut. Laughlin, comerciant nnscut i <text:s text:c="2"/>nicidecum un organizator sau un conductor, nu fusese niciodat n <text:s text:c="2"/>stare s ntrebuineze cu adevrat constructiv cunotinele sale. Se <text:s text:c="2"/>purta la fel i la c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tig i la pagub, mulumindu-se, n <text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>az de pierdere, s exclame:  Vai! nu trebuia s fac aa, i pocnea din degete. <text:s text:c="2"/>Cnd c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tiga v<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rtos sau avea perspective de ctig, mesteca<text:span text:style-name="T1"> f</text:span>oi de <text:s text:c="2"/>tutun cu un zmbet angeli<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>, i, brusc, n mijlocul tratativelor, striga<text:span text:style-name="T1">: </text:span><text:s/> Venii, biei, c iar o s plou. Era greu s-l prinzi cu vreo <text:s text:c="2"/>mecherie i nu pierdea sau nu c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tiga dec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t atunci cnd se ddea o <text:s text:c="2"/>lupt deschis pe pia ori combina pe cont propriu c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>te o mic <text:s text:c="2"/>afacere. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Asociaia Cowperwood-Laughlin nu se per<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>ect imediat. Btr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nul <text:s text:c="2"/>voia s se mai gndeasc, dei avea o sl<text:span text:style-name="T1">b</text:span>iciune pentru Cowperwood. <text:s text:c="2"/>De fapt era <text:span text:style-name="T1">menit din capul </text:span>locului s fie omul i victima lui <text:span text:style-name="T1">Cowperwood. S</text:span>e ntilneau zilnic, <text:s text:c="2"/>i discutau unele <text:s text:c="2"/>amnunte i condiii. n cele din urm, m<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nat de <text:s text:c="2"/>instinct, btrnul Peter ceru o participare e<text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span>al.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Oho, dar <text:s text:c="2"/>ce-ai s faci cu at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ta? exclam Cowperwood, prietenos. Asta se <text:s text:c="2"/>petrecea n biroul lui <text:s/>Laughlin, ntre orele patru i cinci <text:s text:c="2"/>dup mas; <text:s/>btr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nul mesteca de zor tutun, cu sentimentul c <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>e afl n faa unei <text:soft-page-break/>probleme frumoase si interesante<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Eu am un <text:s text:c="2"/>fotoliu la bursa din New York i asta valoreaz patruzeci de <text:s text:c="2"/>mii de dolari, iar fotoliul de la <text:s text:c="3"/>bursa din Philadelphia face mai mult ca al dumitale de aici. Ele vor <text:s text:c="2"/>constitui, fr ndoial, activul cel <text:s/>mai important al viitoarei <text:s text:c="2"/>noastre firme. Va fi pe numele dumitale. Dar am s <text:s text:c="2"/>m port totui generos. n <text:span text:style-name="T1">loc</text:span> de o treime, cum s-ar cuveni, am <text:s text:c="2"/>s-i dau patruzeci i nou la sut<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> i vom numi societatea <text:span text:style-name="T2">Peter Laughlin &amp; Comp</text:span>. in la dumneata, i cred <text:s/>c-mi poi fi de mare folos. <text:span text:style-name="T1">S</text:span>nt sigur c dac lucrezi <text:s text:c="2"/>cu mine vei ctiga mai muli bani dec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t ai citigat lucr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd singur. A <text:s text:c="2"/>putea intra n combinaie cu <text:s text:c="2"/>toi filfizonii de pe aici, dar nu vreau. Ai face bine <text:s text:c="2"/>s nu mai zbaveti i s ncepem treaba.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Btr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nul Laughlin era fericit din cale-a<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>ar c tnrul Cowperwood voia <text:s text:c="2"/>s se asocieze cu el. n ultimul timp i dduse seama c toi tinerii <text:s text:c="2"/>aceia nfumurai, aprui n ultima vreme la burs, l considerau un <text:s text:c="2"/>btr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n de mod veche. n faa lui se gsea un om venit din <text:s text:c="2"/>Philadelphia, curajos i puternic, cu douzeci de ani mai t<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nr ca el, <text:s text:c="2"/>la fel de iste  ba parc mai iste; chiar  care i propunea categoric s se asocieze cu el n afaceri. Afar de asta, Cowperwood cu <text:s text:c="2"/>sntatea i agresiva sa tineree era ca o boare de primvar.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Numele firmei nu m intereseaz atit de mult, relu Laughlin. Poi <text:s text:c="2"/>s-o numeti cum vrei. Cu cincizeci i una la sut vei <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>i oricum cel <text:s text:c="2"/>mai important. Totui, snt de acord... nu fac obiecii. Cred c-am s <text:s text:c="2"/>tiu s iau ce mi se cuvine.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Atunci, s-a fcut! rosti Cowperwood. Ne <text:span text:style-name="T1">tr</text:span>ebuie alte birouri, nu <text:s text:c="2"/>crezi? Aici e cam ntunecos<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> F cum <text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>rezi c-i mai bine, domnule Cowperwood mie mi-e tot una. <text:s text:c="2"/>Abia ate<text:span text:style-name="T1">p</text:span>t s vd cu a<text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span> s ar<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>njezi lucrurile.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">ntr-o sptmn treaba <text:span text:style-name="T1">fu</text:span> gata p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n n cele mai mici amnunte, iar <text:s text:c="2"/>dup alte dou, n centrul cartierului comercial din Chicago apru <text:s text:c="2"/>deasupra uii unui apartament elegant, la parterul unei cldiri din <text:s text:c="2"/>Madison Street, col cu <text:soft-page-break/>La Salle, firma <text:span text:style-name="T2">Peter Laughlin &amp; Comp., <text:s/>agentur i comision n cereale</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Ce-o fi cu btr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nul Laughlin ? se ntrebau agenii <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntre ei, trec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd <text:s text:c="2"/>prin faa casei pretenios renovate; cu geamuri splendide de cristal ; <text:s text:c="2"/>remarcau, de asemen<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>a firma de alam, masiv, mpodobit luxos, pus <text:s text:c="2"/>la dreapta uii din colul cldirii. Ce s-o fi nt<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>mplat? Credeam c <text:s text:c="2"/>s-a isprvit cu el, cnd colo... Cine-o mai fi i <text:span text:style-name="T2">Compania</text:span> asta?</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Habar n-am, cred c vreun individ venit <text:s text:c="2"/>din Est. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Ei, ce s-i spun, se lanseaz. Ia te uit, m <text:s text:c="2"/>rog, la geamurile astea de cristal ! </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"><text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i ast<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>el ncepu cariera <text:s text:c="2"/>financiar a lui <text:span text:style-name="T1">Frank </text:span>Algernon Cowperwood, la Chicago.</text:p>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2"><text:span text:style-name="Label">Capitolul V</text:span> <text:line-break/><text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n care este vorba de o nevast i de o familie</text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Dac i nchipuie cineva, mcar o clip, c aceast iniiativ<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>financiar a dovedit din partea lui Cowperwood grab sa<text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>superficialitate gree<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>e n aprecierea d<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rzeniei i perspicacitii <text:s text:c="2"/>acestui om. Cele treisprezece luni petrecute n penitenciarul districtului din Est i-au dat rgazul s mediteze temeini<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span> asupra vieii <text:s text:c="2"/>i asupra felului n care era <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1">or</text:span>nduit i l-au fcut s adopte o dat pent<text:span text:style-name="T1">r</text:span>u <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1">totd</text:span>eauna <text:span text:style-name="T1">o at</text:span>itudine bine chibzuit. E<text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span> putea, <text:span text:style-name="T1">trebuia i era </text:span>hotr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t s conduc singur<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> De<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>acum nu va mai avea dreptul s <text:span text:style-name="T1">p</text:span>reti<text:span text:style-name="T1">nd</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1"> ceva de la el</text:span> dec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t n calitate de <text:s text:c="2"/>solicita<text:span text:style-name="T1">nt</text:span>. Nu <text:span text:style-name="T1">mai</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>vo<text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span>a asociaii periculoase cum se nt<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>mplase cu Stener i <text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>lii, care <text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>l duseser de r<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>p la Philadelphia. Curajul i talentul lui pe <text:s text:c="2"/>tr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>m financiar<text:span text:style-name="T12"> <text:s/></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span> plasau <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n<text:span text:style-name="T12"> </text:span>fruntea tuturor i asta o s-o dovedeasc. Oamenii se vor <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>v<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rti n jurul lui ca planetele n jurul soarelui.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Ceva mai mult, dup dezastrul de la Philadelphia ajunsese s <text:s text:c="2"/>cread c niciodat poate nu va mai face parte din lumea <text:s text:c="2"/>bun, n sensul n care aa-zisa <text:s text:c="3"/>bun<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> societate dintr-un ora nelege aceast expresie; i <text:s text:c="2"/>medit<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd, n clipele de rgaz, i ddea seama c mai mult ca sigur <text:s text:c="2"/>nu-i va gsi viitorii si aliai n rndul celor bogai i <text:s text:c="2"/>bine vzui de societate  simandicoii, care formau o tagm <text:s text:c="2"/>restr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ns  ci printre debutanii plini de vigoare care se <text:s text:c="2"/>ridicaser de jos sau se vor ridica, fr ambiii de parvenire. i erau <text:s text:c="2"/>muli din tia. Dac va avea noroc i n urma unor eforturi uriae va <text:s text:c="2"/>dob<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndi o mare putere n lumea financiar, atunci i va putea impune <text:s text:c="2"/>voina i va putea dicta n buna societate. Cu o fire mai degrab <text:s text:c="2"/>individualist, ba chiar <text:s/>anarhist i fr un grunte de spirit <text:s text:c="2"/>democratic, temperamental vorbind, inea totui mai mult cu masele, <text:s text:c="2"/>pentru care avea o <text:soft-page-break/>mare nelegere. Aa se  poate, ntr-un fel,<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>explica dorina sa de a alege ca asociat pe Peter Laughlin<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span> un om at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t <text:s text:c="2"/>de naiv i ciudat. L-a ales, ca un chirurg cnd i caut un anumit <text:s text:c="2"/>bisturiu pentru operaie, i, cu toat iretenia lui, btr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nul <text:s text:c="2"/>Laughlin era menit s nu fie i aceast asociaie decit un instrument n <text:s text:c="2"/>minile puternice ale lui Cowperwood, un simplu trepdu, gata s <text:s text:c="2"/>primeasc ordine de la aceast minte ager i ascuit<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Deocamdat <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood<text:span text:style-name="T12"> <text:s/></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1">se mulumea</text:span> s lucreze la adpostul firmei <text:span text:style-name="T2">Peter Laughlin &amp; Comp.</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1">,</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>de f<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>pt prefera <text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>hiar astfel; conducnd totul din <text:span text:style-name="T1">umbr</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">i evitnd atenia </text:span>ind<text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span>s<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>ret a oamenilor, v<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span> da ncetul <text:span text:style-name="T1">cu nc</text:span>etul c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>teva <text:s text:c="2"/>lovituri<text:span text:style-name="T1"> prin care spera s-i dobndeasc o situaie solid n viaa financiar de mine a oraului Chicago.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">ntre timp, Harper Steger, avocatul lui Cowperwood, lucra din <text:s/>rsputeri s c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tige ncrederea d<text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span>amnei Cowperwood, care-i bnuia pe <text:s text:c="2"/>avocai n msura n care l bnuia i pe ndrtnicul ei s<text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood considera demersurile lui Steger ca o msur preliminar de <text:s text:c="2"/>mare importan pentru consolidarea situaiei financiare i mondene de <text:s text:c="2"/>la Chicago  at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t a<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>lui ct i a lui Aileen. Doamna Cowperwood, o <text:s text:c="2"/>femeie nalt, cam plinu, cptase n ultimul timp o expresie aspr <text:s text:c="2"/>care ns nu <text:span text:style-name="T1">r</text:span>euea s tearg cu totul urmele unei frumusei trecute acum, care <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>l interesase cndva pe Cowperwood. Zb<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>r<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>ituri <text:s text:c="2"/>pronunate apruser n dreptul ochilor, gurii i nasului. Avea <text:s text:c="2"/>nfiarea, unei femei distante, gata oricnd s critice, <text:s text:c="2"/>indiferent, filistin i <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>usceptibil.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Steger, cu abilitatea lui  avea graia contemplativ a unui cotoi la <text:s text:c="2"/>p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd  era omul ideal care s trateze cu ea. Nu existase de cnd lumea <text:s text:c="2"/>un tip mai oportunist <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i mai viclean, dar plin de tact<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Deviza lui ar <text:s text:c="2"/>fi putut fi: Vorbete cu bl<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nde<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>e i calc tiptil.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Scump doamn Cowperwood, pled el <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntr-o dup mas de primvar, <text:s text:c="2"/>afl<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndu<text:span text:style-name="T1">-</text:span>se n salonaul ei modest din Philadelphia  n<text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span>-i nevoie s-i <text:s text:c="2"/>spun ce om re<text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span>arcabil este soul dumitale, i nici c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t de inutil ar fi <text:s text:c="2"/>s i te <text:soft-page-break/>mpotriveti. Chiar dac recunoatem greelile lui  i s<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nt <text:s text:c="2"/>de acord cu dumneata c are berechet... (doamna Cowperwood prea <text:s text:c="2"/>enervat) totui la ce bun s-i cerem socoteal<text:span text:style-name="T1">?</text:span> tii... i domnul <text:s text:c="2"/>Steger, schi<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd un gest de regret cu m<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>na sa subire i elegant, ce <text:s text:c="2"/>fel de om este domnul Cowperwood i c n-ar sluji la nimic s-l <text:s text:c="2"/>contrazici. El nu-i un om obinuit. Un om obinuit nu trece prin cea <text:s text:c="2"/>trecut el ca apoi z se ridice la situaia de azi. E mai bine s <text:s text:c="2"/>renuni la el, ascult-mi onsimte s divorezi. El dorete i e gata e <text:s text:c="2"/>viitorul dumitale i al copiilor. i, snt<text:span text:style-name="T1"> convins c</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1">v</text:span>a fi generos. Acum e foarte iritat d<text:span text:style-name="T1">e refuzul dumi</text:span>tale, iar dac ai s te <text:s text:c="2"/>ncp<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nezi, <text:span text:style-name="T1">mi-e</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>team c vei ajunge la judecat<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> E<text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span>, drept s-i <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>pun, <text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span> prefera s <text:s text:c="2"/>ajungem la o nelegere amical nainte ca lucrurile s mearg prea <text:s text:c="2"/>departe. tii, desigur, ct am regretat felul n care s-au desf<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>urat <text:s text:c="2"/>evenimentele. <text:span text:style-name="T1">mi</text:span> pare extrem de ru c lucrurile stau at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t de prost<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Domnul Steger ridic ochii, cu o expresie m<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>hnit i dezaprobatoare. <text:s text:c="2"/>Regreta din tot sufletul curentele potrivnice c<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>re conduceau lumea asta <text:s text:c="2"/>zbuciumat<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Doamna Cowperwood, pentru a cincisprezecea sau chiar a douzecea oar <text:s text:c="2"/>asculta, cu rbdare, acelai discurs. Va s zic Frank n-avea de g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd <text:s text:c="2"/>s se <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntoarc la ea, iar Steger i arta tot atta prietenie ca <text:s text:c="2"/>oricare avocat. i apoi, l socotea o relaie agreabil. Cu toat <text:s text:c="2"/>profesia lui machiavelic, avea ncredere n el, dar numai pe <text:s text:c="2"/>jumtate. Steger expunea mai departe, cu tact, punctele importante<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">n cele din urm, la a douzeci i una vizit, n aparen foarte <text:s text:c="2"/>ngrijorat, i aduse la cunotin c soul ei era hotr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t s n-o mai <text:s text:c="2"/>ajute cu bani i s <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nceteze de a mai plti cheltuielile ei i ale <text:s text:c="2"/>copiilor, c n-avea de gn<text:span text:style-name="T1">d </text:span>s-i mai dea nimic pin ce tribunalul nu <text:s text:c="2"/>va fixa suma cuvenit, i c el, Steger, se vedea silit s se retrag. <text:s text:c="2"/>Doamna Cowperwood nelese c era nevoit s cedeze i-i formul preteniile. Dac soul ei va depune n numele ei i al copiilor dou sute <text:s text:c="2"/>de mii de dolari (suma fusese sugerat de Cowperwood) <text:soft-page-break/>i dac mai <text:s text:c="2"/>trziu i va gsi o situaie fiului lor, Frank junior, ea accept divorul. Dar toate astea i displceau profund. Era clar c asta va <text:s text:c="2"/>nsemna un fel de trium<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span> al lui Aileen Butler, ceea ce de alt<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>el a i <text:s text:c="2"/>fost. Dar, la urma, urmelor <text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>ceast femeie deczut fusese complet <text:s text:c="2"/>compromis n Philadelphia. Era puin probabil c Aileen va mai cuteza <text:s text:c="2"/>vreodat s ridice capul, n societate, oriunde s-ar afla. Consimi s <text:s text:c="2"/>fac o cerere redactat de Steger i graie manevrelor acestui domn <text:s text:c="2"/>abil, <text:s text:c="2"/>cererea a fost naintat tribunalului n cea mai <text:s text:c="2"/>desv<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>r<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>it tain. Dup vreo ase sptmini apru <text:s text:c="2"/>un mi<text:span text:style-name="T1">c </text:span>para<text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span>ra<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span> n trei di<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span> iucnalele din Philadelphia, <text:s text:c="2"/>prin <text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>are <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>e aducea la cunotin pronun<text:span text:style-name="T1">area unui</text:span> divor. Citind acest <text:span text:style-name="T1">paragraf doamnei Cowperwood </text:span>nu-i veni s cread c evenimentele st<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rniser at<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span> de puine <text:s text:c="2"/>comentarii. Se temuse de o publicita<text:span text:style-name="T1">te</text:span> mult mai mare. Habar n-avea de <text:s text:c="2"/>campania subtil, de demersurile juridice i de concursul obinut din <text:s text:c="2"/>partea presei de ctre avocatul abil al soului ei<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> C<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t despre <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood, cnd vzu, cu ocazia unei vizite la Chicago, anunul <text:s text:c="2"/>ntr-un ziar, o<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>t uura<text:span text:style-name="T1">t.</text:span> n sfirit, se terminase! Acum se putea <text:s text:c="2"/>cstori c<text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span> Aileen. i-i trimise o telegram enigmatic de felicitare. <text:s text:c="2"/>Cind o citi, Aileen simi un fior de fericire.<text:span text:style-name="T1"> n</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>curnd va deveni soia legitim a lui Frank Algernon Co<text:span text:style-name="T1">w</text:span>perwood, <text:s text:c="2"/>financiarul care debutase n mod at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t de strlucit la Chicago. i pe <text:s text:c="2"/>urm...</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:span text:style-name="T1">O</text:span>! exclam ea cnd primi telegrama la Philadelphia. Ce minunat ! <text:s text:c="2"/>Acum voi fi doamna Cowperwood ! Doamne, doamne !</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Prima doamn Cowperwood, cnd se g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndea la legtura brbatului ei cu <text:s text:c="2"/>Aileen, la fal<text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span>mentul, la nchisoarea, la operaiile extraordinare cu <text:s text:c="2"/>ocazia falimentului Jay Cooke i la actuala lui ascensiune <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n lumea <text:s text:c="2"/>financiar, considera tainele vieii ca pe un lucru de neneles. <text:s text:c="2"/>Trebuia s existe un Dumnezeu  s<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>rie i n <text:span text:style-name="T2">Biblie</text:span>. Soul ei, oric<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t ar <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>i el de imoral, nu putea, fi cu desv<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rire ru  copiii l iubeau, <text:s text:c="2"/>iar el avusese grij, cu prisosin, de viitorul ei i al lor. C<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd l <text:s text:c="2"/>arestaser nu fusese desigur mai vinovat ca muli <text:soft-page-break/>alii care erau <text:s text:c="2"/>liberi. Totui fusese condamnat, lucru de care ei i pruse <text:s text:c="2"/>ntotdeauna ru. Era un om capabil i necrutor. Nu prea tia, ce s <text:s text:c="2"/>cread despre el. Singura persoan ntr-adevr vinovat era Aileen <text:s text:c="2"/>Butler  femeia aceea deczut, vanitoas, proast i fr frica lui <text:s text:c="2"/>Dumnezeu, care i <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>ucise capul lui Frank i cu care probabil se <text:span text:style-name="T1">va cstori. Dumnezeu s o pedepseasc, desigur. Trebuie s-o pedepseasc. i astfel, doamna Cowperwood se duce n fiecare duminic la biseric i se strduia s cread c orice s-ar ntmpla, pn la urm dreptatea va nvinge.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2"><text:span text:style-name="Label">Capitolul VI</text:span><text:line-break/> <text:s text:c="2"/>Noua stp<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n a casei</text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">n ziua n care Cowperwood se cstori cu Aileen  <text:s text:c="3"/>ceremonia avusese loc ntr-un stule numit Dalston, l<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ng Pittsburg, <text:s text:c="2"/>n Pennsylvania de vest, unde <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>e opriser cu acest scop  Frank i <text:s text:c="2"/>declar: </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Iubita, mea, acum ncepem ntr-adevr o via nou. Succesul <text:s text:c="2"/>nostru depinde numai de noi. De aceea te rog s m asculi, deocamdat <text:s text:c="2"/>s stai mai retras. Evident, o s trebuiasc s ne facem c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>teva <text:s text:c="2"/>cunotine n-avem ncotro. Domnul i doamna Addison snt foarte <text:s text:c="2"/>nerbdtori s te cunoasc... i-am am<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nat i aa destul. Dar cred c e <text:s text:c="2"/>bine de<text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span>camdat s nu facem prea mult v<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>lv. Oamenii vor <text:s text:c="2"/>ncepe fr ndoial s ne iscodeasc, mai ales dac o s ne <text:s text:c="2"/>afim. Planul meu este s atept<text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span> o vreme i apoi s ne construim o <text:s text:c="2"/>cas frumoas pe care s nu trebuiasc s-o mai transformm ulterior. <text:s text:c="2"/>La primvar dac treburile merg bine, plecm n Europa; acolo ne vom <text:s text:c="2"/>face o idee despre ce<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>e frumos. Vreau s am o galerie mare de tablouri <text:s text:c="2"/>i n timpul cltoriei vedem noi ce mai putem gsi n materie de <text:s text:c="2"/>pictur, obiecte de art i aa mai departe.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Aileen era emoionat i <text:s text:c="2"/>nerbdtoare. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Vai, Frank, <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i spuse ea, n culmea fericirii, eti <text:s text:c="2"/>un om minunat ! Tu faci tot ce-i pui n g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd, nu-i aa? </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Nu <text:s text:c="2"/>chiar tot, protest el. Dar nu pentru <text:span text:style-name="T1">nu </text:span>vreau eu. tii, <text:s text:c="2"/>exist cazuri n care norocul joac un rol destul de important.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Aileen sttea n faa lui, cum i se ntimpla deseori,<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>cu m<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>inile ei durdulii i ncrcate de inele pe umerii<text:span text:style-name="T1"> lui i </text:span>uitndu-i-se n apa ad<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nc i linitit a ochilor. Un alt om n<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>locul lui, mai puin energic, cu g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nduri nu att d<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span> multiple i de <text:s text:c="2"/>variate, n-ar fi putut avea privirea asta direct. nfrunta <text:s/><text:soft-page-break/>curiozitatea i suspiciunea lumii cu o sinceritate prefcut, dezarmant, la fel ca sinceritatea unui copil. Adevrul e<text:span text:style-name="T1"> c</text:span> Aileen avea o mare <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ncredere n el, i numai n <text:span text:style-name="T1">el </text:span>i de aici curajul <text:s text:c="2"/>de a face numai ce-i place. N<text:span text:style-name="T1">edu</text:span>merit, Aile<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>n nu tia ce s cread.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Oh, tigrul meu, leul meu frumos.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">O <text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>iupi de obraz i zmbi. Biat Aileen, i <text:span text:style-name="T1">zise.</text:span> Ce puin cunotea <text:s text:c="2"/>misterul de neptruns al pe<text:span text:style-name="T1">r</text:span>sonalitii lui, mister chiar i pentru el <text:s text:c="2"/>sau, mai bin<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">zis</text:span>, n special pentru el.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">ndat dup cstorie plecar la Chicago i <text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span>nstalar provizoriu n cel <text:s/>mai frumos apartame<text:span text:style-name="T1">nt</text:span> al hotelului Tremont<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Mai trziu gsir o cas<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>mobilat i relativ mic, de pe strada Douzeci i trei, col cu <text:s text:c="2"/>Michigan Avenue, care putea <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>i nchiriat pentru o bucat de vreme, <text:s text:c="2"/>mpreun cu o trsur cu cai.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Au nchiriat-o deci i numaidec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t au angajat u<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span> majordom, servitori i <text:s text:c="2"/>tot ce era necesar ntr-o cas bine inut<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Din amabilitate i <text:s text:c="2"/>nicidecum pentru c socotea important sau bine venit s nceap o <text:s text:c="2"/>ofensiv monden, Frank i invit pe soii Addison <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i alte c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>teva persoane despre care <text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>ia sigur c <text:s text:c="2"/>n-aveau s-l refuze  Alexander Rambaud, pre<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>edintele Societii <text:span text:style-name="T2">Chicago &amp; Nor</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">t</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">hwestern</text:span>, cu soia, <text:span text:style-name="T1">T</text:span>aylor Lord, un arhitect pe care-l<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>consultase n <text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span>ltim<text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span>l timp i care i se prea o relaie acceptabil. <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1">T</text:span>. Lord ca i familia Addison fceau parte din lumea bun, dei <text:s text:c="2"/>personaliti mai puin proeminente.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Nici o grij, Cowperwood tia exact ce trebuie s fac! Casa pe care o <text:s text:c="2"/>nchiriase era o locuin nc<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nttoare, puin cenuie, nu prea mare: <text:s text:c="2"/>avea nite trepte de granit, cu balustrad, care duceau la ua <text:s text:c="2"/>vestib<text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span>lului, foarte spaioas i boltit. V<text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span>traliile contribuiau la <text:s text:c="2"/>atmosfera interiorului cu o not pronunat artistic<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Din fericire casa <text:s/>era mobilat cu gust, iar pentru masa pe care voia s-o dea<text:span text:style-name="T1">, Cowperwood ceruse concursul unui restaurant excelent i al unui artist decorator. Ct despre Aileen, ea n-avea altceva de fcut dect s se gteasc, s-i atepte musafirii i s fie frumoas.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> <text:s text:c="2"/>Cred c nu-i nevoie s-i <text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span>ai <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>pun, i se adres Cowperwood dimineaa, <text:s text:c="2"/><text:soft-page-break/>nainte de a pleca, c dis<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>ar vreau s fii ncinttoare, iubito. <text:s text:c="2"/>Vreau s, placi <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>oilor Addison i domnului Rambaud.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Pentru Aileen sfatul era inutil. ndat dup ce sosise la Chicago <text:s text:c="2"/>cutase, i p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n la urm a descocoperit, o camerist francez<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Dei <text:s text:c="2"/>i adusese multe rochii de la Philadelphia, mai comandase la cea mai<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>bun i scump cas de mode din Chicago  Theresa <text:s text:c="2"/>Donovan  o seam de lucruri pentru iarn. Doar cu o zi nain<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>ea <text:s text:c="2"/>dineului primise o rochie de mtase, galben aurie, acoperit cu o <text:s text:c="2"/>dantel verde groas, care se armonizau ct se poate de bine cu prul <text:s text:c="2"/>ei de aur rou i cu braele i umerii albi. n seara dine<text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span>lui, n <text:s text:c="2"/>budoarul lui Aileen, era o adevrat revrsare de mts<text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span>ri, satinuri, <text:s text:c="2"/>dantele, lenjerie, podoabe pentru pr, parfumuri i bijuterii  ntr-un <text:s text:c="2"/>cuvn<text:span text:style-name="T1">t,</text:span> tot ce putea contribui la desvirirea <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>rumuseii feminine. <text:s text:c="2"/>Odat angajat n combinarea unei noi toalete, Aileen nu mai avea <text:s text:c="2"/>linite, era fr ast<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>mpr, iar camerista ei, Fadette, trebuia s umble <text:s text:c="2"/>ca o sf<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rleaz. Ieit din baie, ca o vener de ivoriu, trecu de la <text:s text:c="2"/>lenjeria de mtase, ciora<text:span text:style-name="T1">pi</text:span> i panto<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>i, la aranjatul prului. Fade<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>te <text:s text:c="2"/>avea ide<text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span> pentru prul lui Aileen. N-ar vrea doamna <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>cerce o <text:s text:c="2"/>torsad n jurul capului, la mod acum? i doamna era de acord. Astfel <text:s text:c="2"/>ncercau <text:span text:style-name="T1">cnd</text:span> o pieptntur, cnd alta, cu pletele ei bogate i <text:span text:style-name="T1">lu</text:span>cioase. Dar parc tot nu mergea. Apoi au m<text:span text:style-name="T1">pl</text:span>eti<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span> prul, dar efectul <text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span>e <text:s text:c="2"/>displcu ; n cele din urm se oprir la o dubl me mple<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>it, care <text:s text:c="2"/>cdea pe frunte, fixat cu dou panglici  de un verde-nchis, formnd <text:s text:c="2"/>un X deasupra frunii  prinse cu o diadem de briliante. i venea <text:s text:c="2"/>minunat ! n dezabieul ei roz de mtase i dantel subire se ridic n <text:s text:c="2"/>picioare i se privi n oglinda lung din perete.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Da! exclam Aileen n cele din urm, ls<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndu-i capul cnd ntr-o <text:s text:c="2"/>parte, cnd ntr-alta.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Apoi lu rochia de<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>la Donovan, fonind, vaporoas<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> O puse pe ea, nc <text:s text:c="2"/>nedecis, i se studie cu ochi <text:s text:c="2"/>critici, n timp ce Fadette i-o aranja la spate, umeri i-i potrivea</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:soft-page-break/>trena ca s cad cit mai bine<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Vai, doamn ! strig camerista. Oh, <text:span text:style-name="T2">charman</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">t!</text:span> Rochia se potrivete <text:s text:c="2"/>perfect cu prul. C<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t de bogat i <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>rumos cade aici  art cu degetul <text:s text:c="2"/>la old<text:span text:style-name="T1">uri</text:span> u<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>de dantela forma un gen de basc ajustat. Oh<text:span text:style-name="T1">,</text:span> dar este <text:s text:c="2"/>prea, prea frumos.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Aileen era radioas, dar nu z<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>mbea. i fcea t<text:span text:style-name="T1">ot</text:span> felul de griji. Nu <text:s text:c="2"/>at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t de rochia ei, care evident avea s fie fr cusur, dar trebuia <text:s text:c="2"/>s-i plac nu numai domnului Addison  un om bogat, din lumea bun  ci <text:s text:c="2"/>i domnului Rambaud, personaj foarte influent, du<text:span text:style-name="T1">p</text:span> spusele lui Frank. <text:s text:c="2"/>Ceea ce dorea era s apar n cea mai bun lumin. Pe oamenii tia <text:s text:c="2"/>trebuia s-i seduc nu numai prin fizic, dar i prin inteli- gena i <text:s text:c="2"/>graia ei de femeie de lume, i asta nu era, chiar at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t de simplu. Cu <text:s text:c="2"/>toi banii i luxul pe care-l afiase la Philadelphia, nu fcuse <text:s text:c="2"/>niciodat parte din lumea bun, n sensul adevrat al cuvntului, nu <text:s text:c="2"/>dduse nicioda recepii de oarecare amploare... Frank era omul cel <text:s text:c="2"/>mai nsemnat; din <text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>i cunoscuse p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n atunci. Domnul Rambaud avea <text:span text:style-name="T1">cu s</text:span>iguran o nevast sever i de mod veche. Ce o s <text:span text:style-name="T1">v</text:span>or<text:span text:style-name="T1">b</text:span>easc<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> oare cu <text:s text:c="2"/>ea? Dar cu doamna Addison? Trebuia s tie c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>te-n lun i-n stele! Ca <text:s text:c="2"/>s-i potoleasc nelinitea i s-i mai dea puin curaj, n timp ce se <text:s text:c="2"/>mbrca, Aileen <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>e trezi vorbind cu glas tare; dar continu s se <text:s text:c="2"/>gteasc, aducnd ultimele retuuri frumuseii ei. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">C<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd, n <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>f<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rit, cobor<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> s vad cum artau salonul i<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>sufrageria  <text:s text:c="2"/>Fadette se apucase s str<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ng maldrul de rochii care nu trecuser <text:s text:c="2"/>examenul  Aileen era ca o viziune de basm, o fermectoare apariie n <text:s text:c="2"/>nuane aurii i verzi, cu un pr bogat, cu brae <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>cul<text:span text:style-name="T1">pt</text:span>urale, ca de <text:s text:c="2"/>filde, cu o splendid linie a g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tului, <text:s text:c="2"/>piept i rotunjimi armonioase. Se simea frum<text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span>as, <text:span text:style-name="T1">er</text:span>a puin enervat. <text:s text:c="2"/>Frank avea un ochi sever. <text:span text:style-name="T1">Intr n su</text:span>frageria pe care arta restaur<text:span text:style-name="T1">at</text:span>orului o <text:span text:style-name="T1">transfor</text:span>mase <text:s text:c="2"/>n<text:span text:style-name="T1">tr-</text:span>un fel de caset, de bijuterii ;<text:span text:style-name="T1"> florile, argintr</text:span>ia, aurul, cristalu<text:span text:style-name="T1">r</text:span>ile colorate <text:span text:style-name="T1">i albul</text:span> imaculat al fete<text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span> de mas ddeau o mare strlucire <text:span text:style-name="T1">nc</text:span>perii, ca opal<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>scpt<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd lumini discrete. <text:span text:style-name="T1">T</text:span>recu apo<text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">n salon </text:span><text:soft-page-break/>unde se gsea un pian<text:span text:style-name="T1"> scldat n roz i aur; pe el </text:span>aezase partiturile c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntecelor i pieselor instrumentale pe care le tia cel mai bi<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>e. <text:span text:style-name="T1">D</text:span>e fapt, <text:s text:c="2"/>Aileen nu era o pianist strlucit.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Pentru prima oar n via <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ncetase de a se mai simi o <text:s text:c="2"/>fetican  se simea o femeie n toat firea, cu rspunderi <text:s text:c="2"/>serioase, chemat s joace un rol, care, la drept vorbind, nu i se <text:s text:c="2"/>potrivea. Preocuprile ei fuseser totdeauna ndreptate ctre <text:s text:c="2"/>aspectul <text:s/>artistic, monden i spectaculos al vieii, asupra zi <text:s/>cruia, din pcate, nu avea o concepie prea clar i, de aceea, <text:s text:c="2"/>nu izbutea s se concentreze pentru a <text:s/>nfptui ceva definit, <text:s text:c="2"/>concret. C<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd i plcea un anumit lucru atunci se nflcra, <text:s text:c="2"/>curiozitatea ei depea orice msur.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Tocmai atunci se auzi clinchetul cheii lu<text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span> Frank n u. Era aproape <text:s text:c="2"/>ase. Intr zmbitor, stp<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n pe sine, crend o atmosfer de plcut <text:s text:c="2"/>siguran.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Ei bine! rosti Frank, examinind-o n lumina difuz a salonului, cu <text:s text:c="2"/>aplicele dispuse n mod <text:span text:style-name="T1">j</text:span>udicios. Ce viziune fermectoare! Aproape c <text:s text:c="2"/>nu ndrznesc s te ating. Ai mult pudr pe brate !?</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">O strnse la piept, iar ea, sigur acum de succes, <text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nl capul ca i cum i s-ar fi luat o piatr de pe inim. Nu mai <text:s text:c="2"/>ncpea nici o ndoial, Frank o gsea nc<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nttoare.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Mi-e team c te-ai fcut numai pudr. Deh... oricum, tot trebuie <text:s text:c="2"/>s te schimbi.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">i-i cuprinse g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tul cu braele ei pline i cat<text:span text:style-name="T1">ife</text:span>late, iar el se simea n<text:span text:style-name="T1">em</text:span>ulumit. Iat femeia ideal.<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>O <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>rumusee... G<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tul ei era pus n valoare de un colier de turcoaze i <text:s/>degetele prea ncrcate cu inele erau totui frumoase. Avea un parfum <text:s text:c="2"/>discret de <text:s text:c="2"/>levnic sau de zambil. Era fermecat de prul ei i mai ales de <text:s text:c="2"/>bogia materialului galben al rochiei, care lucea ca aurii prin <text:s text:c="2"/>dantela, verde i deas.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Minunat, fetio, n ast sear te-ai depit. N-am vzut nc rochia <text:s text:c="2"/>asta. <text:soft-page-break/>Unde ai gsit-o?</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Aici, la Chicago.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Frank i ridic mna fierbinte, privind cu <text:span text:style-name="T1">atenie </text:span>trena rochiei <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i o puse s <text:s text:c="2"/>se nv<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rteasc<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> N-ai nevoie de sfaturi. Ai putea desclide<text:span text:style-name="T1"> o</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>coal<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> mi st bine? ntreb<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span><text:s/>Aileen, coch<text:span text:style-name="T1">et, dei</text:span> nc nesigur ; i <text:s text:c="2"/>asta numai din cauza lui<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Eti minunat. Mai frumos nici c se poate<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Splendid. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"><text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i venise inima la lo<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> A vrea ca i prietenii ti s g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndeasc l<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>e<text:span text:style-name="T1">l.</text:span> i acum grbete-te, <text:s text:c="2"/>du-te i<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>te mbrac.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Frank se duse sus, iar ea l urm dup ce se mai uit o dat prin <text:s text:c="2"/>sufragerie. Totul era pus la punct, Frank se pricepea ca un adevrat <text:s text:c="2"/>maestru.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">La ora apte se auzi tropotul cailor i imediat Louis, majordomul, deschise ua, Aileen cob<text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span>r<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> emoionat, cu inima la gur, ncercnd s <text:s text:c="2"/>se g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndeasc, la, lucruri agreabile i nc nesigur dac<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> va plcea <text:s text:c="2"/>oaspeilor ei. Cowperwood se a<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>la l<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ng <text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>a ntr-o stare de spirit i o <text:s text:c="2"/>atitudine complet diferit<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> de a ei. Viitorul lui era sigur, iar <text:s text:c="2"/>viitorul lui Aileen depindea numai de el. Ascensiunea pe <text:span text:style-name="T1">sc</text:span>ar<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span>erarhiei sociale, care pentru ea era o problem atit de important, pentru <text:s text:c="2"/>el nu avea aceeai semnificaie.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Dineul se desfur cu succesul scontat, at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t in privina organizrii <text:s text:c="2"/>ct i ca amuzament. Cowperwood, o<text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span> cu gusturi i preocupri variate, <text:s text:c="2"/>discut problema cilor ferate cu mult precizie i priceper<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span> cu domnul <text:s text:c="2"/>Rambaud; cu domnul Lord discut arhitectur, cum ar vorbi un student de <text:s text:c="2"/>mare talent, cu profesorul su ; i eu femei ca doamna Addison sau <text:s text:c="2"/>doamna Rambaud, angaja orice conversa<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ie menit s le intereseze<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>Ail<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>en, din pcate, nu se prea simea la largul ei. Dispoziia, i sta<text:span text:style-name="T1">rea ei de </text:span><text:s/>spirit nu oglindeau o concepie de via <text:span text:style-name="T1">dac nu </text:span>joas, mcar bine definit.<text:span text:style-name="T1"> E</text:span>rau <text:soft-page-break/>multe <text:span text:style-name="T1">lucruri pe c</text:span>are nu le cunoatea Aile<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>n, av<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd doar o i<text:span text:style-name="T1">dee vag i superficial </text:span>despre ele  un ecou nde<text:span text:style-name="T1">prtat i nedefinit. Lecturile ei se limitau la civa autori <text:s/></text:span>care, pen<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>ru oameni cultivai, nu prezentau nici un interes. <text:s text:c="2"/>C<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t despre art, n general, cunotinele ei se rezumau la un ir de <text:s text:c="2"/>nume fr semnificaie, <text:s/>culese din discuiile cu Frank. Adevrul i <text:s text:c="2"/>singurul <text:s text:c="3"/>lucru pe care<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>putea conta era vibranta i st<text:span text:style-name="T1">r</text:span>lucitoarea ei <text:s text:c="2"/>frumusee. Rambaud, un om indi<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>ere<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>t, <text:s/>un om de afaceri, cu idei <text:s text:c="2"/>conservatoare, i ddu <text:span text:style-name="T1">seama </text:span>de locul pe care o femeie ca Ail<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>en <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>l ocupa n viaa <text:s text:c="2"/>lui Cowperwood. Dintr-un anumit punct de vedere era femeia pe care <text:s text:c="2"/>ar i preuit-o i el. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">La oamenii tari, preocuprile sexuale nu <text:s text:c="2"/>dinuie p<text:span text:style-name="T1">n la</text:span> sf<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ritul vieii, fiind <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>inute uneori n <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>r<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>u <text:s text:c="2"/>de o stoic resemnare. Oamenii acetia, dup cum chiar <text:s text:c="3"/>ei o tiu, pot avea mereu experiene de<text:span text:style-name="T1"> f</text:span>elul acesta, dar la ce <text:s text:c="2"/>bun? Pentru muli acest lucru devine <text:s/>suprtor. Totui n seara <text:s text:c="2"/>aceea, prezen strlucitoare a lui Aileen trezi la domnul Rambaud <text:s text:c="2"/>ambiii la care renunase de mult. O privi aproape cu tristee. Fusese<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>i el t<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nr. Dar vai, nu strnise niciodat pasiunea unei asttel de <text:s text:c="2"/>femei. Acum, pe cnd o privea, ar <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>i vrut mcar o dat s fi avut parte <text:s text:c="2"/>de un asemenea noroc. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Strlucirea cald i bogia colorat a <text:s text:c="2"/>prezenei lui Aileen erau n contrast cu doamna Rambaud n rochia ei <text:s text:c="2"/>simpl, de mtase gri, al crei guler i aju<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>gea aproape p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n la <text:s text:c="2"/>urechi. Contrastul era suprtor, aproape ca un repro  dar politeea<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>i spiritul doamnei Rambaud reuisr s restabileasc un echilibru <text:s text:c="2"/>plcut. Fcea parte dintr-o familie de intelectuali din New England <text:s text:c="2"/> coala filozofic Emerson-Theoreau-Channing. Phillips  i era <text:s text:c="2"/>o femeie foarte nelegtoare. n fond i plcea: Aileen, i plcea i <text:s text:c="2"/>toat splendoarea ei oriental. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Ce minunat csu avei, i spuse cu <text:s/>un <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>ur<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>s<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Am remarcat-o de mult. Locuim destul de aproa<text:span text:style-name="T1">pe </text:span><text:s/>de <text:s text:c="2"/>dumneavoastr ca s ne putem considera vecini.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:soft-page-break/>Privirea lui Aileen exprima mulumire; dei nu nelegea prea bine <text:s text:c="2"/>genul de femeie care era doamna, Rambaud, totui at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t putea <text:s text:c="2"/>s-i dea, seama i plcea  i se prea c seamn cu mama ei, dac <text:s text:c="2"/>aceasta din urm ar <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>i avu<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span> o educaie i o <text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>ul<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>ur<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> aleas. n timp ce <text:s text:c="2"/>toat lumea intra n salon Taylor fu anunat. Cowperwood i strnse <text:s text:c="2"/>m<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>na i conduse ctre ceilali.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Doamn Cowperwood, ncepu Lord pli<text:span text:style-name="T1">n d</text:span>e a<text:span text:style-name="T1">d</text:span>miraie  era un om nalt, <text:s text:c="2"/>cu trsturi aspre i <text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span> fire meditativ  dai-mi voie s fiu unul din <text:s text:c="2"/>numeroii ceteni ai oraului Chicago care <text:span text:style-name="T1">v</text:span> spune <text:span text:style-name="T1">b</text:span>ine ai <text:s text:c="2"/>venit. Dup Philadelphia, viaa aici o s<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> vi se par mai puin <text:s text:c="2"/>elegant la <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nceput, dar p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n la urm are s v plac aa cum ne place <text:s text:c="2"/>i nou. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> <text:span text:style-name="T1">S</text:span>nt sigur c o s-mi plac, spuse Ail<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>en<text:span text:style-name="T1">,</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>zmbind. Acum civa ani am locuit la Philadelphia, dar <text:s text:c="2"/>num<text:span text:style-name="T1">ai</text:span> scurt vreme. De acolo am venit aici, adug Lot.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">I<text:span text:style-name="T1">nf</text:span>ormaia nu trecu neobservat de Ailc<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>n ; dar nu-i acord pea mare <text:s text:c="2"/>importan.<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>Va trebui s fie pregtit pentru asfel de aluzii; va avea <text:s text:c="2"/>de trecut prin momente i mai grele.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> mi place Chicago foar<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>e mult, zise ea, repede. Nu-i gsese nici un <text:s text:c="2"/>cusur, are mult mai mult via <text:s text:c="2"/>dec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t Philadelphia.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> <text:span text:style-name="T1">S</text:span>nt fericit s v aud vorbind aa. Mie <text:s text:c="2"/>personal mi place extrem de mult. Poate i pentru c aici <text:s text:c="2"/>gsesc at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tea lucruri interesante de fcut<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Admira splendoarea <text:s text:c="2"/>prului i braelor ei. La urma, urmei, ce nevoie are o femeie frumoas <text:s text:c="2"/>s fie i intelectual, i zicea el, contient c Aileen nu era de un <text:s text:c="2"/>suprem rafinament<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">O nou apariie a majordomului vesti sosirea <text:s text:c="2"/>domnului i a doamnei Addison. Pe Addison nu-<text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span> deranja de loc s<text:span text:style-name="T1">-l</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>frecventeze pe Cowperwood, dimpotriv, ideea <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>l atrgea; at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t <text:s/>el<text:span text:style-name="T1"> c</text:span>t i <text:s text:c="2"/>soia sa <text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>veau o situaie destul de solid n societate. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Ce mai <text:s text:c="2"/>faci, Cowperwood? ntreb el radi<text:span text:style-name="T1">os</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>u o m<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n pe umrul acestuia <text:soft-page-break/> ai <text:s text:c="2"/>avut o id<text:span text:style-name="T1">ee strlu</text:span>cit s ne chemi ast sear. Doamn Cowpe<text:span text:style-name="T1">rwood, de un an i </text:span>tot sp<text:span text:style-name="T1">u</text:span>n soului dumitale s te<text:span text:style-name="T1"> aduc la </text:span><text:s text:c="3"/>Chicago. Nu i-a spus? (Addison nu-i destinuie nevestei sale povestea <text:s text:c="2"/>lui Cowperwood i a lui Aileen).</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Ba da, mi-a spus, replic Aileen voioas con<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>ient de efectul <text:s text:c="2"/>farmecului ei asupra lui Addi<text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>on. i eu doream s vin aici. E vina lu<text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span> <text:s/>c n-am veni<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span> mai de mult.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Addison, care o examina discret<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>pe Aileen, si zise c nevasta lui <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood era fr ndoial o <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>emeie impresionant de frumo<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>s. Va s <text:s text:c="2"/>zic din cauza ei divorase Cowperwood. Nu era de mirare. Ce fiin <text:s text:c="2"/>minunat !! O compar cu doamna Addison care iei dezavantajat. Soia <text:s text:c="2"/>lui nu avusese nicioda<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span> alura i frumuseea izbitoare a lui Aileen, <text:s text:c="2"/>dei poate c era mai deteapt, Dumnezeule <text:span text:style-name="T1">!</text:span> De ce nu poate i el s <text:s text:c="2"/>gseasc o femeie ca asta? Viaa ar cpta imediat o nou strlucire.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">i totui <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n viaa lui existau femei  frecventri prudente, tainice, <text:s text:c="2"/>dar reale. Mai bine zis existaser.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> <text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>mi pare bine s v cunosc, spunea doamna Addison, o cucoan gras i <text:s text:c="2"/>plin de bijuterii. Am impresia c, soii notri au devenit cei mai <text:s text:c="2"/>buni prieteni. Ar trebui s ne vedem mai des.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Doamna Addison continu s vorbeasc intr-un stil monden i banal, iar <text:s text:c="2"/>Aileen avea impresi<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span> c lucrurile merg strun. Majordomul aduse o ta<text:span text:style-name="T1">v</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>mare cu aperitive i buturi i o puse, atent, pe o mas mai izolat. <text:s text:c="2"/>Apoi se servi masa, iar conversaia i urm cursul. Se vorbi despre <text:s text:c="2"/>dezvoltarea or<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>ului, despre biserica pe care o construia Lord c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>teva <text:s text:c="2"/>strzi mai departe ; Rambaud povesti despre niste escrocherii amuzante <text:s text:c="2"/>n le<text:span text:style-name="T1">gt</text:span>ur cu v<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nzarea unor <text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>erenuri. Atmosfera era, f<text:span text:style-name="T1">oar</text:span>te vesel. i <text:s text:c="2"/>tot timpul Aileen se strduia s<text:span text:style-name="T1"> par</text:span> c particip<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> cu interes la<text:span text:style-name="T1"> conversaia </text:span>celor dou<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">do</text:span>amne. Doamna <text:s text:c="2"/>Ad<text:span text:style-name="T1">d</text:span>ison i <text:span text:style-name="T1">plcea m</text:span>ai mult pentru c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> n prezena ei <text:span text:style-name="T1">conversaia era m</text:span>ai uoar. Aileen tia <text:s text:c="2"/>c doamna <text:span text:style-name="T1">Rambaud era o f</text:span>emeie mai <text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>eleg<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>o<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>re i <text:soft-page-break/>mai int<text:span text:style-name="T1">eligent, dar o intimida puin; pn la urm terbuia mereu s recurg la domnul Lord, care-i venea</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>cava<text:span text:style-name="T1">le</text:span>rete n ajutor, vorbind despre orice-i<text:span text:style-name="T1"> trecea </text:span><text:s text:c="3"/>prin minte. Toi brbaii, n afar<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> de <text:span text:style-name="T1">Cowperwood </text:span>erau subjugai de <text:s text:c="2"/>frumuseea nemaipomeni<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span> a lui Aileen, de albeaa braelor ei, de linia <text:s text:c="2"/>seduc<text:span text:style-name="T1">toare </text:span>a g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tului, de rotunjimea umerilor, de prul ei <text:span text:style-name="T1">bogat.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2"><text:span text:style-name="Label">Capitolul VII </text:span><text:line-break/>Chicago i gazul aerian</text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Dinamismul lui Cowperwood<text:span text:style-name="T13"> </text:span>l <text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>ntinerise pe btr<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>nul Peter Laughlin, care acum c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tiga bani frumoi pentru firm. Aflase de la burs <text:s text:c="2"/>cancanuri care mai de care mai nstrunice, i anticipa cu atta siguran<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> planurile anumitor grupuri i indivizi, nc<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t asta, i permitea <text:s text:c="2"/>lui Cowperwood s trag concluzii ndrznee i fructuoase.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Pe cuv<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntul meu, Frank, cred c tiu exact ce au de g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd s fac <text:s text:c="2"/>oamenii tia, obi<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nuia s spun dimineaa, dup o noapte petrecut n <text:s text:c="2"/>locuina lui sin<text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span>uratic din strada Harrison, noapte petrecut <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n mare <text:s text:c="2"/>parte st<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd n pat i medi<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>nd. Gaca de l<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span> ocolul de vite (i cnd <text:s text:c="2"/>spunea gac se g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndea la cei care <text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>rgeau sforile acest<text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span>r afaceri, ca <text:s text:c="2"/>de pild Arneel Hand, S<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>hryhart i alii) a nceput iar s <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>e ocupe de porumb. Acum e <text:s text:c="2"/>momentul zu, s ne bgm i noi <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n afacerea asta. Ce zici? </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">C<text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span>wperwood, la curent cu multe subtilit<text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span> ale Vestului i tot mai <text:s text:c="2"/>informat pe zi ce trecea, se obinuise s ia hotr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ri pe loc. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Ai dreptate. Risc o sut de mii de bnui. Cred c <text:span text:style-name="T2">New York Central</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>teva zile o s scad cu un punct sau dou. Am putea cumpra, fr <text:s text:c="2"/>acoperire, la o di<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>eren<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> de un punct.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Laughlin n-a neles niciodat cum se <text:span text:style-name="T1">fcea c Franck</text:span> Cowperwood prea totdeauna la<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>cure<text:span text:style-name="T1">nt gata s</text:span> treac la aciune n treburile loc<text:span text:style-name="T1">ale, cu aceeai</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">r</text:span>apiditate ca i <text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>l. Competena <text:s text:c="2"/>lui <text:span text:style-name="T1">n privina</text:span> aciunilor din Est i n afac<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>rile care<text:span text:style-name="T1"> se tratau</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>la bursa din Est era explicabil, dar n treburile din <text:span text:style-name="T1">Chicago?</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> <text:span text:style-name="T1">Ce te face </text:span>s crezi<text:span text:style-name="T1"> asta? </text:span>l ntrebase odat, nedumerit, pe Cowperwood. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"><text:soft-page-break/> <text:span text:style-name="T1"><text:s/>P</text:span>i, Peter, <text:s text:c="2"/>rspunse Cowperwood cu mult calm, <text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>iu asta de la Anton Videra (unul din directorii bncii <text:span text:style-name="T2">Gru i Porumb</text:span>) care a fost ieri pe aici, cnd dumneata te afla<text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span> la burs. <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood descria acum situaia aa cum o prezentase Videra. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Laughlin</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">l cunotea pe Videra, un polonez puterni<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span> i bogat, care se ridicase <text:s text:c="2"/>n ultimii ani. Era curios felul att<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>de firesc n care Cowperwood se <text:s text:c="2"/>mprietenise cu aceti oameni bogai i ct de<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>repede le-a c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tigat <text:s text:c="2"/>ncrederea. Videra niciodat nu-i artase lui atta ncredere.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> <text:span text:style-name="T1">Hm,</text:span> bine, dac aa spune el, mai mult ca sigur <text:s text:c="2"/>c-i a<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>a!</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">i, n consecin, Laughlin a cumprat porumbul i astfel <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T2">Peter Laughlin &amp; Comp</text:span> a ctigat bani buni. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Dar aceast agentur de <text:s text:c="2"/>cereale, dei le asigura fiecruia un profit anual de aproximativ <text:s text:c="2"/>douzeci de mii de dolari, pentru Cowperwood nu reprezenta altceva <text:s text:c="2"/>dec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t o surs de informaii preioase. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Cowperwood dorea s intre ntr-o <text:s text:c="2"/>combinaie care s-i aduc profituri mari pentru care s nu a<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tepte <text:s text:c="2"/>prea mult i totodat s-l fereasc de a mai ajunge vreodat n <text:s text:c="2"/>situaia disperat n care l-a gsit focul de la Chicago  fr o <text:s text:c="2"/>acoperire solid, dup cum spunea el. A cointeresat n afacerile sale <text:s text:c="2"/>un grup mic de financiari din Chicago, care aveau <text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span>chii pe el  Judah <text:s text:c="2"/>Addison, Alexander Rambaud, Milard Bailey, Anton Videra  oameni care, <text:s text:c="2"/>fr s dein suprema<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ia dispuneau de mari capitaluri. <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tia c putea <text:s text:c="2"/>apela la ei, cu condiia s le fac o propunere ntr-adevr serioas. <text:s text:c="2"/>l atrgea n primul r<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd afacerea cu gazul aerian din C<text:span text:style-name="T1">hicago</text:span> i asta <text:s text:c="2"/>pentru c n acest domeniu nc neexpl<text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span>atat avea anse s prtrund <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>r s atrag prea mult atenia: o dat privilegiile acordate  <text:s text:c="2"/>cititorul va nelege cum  putea s apar ca Hamilcar Barca n inima <text:s text:c="2"/>Spaniei <text:s text:c="2"/>sau ca Hannibal la porile Romei, cerind c<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>pitul<text:span text:style-name="T1">area</text:span> i mprirea przii <text:s text:c="2"/>de rzboi. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"><text:soft-page-break/>Existau pe atunci tei societi de <text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span>az <text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span> cele trei <text:s text:c="2"/>sectoare administrative ale oraului <text:s/>trei cartiere sau districte, <text:s text:c="2"/>dup cum li se spun: de sud, de vest i de nord  iar din <text:span text:style-name="T1">toate, compania</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T2">Gas, Light and Coke</text:span>, fondat n 1848, n districtul sudic, era <text:s text:c="2"/>cea mai nfloritoare i mai <text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span>mp<text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span>rtant, Compania <text:span text:style-name="T2">Peoples Gas, </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">L</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">igh</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">t</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2"> and Coke</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">d</text:span>in vest era cu civa ani mai t<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nr ca cea din sud <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i <text:s text:c="2"/>apruse din pricina nesbuinei celor de la conducerea companiei din <text:s text:c="2"/>sud, care <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nchipuiser c nici dist<text:span text:style-name="T1">r</text:span>ictul vestic i nici cel <text:s text:c="2"/>nordic nu se vor dezv<text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span>lta prea repede <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n urmtorii ani<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span> consiliul <text:s text:c="2"/>municip<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span>l, <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i spuneau <text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span>i, le va ngdui oricnd s-i extind conductele i n celelalte cartiere ale oraului. A <text:span text:style-name="T1">treia</text:span> societate  <text:span text:style-name="T2">North Chicago Gas Illum</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">i</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">n</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">at</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">ing</text:span>  s-a nfiinat aproape simultan cu cea <text:s text:c="2"/>din vest i <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n acelai fel ca celelalte  compania din nord recunotea c inteniile ei fuseser identice cu cele ale companiei din <text:s text:c="2"/>vest, adic o delimitare a activitii ei n sectoarele de care ineau <text:s text:c="2"/>directorii s. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Primul pas fcut de Cowperwood a <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>ost s rscumpere i <text:s text:c="2"/>s comaseze cele trei companii vechi din ora i de aceea lu <text:s text:c="2"/>informaii despre acionarii lor  despre situaia lor s<text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span>cial i <text:s text:c="2"/>financiar. Avea de g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd s<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> ofere trei sau patru dolari n plus pentru <text:s text:c="2"/>fiecare dolar din valoarea de pe pia a aciunilor i astfel s <text:s text:c="2"/>rscumpere cele trei companii i s le fuzioneze. Dup care, emi<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd o <text:s text:c="2"/>cantitate suficient de aciuni ca s-i acopere toate obligaiile, s <text:s/>realizeze un mare ctig i n acelai timp s rm<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n n fruntea conducerii. Se adres nt<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i lui Judah Addison, omul cel mai dispus <text:s text:c="2"/>s-l ajute la lansarea <text:s text:c="2"/>unui astfel de proiect. Addison nu-l interes<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> at<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span> ca asociat, ct mai <text:s text:c="2"/>ales ca unul care s-i furnizeze capitalul necesar<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> <text:span text:style-name="T1">E</text:span>i bine, am s-i spun exact ce cre<text:span text:style-name="T1">d despre</text:span> treaba asta, i mrturisi <text:span text:style-name="T1">n </text:span>cele <text:s text:c="2"/>din <text:span text:style-name="T1">Addison. </text:span>Ideea dumitale mi se pare grozav. M<text:span text:style-name="T1"> ntreb cum</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>nu s-a g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndit nimeni la as<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>a p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n acum <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i ai face bin<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span> nu <text:span text:style-name="T1">p</text:span>rea <text:s text:c="2"/>vorbe<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ti<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span><text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">ri</text:span>ti s i-o ia careva <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nainte<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">E </text:span>plin oraul de oameni <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ntreprinz<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>tori. Dar eu te simpatizez i snt alturi de dumneata. <text:span text:style-name="T1">D</text:span>ar <text:s text:c="2"/>nc ceva ; <text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span>-a vrea s <text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span> bag <text:soft-page-break/>n treaba asta personal  sau n <text:s text:c="2"/>orice caz nu pe fa  <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i pro<text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span>it ns <text:span text:style-name="T1">s-i </text:span>procur<text:span text:style-name="T1">r</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span> parte din banii <text:s text:c="2"/>de care ai nevoie. Mi sa pare bu<text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span> ideea unei societi pe aciuni, <text:s text:c="2"/>unic, adic a unui trust condus de dumneata <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n calitate de membru n <text:s text:c="2"/>consiliul de administraie; e o idee cu care snt perfect de acord, <text:s text:c="2"/>convins c ai s faci fa foarte bine la aceast misiune. n tot cazul eu n-am s apar altfel dec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t ca omul care finaneaz. Numai c o s <text:s text:c="2"/>trebuiasc s mai gset<text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span> alte dou-trei persoane care mpreun cu mine s investeasc <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>umele necesare. Te-ai g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndit la cineva? </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Da, sigur, rspunse Cowperwood, numai c am vrut s vin nt<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i la <text:s/>dumneata. Apoi menion pe Rambaud, Videra, Bailey i alii.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Foarte bine, firete, dac au s consimt. Dar chiar i aa, nu-s <text:s text:c="2"/>sigur c ai s izbuteti s-i convingi pe vechii acionari s <text:s text:c="2"/>lichideze tot. Ei n-au investit banii la ntmplare; considerau aceast societate de gaz aerian ca pe un bun al lor. Ei au nfiinat-o i in <text:s text:c="2"/>la ea. Au construit rezervoarele i au instalat conductele. Nu cred c <text:s text:c="2"/>o s fie uor.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Cowperwood constat, dup cum prevzuse Addison, c ntr-adevr nu era<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>lesne s-i conving pe diferiii acionari i directori ai vechilor <text:s text:c="2"/>societi s admit planul lui de reorganizare. Niciodat nu-i <text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>usese <text:s text:c="2"/>dat s aib de-a face cu<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>oameni at<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t de circumspeci, de reci. Au <text:s text:c="2"/>refuzat net oferta, lui Cowperwood de a cumpra imediat la trei sau <text:s text:c="2"/>patru dolari n loc de unul. Aciunile fiecreia din aceste societi <text:s text:c="2"/>erau cotate ntre o sut aptezeci i dou sute zece, iar valoarea lor <text:s text:c="2"/>intrinsec cretea pe msur ce oraul se dezvolta, i nevoia de gaz <text:s text:c="2"/>aerian devenise n consecin tot mai mare. n afar de asta, toi <text:s text:c="2"/>suspectau orice combinaie propus de un nou venit. n fond <text:span text:style-name="T1">ci</text:span>ne era <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood? Pen<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>ru cine lucra<text:span text:style-name="T1">?</text:span> Las s se <text:s text:c="2"/>neleag c era posesorul unui capital serios, dar <text:s text:c="2"/>nu i pe cine anume <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>e bizuia<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> Vechii funcionari <text:s text:c="2"/>i directori i nchipuiau c ar putea fi un complot <text:s text:c="2"/>organizat de conductorii celorlalte societi cu <text:s text:c="2"/>scopul de a-i mtura pe ei. De ce ar vinde? De ce <text:s text:c="2"/>s-ar lsa ispitii de nite profituri mai mari pe care <text:s text:c="2"/>ar putea s <text:soft-page-break/>le trag din aciuni, care deocamdat le <text:s text:c="2"/>aduceau i aa venituri frumuele. De aceea, pentru <text:s text:c="2"/>c el venise de cur<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd la Chicago, cu relaii insu<text:span text:style-name="T1">fi</text:span>ciente n lumea marei finane, Cowperwood fu sili<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span> s recurg la un alt plan. A fost nevoit s organizeze noi societi la periferia oraului, un prim pas n<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>atacul mpotriva centrului. Suburbii ca de pild<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>Lake View i Hyde Park, cu consilii steti i or<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>eneti proprii, aveau dreptul s acorde privilegii <text:s text:c="2"/>companiilor de gaz aerian, de ap i de tramvaie, <text:s text:c="2"/>organizate conform legilor n vigoare ale statului; <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood socotea c dac va putea njgheba <text:s text:c="2"/>societi n aparen autonome pentru fiecare ora <text:s text:c="2"/>sau sat, iar mai trziu o singur companie general; <text:s text:c="2"/>va fi n situaia de a pune condiii vechilor organizaii. Totul era doar s obin drepturile i privi legiile nainte <text:s text:c="2"/>ca rivalii lui s se fi desmetici<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Singura dificultate era c el, Cowperwood, nu <text:s text:c="2"/>tia absolut nimic n materie de gaz aerian  despre <text:s text:c="2"/>producia i distribuirea lui  p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n atunci nu-l interesase niciodat n mod special. Tramvaiele, care <text:s text:c="2"/>la Philadelphia constituiser obiectivul su prefera<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span> n goana dup profituri pentru municipiu i <text:s text:c="2"/>despre care acum poseda o cantitate enorm de <text:s text:c="2"/>informaii specializate, aici nu ofereau o surs de <text:s text:c="2"/>ctiguri reale aa cum nelegea el, ntoarse problema n fel i chip, i se document n materie de <text:s text:c="2"/>gaz aerian, pin cind, brusc, pentru c era, un om <text:s text:c="2"/>norocos, Cowperwood gsi <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>oluia cea mai la <text:s text:c="2"/>ndemn<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"><text:span text:style-name="T1">Cndva, </text:span><text:s text:c="2"/>de-a <text:span text:style-name="T1">l</text:span>ungul dezvoltrii companiei <text:span text:style-name="T2">South</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3"> Side</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1"> existase </text:span>o societate mai mic ntemeiat <text:s text:c="2"/>de matrapazl<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>curi, un privilegiu, care s-i permit s produc i s <text:s text:c="2"/>v<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nd gaz aerian n suburbiile oraului <text:span text:style-name="T1">i</text:span> avusese <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ns tot soiul de <text:s text:c="2"/>neplceri i de rfuieli <text:span text:style-name="T1">cu</text:span> legea p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n ce a trebuit<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>s plece sau mai <text:s text:c="2"/>bine zis p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n c<text:span text:style-name="T1">e</text:span> a fost convins s se retrag. Acum conducea o agenie <text:s text:c="2"/>imobiliar la Lake View. <text:span text:style-name="T1">B</text:span>tr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nul Peter Laughlin l cunotea. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Este detept i destul de abil, <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>i spuse Laughlin lui Cowperwood. La <text:s text:c="2"/>un moment dat am crezut c o s reueasc, dar l-au prins cu m<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>a-n sac <text:s text:c="2"/>i a <text:soft-page-break/>trebuit s dea bir cu fugiii. A explodat o cistern de l<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ng ru <text:s text:c="2"/>i el i-a nchipuit c bieii au pus treaba la cale. n tot cazul a <text:s text:c="2"/>plecat. N-am mai auzit nimic de el, i nici nu l-am mai vzut de-un car <text:s text:c="2"/>de ani.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Cowperwood trimise pe btr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nul Laughlin s-l caute pe domnul Sippens i <text:s text:c="2"/>s vad cu ce anume se ndeletnicea, i dac nu l-ar interesa s intre <text:s text:c="2"/>din nou ntr-o afacere cu gazul aerian. Astfel, c<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>teva zile mai trziu, <text:s text:c="2"/>Henry De Soto Sippens se prezent la sediul lui Peter Laughlin &amp; Comp. <text:s text:c="2"/>Era<text:span text:style-name="T1"> </text:span>un om foarte mic de statur i avea aproximativ cincizeci de ani; <text:s text:c="2"/>purta o plrie nalt, ptrat, de fetru tare, i o hain cafenie, <text:s text:c="2"/>scurt, cu care se ducea de obicei la birou (vara haina era de doc) i <text:s text:c="2"/>nite ghete cu botul ptrat. Semna a librar sau a spier de provincie; <text:s text:c="2"/>la asta se mai adiuga poate i un aer de doctor sau avocat de ar. <text:s text:c="2"/>Manetele prea ieeau muli n mi: necile hainei, cravata din vest, iar <text:s text:c="2"/>plri<text:span text:style-name="T1">a</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">p</text:span>urta dat cam prea tare pe spate; altminteri era un om <text:s text:c="2"/>prezentabil, simpatie i interesant. Avea cotlei scuri  zb<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>rlii, de <text:s text:c="2"/>un cafeniu roscat  i spr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ncene stu<text:span text:style-name="T1">f</text:span>oase.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Domnule Sippe<text:span text:style-name="T1">ns</text:span>, se adres Cowperwood, mieros, dac nu m-nel ai <text:s text:c="2"/>lucra<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span> pe vremuri la o societate de gaz aerian, aici n Chicago? </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Da, <text:s text:c="2"/>cunos<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span> problema, cred, mai bine ca oricine, rosti Sippens, gata de <text:s text:c="2"/>lupt. Ani de zile am <text:span text:style-name="T1">lucrat </text:span>n domeniul <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>sta. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> <text:span text:style-name="T1">E</text:span>i bine, domnule <text:s text:c="2"/>Sippens, m-am g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndit c ar fi nimerit s nfiinm o mic societate de <text:s text:c="2"/>gaz aerian <text:span text:style-name="T1">ntr-</text:span>unul din satele din jurul oraului care se dezvolt vznd cu ochii. Am putea trage un profi<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span> din <text:s text:c="2"/>asta. Personal nu snt specialist n materie de <text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span>az <text:s text:c="2"/>dar m-am g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndit c propunerea mea ar putea, ispit <text:s text:c="2"/>pe cineva versat n acest domeniu. l privea pe <text:s text:c="2"/>Sippens cu simpatie, dar iscoditor. Mi <text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>-a vorhi<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>despre dumneata ca despre un om cu o vast experien, Dac eu a <text:s text:c="2"/>nfiina <text:span text:style-name="T1">o</text:span> astfel de societate <text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>u un capital serios ai fi dispus s-o <text:s text:c="2"/>conduci?</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7">Oh, cunos<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span> foarte bine problema, a spune chiar n toate <text:s text:c="2"/>aspectele ei, era gata s rspund domnul Sippens, e un lucru <text:s text:c="2"/>imposibil. Dar nainte de a <text:soft-page-break/>deschide gura, se r<text:span text:style-name="T13">z</text:span>g<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ndi.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Dac a fi destul de bine pltit... spuse el circumspect ... <text:s text:c="2"/>cred c v dai seama de toate dificultile pe care le-a <text:s text:c="2"/>avea de ntimpinat.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"> Da, sigur, zise Cowperwood, zmbind. Ce nelegi prin <text:span text:style-name="T2">destul de bine pl</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3">t</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">it</text:span>?</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Cu un salariu fix de ase mii de dolari pe an i cu o participare <text:s text:c="2"/>rezonabil, la ctigurile societii  s zicem cincizeci la sut sau <text:s text:c="2"/>cam aa ceva  a pu<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>ea lua propunerea dumitale n serios, preciz <text:s text:c="2"/>Sippens, care urmrea s-l descurajeze pe Cowperwood cu preteniile lui <text:s/>exagerate. n afacerile imobiliare cu care se ocupa, scotea, anual, cam <text:s text:c="2"/>ase mii de dolari.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Nu crezi c patru mii de dolari n mai multe societi, ceea ce i <text:s text:c="2"/>va aduce p<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n la cincisprezece mii pe an  plus o participare de <text:s text:c="2"/>aproape zece la sut la fiecare ar fi mai avantajos?</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Domnul Sippens chibzui oferta cu atenie i pruden. Era clar c nu <text:s text:c="2"/>se afla n faa unui tinerel <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>nceptor. Se uit la Cowperwood cu <text:s text:c="2"/>mult bgare de seam i pricepu numaidec<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>t, fr s mai atep<text:span text:style-name="T1">t</text:span>e alte <text:s text:c="2"/>explicaii, c acesta, se pregtea s dea, o mare lupt, fr s tie <text:s text:c="2"/>ce lupt anume. Cu zece ani n urm Sippens ntrezrise avantajele <text:s text:c="2"/>imense care <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T1">s</text:span>e puteau obine din gazul aerian. ncercase s intre<text:span text:style-name="T1"> n</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">aceasst </text:span>afacere dar fusese atras ntr-o curs i dat<text:span text:style-name="T1"> n judecat, dup </text:span>care primise ordinul s lichideze<text:span text:style-name="T1">.</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T1">Apoi, cu toi </text:span>banii blocai<text:span text:style-name="T1">,</text:span> s<text:span text:style-name="T1">e trezise</text:span> la sap<text:span text:style-name="T1"> de lemn. Nu uitase nici pn azi felul jignitor n care fusese tratat, i-i prea ru c nu putuse s se rz</text:span>bune. Credea c epoca ambiiilor lui financiare se ter<text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span>inase, dar iat <text:s text:c="2"/>c acum se afla <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>n faa unui om care-i sugera n <text:span text:style-name="T1">m</text:span>od subtil o lupt <text:s text:c="2"/>cr<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>ncen, i care, precum vntorul, i aduna oamenii cu goarna.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Ei bine, domnule Cowperwood, rspunse Sippens, cu mai puin <text:s text:c="2"/>scepticism i cu mai mult bunvoin, dac-mi poi dovedi c <text:s text:c="2"/>propunerea dumitale dte serioas vei gsi n mine un adevrat expert n <text:s text:c="2"/>problemele gazului aerian. Cunosc perfect instalarea conductelor, <text:s text:c="2"/>contractele, privilegiile i tot utilajul. Eu am montat uzina de la <text:s text:c="2"/>Dayton, Ohio i de la <text:soft-page-break/>Rochester, New York. i dac veneam la Chicago <text:s text:c="2"/>ceva mai devreme, azi a fi fost un om bogat. n vocea, lui se simea <text:s text:c="2"/>un regret.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> <text:span text:style-name="T13">E</text:span>i bine, atunci, s tii c i-a ieit norocul n cale, l <text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>ndemn <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood, abil. Dumneata i cu mine s<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>ntem pe punctul s njghebm <text:s text:c="2"/>aici o nou i mare societate de gaz aerian. O s le artm noi <text:s text:c="2"/>btr<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>nilor stora cu cine au de-a face. Nu i se pare interesant <text:s/>propunerea? Bani avem destui. Nu asta ne lipsete  ne lipsete un <text:s text:c="2"/>organizator, un lupttor, un specialist care s construiasc uzina, s <text:s text:c="2"/>instaleze conductele i aa mai departe. Cowperwood se scul brusc <text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>n <text:s text:c="2"/>picioare, drept i hotr<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>t  un vechi obicei de-al lui cnd vroia s <text:s text:c="2"/>impresioneze pe cineva. Prea puternic, cuceritor, victorios. Vrei s <text:s text:c="2"/>te asociezi cu mine?</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Da, domnule Cowperwoo<text:span text:style-name="T13">d</text:span>, vreau, strig Sippens, scul<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>ndu-se n <text:s text:c="2"/>picioare ; i puse plria pe cap, ndes<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>nd-o mult spre ceaf. Semna <text:s text:c="2"/>perfect cu un coco pitic, umflat n pene.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Cowperwood i str<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>nse mna.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Pune la punct agenia dumitale imobiliar. A vrea s-mi obii ct se <text:s text:c="2"/>poate de repede un privilegiu la Lake View i s-mi cldeti o uzin. <text:s text:c="2"/>Poi conta pe tot sprijinul de care ai nevoie. ntr-o <text:span text:style-name="T13">s</text:span>ptm<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>n sau <text:s text:c="2"/>zece zile aranjez totul. O s ne trebuiasc i un avocat bun, poate <text:s text:c="2"/>chiar doi.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Sippens zmbi radios, prsind biroul. Ce minune! Dup zece ani de <text:s text:c="2"/>ateptare! Are s le arate es<text:span text:style-name="T13">c</text:span>rocilor lora cine e ei. Acum se putea <text:s text:c="2"/>bizui pe un ade vrat lupttor, un om n genul lui. Suna<text:span text:style-name="T13">s</text:span>e cearul rfuielilor. Dar, n <text:s text:c="2"/>fond, cine era acest Cowperwood? Ce om grozav! O s <text:span text:style-name="T13">s</text:span>e informeze. i <text:s text:c="2"/>ddea seama c de acum ncolo s-ar arunca i n foc dac i-ar cere-o <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood.</text:p>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2"><text:span text:style-name="Label">Capitolul VIII </text:span><text:line-break/>ncepe lupta</text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Cowperwood, dup tentativele infructuoase cu a directorii <text:s text:c="2"/>celor trei companii de gaz aerian din ora, <text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>i destinui lui <text:s text:c="2"/>Addison planul su de a nfiina niste societi concurente n <text:s text:c="2"/>suburbii, iar bancherul ncuviin din ochi.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Eti un biat detept, exclam <text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>n cele din urm, exact omul care ne <text:s text:c="2"/>trebuie ! Mizez pe cartea dumitale ! Apoi i atrase atenia c va avea <text:s text:c="2"/>nevoie de concursul c<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>torva oameni influeni din diferite -consilii <text:s text:c="2"/>steti. Oamenii tia snt mari vulpoi. i printre ei snt doi-trei <text:s text:c="2"/>care-s i mai hoi decit ceilali: tia-s ca berbecii cu talanga n <text:s text:c="2"/>fruntea turmei i din cauza asta prezint un fel de garanie. Ai <text:s text:c="2"/>angajat un avocat!</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> nc nu, dar am eu grij. <text:span text:style-name="T13">S</text:span>nt n cutare, mi trebuie unul bun.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Evident, nu-i nevoie s-i spun ce importan are acest lucru. Cunosc <text:s text:c="2"/>pe cineva... pe btr<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>nul general Van Sickle, care are mare experien <text:s text:c="2"/>n treburile astea. i cred c se poate conta pe el.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P8">Personalitatea generalului Judson P. Van Sickle a aruncat de la nceput <text:s text:c="2"/>o lumin nou asupra ntregii situaii. Veteranul, om de peste <text:s text:c="2"/>cincizeci de ani, fusese general de divizie n rzboiul civil i <text:s text:c="2"/>debutase n cariera lui actual nto<text:span text:style-name="T13">c</text:span>mind acte false de proprietate <text:s text:c="2"/>n sudul statului Illinois, dup care introducea o aciune n <text:s text:c="2"/>justiie ca s-i acopere operaiile <text:span text:style-name="T13">frau</text:span>duloase, comisia de judecat fiind <text:s text:c="2"/>alctuit <text:span text:style-name="T13">din</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T13">buni </text:span>prieteni de<text:span text:style-name="T13">-</text:span>ai <text:span text:style-name="T13">l</text:span>ui. Ac<text:span text:style-name="T13">u</text:span>m era <text:span text:style-name="T13">u</text:span>n intermediar<text:span text:style-name="T13"> prosper care pretindea</text:span> onorarii serioase. Totui <text:span text:style-name="T13">nu era nc un om bogat. </text:span>Pro<text:span text:style-name="T13">iec</text:span>tul lui Cowperwood <text:span text:style-name="T13">era genul de afaceri cu care se mai ocupa. Fr s vrei, i venea s-l compari cu oaia care, n ocolul de vite, ademenete pe celelalte  dresat s conduc turmele speriate la abator, s </text:span><text:soft-page-break/><text:span text:style-name="T13">le conduc domol </text:span>la <text:s text:c="2"/>tiat, destul de neleapt ns ca s stea n urm tot timpul ct <text:s text:c="2"/>nainteaz semenele ei i ast<text:span text:style-name="T13">f</text:span>el s rm<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>n neatins. Era un avocat <text:s text:c="2"/>btr<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>n i pariv, care ticluise at<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>tea testamente false n viaa lui, <text:s text:c="2"/>clcase at<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>tea promisiuni, mituise at<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>ia jurai sau judectori, <text:s text:c="2"/>cumprase at<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>ia legislatori i consilieri, fcuse at<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>tea contracte i <text:s text:c="2"/>acorduri n doi peri i avusese at<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>tea expediente, chipurile sub o <text:s text:c="2"/>spoial de legalitate, nct nu mai tia nici el. n lumea <text:s text:c="2"/>politicienilor, a judectorilor i avocailor trecea n general drept <text:s text:c="2"/>un om cu relaii importante, c<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>tigate prin multiplele servicii <text:s text:c="2"/>fcute n trecut. i plcea s se apeleze la el n orice situaie i <text:s text:c="2"/>asta mai ales ca s-i fac de lucru i s scape de plictiseal. <text:s text:c="2"/>Iarna, cnd trebuia s se nt<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>lneasc cu cineva, <text:span text:style-name="T13">s</text:span>e mbrca cu un <text:s text:c="2"/>palton vechi de stof gri, ponosit de c<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>i ani l purtase, apoi lua din <text:s text:c="2"/>cui o plrie de fetru moale, diform, uzat, pe care o trgea pe ochi, <text:s text:c="2"/>nite ochi cenuii i inexpresivi  i o pornea de-acas. Vara purta <text:s text:c="2"/>nite haine att de boite, nct prea c n ele doarme sptm<text:span text:style-name="T13">n</text:span>i n <text:s text:c="2"/>ir. <text:span text:style-name="T13">i</text:span> plcea s fumeze. Semna puin cu generalul Grant; avea musta <text:s text:c="2"/>i brbu crunt, venic ne<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>ngrijit, iar prul des, tot crunt, i <text:s text:c="2"/>cdea pe frunte. Srmanul general ! Nu era nici prea fericit, ni<text:span text:style-name="T13">c</text:span>i <text:s text:c="2"/>prea nenorocit. <text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>ntocmai ca Toma Necredinciosul, nu credea n oameni, <text:s text:c="2"/>nu-i fcea iluzii i n-avea nici pic de afec<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>iune pentru nimeni.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Am s-i explic, domnule Cowperwood, ce-i cu consiliile astea <text:s text:c="2"/>mrunte, ncepu Van Sickle, cu nelepciune, trecnd direct la <text:s text:c="2"/>chestiune, fr preliminariile de rigoare, chiar de la prima <text:s text:c="2"/>ntrevedere. Aproape c-s mai pctoi dec<text:span text:style-name="T13">t</text:span> Consiliul municipal i <text:s text:c="2"/>asta nseamn ceva! Fr bani nu poi face nimic cu <text:span text:style-name="T13">t</text:span>ipii tia mici. <text:s text:c="2"/>Nu prea-mi place s critic oamenii, dar tia-s nite poame, mam <text:s text:c="2"/>doamne !.. i scutur din cap.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> neleg, spuse Cowperwood. Nu le intri nici<text:span text:style-name="T13">o</text:span>dat <text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>n voie, chiar dac <text:s text:c="2"/>respeci regulile joc<text:span text:style-name="T13">ului.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Mai toi-s aa, continu generalul, i <text:s/>tocmai cnd crezi c-ai pus <text:s text:c="2"/>mai bine mna pe ei. nc<text:span text:style-name="T13">ep</text:span> s vnd i snt n stare s alerge cu limba <text:s text:c="2"/>sco<text:span text:style-name="T13">as la</text:span> <text:soft-page-break/>societile de gaz aerian din nord, s poveste<text:span text:style-name="T13">asc</text:span> tot, nainte ca<text:span text:style-name="T13"> dumneata </text:span>s <text:span text:style-name="T13">f</text:span>i putut face ce<text:span text:style-name="T13">v</text:span>a<text:span text:style-name="T13">. i</text:span> iar ali bani, poate chiar alte <text:s text:c="2"/>propuneri i uite <text:span text:style-name="T13">aa...</text:span> Apoi adug, schimonosindu-se: Totui, unul <text:span text:style-name="T13">s</text:span>au doi <text:s text:c="2"/>dintre ei snt de treab  dac <text:span text:style-name="T13">bineneles</text:span> ajungi s le st<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>rneti <text:s text:c="2"/>interesul  domnul Dun<text:span text:style-name="T13">way</text:span> i domnul Gerecht.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Pe mine nu m privete cum se va proceda domnule general, interveni <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood amabil. <text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>in ns ca totul s se fac repede i discret. <text:span text:style-name="T13">N</text:span>u <text:s text:c="2"/>vreau s-mi bat capul cu detalii. Nu s-ar putea s evitm o<text:span text:style-name="T13"> </text:span>prea mare <text:s text:c="2"/>publicitate? i cam c<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>t crezi c o s coste?</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Pi, e greu de spus nainte de a studia che<text:span text:style-name="T13">s</text:span>tiunea, rspunse <text:s text:c="2"/>generalul, chibzuind. S-ar putea s coste numai patru mii de dolari, <text:s text:c="2"/>dup cum s-ar putea s n-ajung nici patruzeci de mii. Nu <text:span text:style-name="T13">t</text:span>iu nc. <text:s text:c="2"/>Mi-ar trebui puin rgaz ca s m informez<text:span text:style-name="T13">.</text:span> Generalul se ntreba cam <text:s text:c="2"/>c<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>t ar fi fost dispus Cowperwood s cheltuiasc.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> n orice caz, s lsm astea deocamdat. <text:span text:style-name="T13">S</text:span>nt gata s vin cu toi <text:s text:c="2"/>banii necesari. Am i trimis dup domnul Sippens, preedintele companiei de ga<text:span text:style-name="T13">z</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T13">a</text:span>erian i combustibil din Lak<text:span text:style-name="T13">e</text:span> View, <text:span text:style-name="T13">c</text:span>are trebuie s <text:s text:c="2"/>soseasc dintr-o clip-ntr-al<text:span text:style-name="T13">t</text:span>a. Va trebui s lucrai ct mai mult <text:s text:c="2"/>mpreun.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Dup cteva minute apru i energicul domn Sippens. Cowperwood le <text:s text:c="2"/>atrase atenia am<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>ndurora c vor trebui s colaboreze i s evite ca <text:s text:c="2"/>numele lui s apar n aceast afacere. Dup care, bine instrui<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>i, <text:s text:c="2"/>plecar mpreun. Alctuiau o pereche foarte bizar  generalul, <text:s text:c="2"/>btr<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>n, flegmati<text:span text:style-name="T13">c</text:span>, dezamgit, util, <text:span text:style-name="T13">fr</text:span> s-i dea seama, i Sippens, <text:s text:c="2"/>detept, vesel, nsu<text:span text:style-name="T13">f</text:span>l<text:span text:style-name="T13">e</text:span>it de un sentiment aproape poetic de <text:s text:c="2"/>rzbunare <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T13">mpotriva </text:span>vechiului lui South Side Gas<text:span text:style-name="T13"> Company, prin acest complot destul de subtil al</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>celor din districtul nordic. n zece minute <text:span text:style-name="T13">e</text:span>rau ca fraii. Generalul <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>i explica lui Sippens politica meschin i lipsit de scrupule a <text:s text:c="2"/>consilierului Duniway i natura prietenoas, dar interesat, a lui <text:s text:c="2"/>Jacob Gerecht. Aa e viaa!</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">n vederea nfiinrii companiei <text:span text:style-name="T2">Hyde Par</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T4">k</text:span>, Co<text:span text:style-name="T13">w</text:span>perwood, pentru c <text:s text:c="2"/>nu-i <text:soft-page-break/>plcea niciodat s mizeze toi banii pe o singur carte, se <text:s text:c="2"/>hotr<text:span text:style-name="T13"> </text:span>s mai <text:span text:style-name="T13">g</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T13">s</text:span>easc un avocat i un al<text:span text:style-name="T13">t</text:span> om de paie n calitate d<text:span text:style-name="T13">e</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>pre<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>edinte, dei era dispus s-l pstreze pe De Soto Sippens ca pe <text:s text:c="2"/>sfetnicul lui permanent n toate chestiunile de ordin practie ale <text:s text:c="2"/>celorlalte trei sau patru co<text:span text:style-name="T13">m</text:span>panii.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">C<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>nd se gndea, cum s rezolve aceast problem, apru n scen un om <text:s text:c="2"/>mult mai tnr ca b<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>tr<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>nul general, un oarecare Kent Barrows Mc<text:span text:style-name="T13">K</text:span>ibben, <text:s text:c="2"/>unicul fiu al lui Marshall Scammon Mckibben, fostul judector al Curii <text:s text:c="2"/>Supreme din Statul <text:span text:style-name="T13">Il</text:span>linois. Kent McKibben avea treizeci i trei de <text:s text:c="2"/>ani, era nalt, sportiv, un biat frumos, n genul lui. Cunotinele <text:s text:c="2"/>lui n ceea ce privete conducerea afacerilor erau precise i <text:s text:c="2"/>preioase; ca om ns era cam fandosi<text:span text:style-name="T13">t </text:span>i uneori distant<text:span text:style-name="T13">.</text:span> Cu un aer <text:s text:c="2"/>superior pornea n fiecare diminea la ora nou  dac bine<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>neles nu <text:s text:c="2"/>intervenea ceva important; care s-l cheme mai devreme n orala <text:s text:c="2"/>biroul lui situat ntr-unul din ele mai frumoase blocuri de pe strada <text:s text:c="2"/>Dearborn. <text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>nt<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>mplarea fcuse ca el s fi redactat actele i <text:span text:style-name="T13">c</text:span>ontractele <text:s text:c="2"/>societii imobiliare care-i v<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>nduse lui <text:span text:style-name="T13">C</text:span>owperwood parcelele din strada <text:s text:c="2"/>Treizeci i apte, <text:span text:style-name="T13">co</text:span>l <text:span text:style-name="T13">c</text:span>u Michigan Avenue iar cnd h<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>rtiile fuseser <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T13">g</text:span>ata, se <text:span text:style-name="T13">d</text:span>usese la biroul acestuia s-l ntrebe dac <text:span text:style-name="T13">nu</text:span> cumva mai erau <text:s text:c="2"/>i alte amnunte de care Cow<text:span text:style-name="T13">per</text:span>wood ar <text:span text:style-name="T13">f</text:span>i dorit s se in seam. Cnd <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T13">f</text:span>u intro<text:span text:style-name="T13">dus, </text:span>Cowperwood l msur din cap p<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>n-n picioare<text:span text:style-name="T13"> cu o privire</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>analitic, i <text:span text:style-name="T13">f</text:span>u izbit de personalitatea,<text:span text:style-name="T13"> plcut a</text:span> <text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T13">lui </text:span>Ribben. nfiarea lui distant <text:span text:style-name="T13">i elegant atr</text:span>gea<text:span text:style-name="T13">.</text:span> i plcu felul n care era <text:s text:c="2"/>mbr<text:span text:style-name="T13">cat, aerul enigmatic</text:span> i manierele lui de om de lume. <text:span text:style-name="T13">Pe de alt parte, Mc</text:span>Kibbe<text:span text:style-name="T13">n</text:span> i ddu din prima <text:s text:c="2"/>clip<text:span text:style-name="T13"> seama c se afl n </text:span>lumea marii finane. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P8"><text:span text:style-name="T13">Observase</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>imediat costumnul maro deschis al lui Cowpe<text:span text:style-name="T13">rwood, </text:span>n dungi roii, cravata asortat i butonii <text:span text:style-name="T13">mici cu</text:span> <text:s/>camee de la manete. Masa de lucru, acoperi<text:span text:style-name="T13">t cu </text:span><text:s text:c="3"/>un cristal, era sobr, impecabil. Lambriurile <text:span text:style-name="T13">odilor </text:span>erau toate din lemn de cire lustruit, iar grav<text:span text:style-name="T13">urile</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>de pe perei reprezentnd aspecte din viaa: ameri<text:span text:style-name="T13">can</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>erau <text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>nrmate cu gust. Maina de scris  caro a<text:span text:style-name="T13">bia</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>apruse la epoca aceea  trona pe mas. Telexu<text:span text:style-name="T13">l </text:span>bursei  nou i el  <text:s text:c="2"/><text:soft-page-break/>comunica continuu pre<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>urile <text:s text:c="2"/>curente. Secretara lui Cowperwood  o t<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>nr pol<text:span text:style-name="T13">o</text:span>nez pe care o chema <text:s text:c="2"/>Antoinette Nowak, o bru<text:span text:style-name="T13">net </text:span><text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T13">f</text:span>oarte atrgtoare, prea deteapt i rezer<text:span text:style-name="T13">vat.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Cu ce fel de afaceri te ocupi, domnule McKib<text:span text:style-name="T13">ben? <text:s/></text:span>ntreb Cowperwood pe un ton detaat. Du<text:span text:style-name="T13">p ce </text:span>ascult rspunsul lui McKibben, adug<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span> indifere<text:span text:style-name="T13">nt:</text:span> Dac vrei, poi <text:s text:c="2"/>trece pe la mine sptmna viitoar<text:span text:style-name="T13">e.</text:span> S-ar putea ntimpla s am atunci <text:s text:c="2"/>ceva pentru dumneata.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Din partea oricrui alt om, sugestia vag de a-l ajuta l-ar fi jignit <text:s text:c="2"/>pe MeKibben ; acum, dimpotri<text:span text:style-name="T13">v</text:span>, i fcu mare plcere. Omul din faa lui <text:s text:c="2"/>i stimula imaginaia. ncepu s mai renune la ifosele de intelectual blazat. C<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>nd veni din nou la Cowperwood, acesta i preciz ce <text:s text:c="2"/>anume ar vrea s-i dea de lucru, iar M<text:span text:style-name="T13">c</text:span>Kibben se prinse ca petele de <text:s text:c="2"/>momeal<text:span text:style-name="T13">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Tare a dori s ncerc, rosti M<text:span text:style-name="T13">c</text:span>Kibben cu entuziasm. E un lucru pe <text:s text:c="2"/>care nu l-am mai fcut, dar de care cred c m pot achita. Locuiesc la <text:s text:c="2"/>Hyde Park i cunos<text:span text:style-name="T13">c</text:span> majoritatea consilierilor de acolo<text:span text:style-name="T13">.</text:span> A putea <text:s text:c="2"/>exercita o influen destul de mare n favoarea dumitale.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Cowperwood zmbi cu simpatie.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Astfel se nfiin o nou societate condus, de nite oameni de paie <text:s text:c="2"/>alei de M<text:span text:style-name="T13">c</text:span>Kibben. Sippens, fr tirea btrinului general Van Sickle, <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T13">f</text:span>usese i el cooptat consilier consultant. Se ceruse un privilegiu, <text:s text:c="2"/>iar Kent Barrows MeKibben ncepu s<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>lucreze pe tcute i cu mult tact la societatea <text:span text:style-name="T2">South Side</text:span>, c<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>tignd <text:s text:c="2"/>treptat ncrederea diferiilor consilieri.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">M<text:span text:style-name="T13">ai era </text:span>al treilea avocat, Burton Stimson, i cel <text:span text:style-name="T13">m</text:span>ai puin capabil din cei <text:s text:c="2"/>trei  un fel de Romeo, palid, cu pr negru i cu o privire pasionat, <text:s text:c="2"/>pe care Cowperwood l cunoscuse pe cnd t<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>nrul se ocupa de ni<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>te <text:s text:c="2"/>afaceri mrunte de-ale lui Laughlin. Cowperwood l angaja<text:span text:style-name="T13">s</text:span>e acum s <text:s text:c="2"/>lucreze la West Side mpreun cu btr<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>nul Laughlin, ca director <text:s text:c="2"/>prezumat, i cu neobositul <text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>i <text:soft-page-break/>ntre<text:span text:style-name="T13">p</text:span>rinztorul De Soto Sippens n <text:s text:c="2"/>funcia de consilier consultant. Stimson, <text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>ns, departe de a fi un <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T13">R</text:span>omeo vistor, era un om cu o minte ptrunztoare, ambiios, nscut <text:s text:c="2"/>n srcie i dorni<text:span text:style-name="T13">c</text:span> s parvin. Co<text:span text:style-name="T13">w</text:span>perwood i ddu numaidec<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>t seama <text:s text:c="2"/>c agerimea minii acestui biat putea duce pe muli la sap de lemn, <text:s text:c="2"/>dar pentru el, putea fi o binefacere. Avea nevoie de subalterni <text:s text:c="2"/>inteligeni. Era gata s-i plteasc bine, s-i fac s munceasc <text:s text:c="2"/>serios, s-i trateze cu o politee desvirit, dar n schimb le cerea <text:s text:c="2"/>un devotament absolut. Stimson, cu toat morga pe care se strduia s <text:s text:c="2"/>o afieze, ar fi fost n stare s srute mina arhiepiscopal. Ce <text:s text:c="2"/>misterioase snt legturile care se stabilesc ntre oameni !</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">i iat cum deodat n North Side, West Side i <text:s text:c="2"/>South Side ncepur s se desfoare n umbr tot <text:s text:c="2"/>soiul de manevre. La Lake View, btr<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>nul general Van Sickle i De Soto <text:s text:c="2"/>Sippens duceau tratative cu consilierul Duniway, un farmacist iret, <text:s text:c="2"/>i cu<text:span text:style-name="T13"> Jacob Gerecht, eful circumscripiei electorale i mcelar angrosist, amndoi oameni acomodani </text:span><text:s text:c="3"/>dar perari din cale-afar; se str<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>ngeau la discuie n odile din <text:s text:c="2"/>dos sau n magazin i socoteau centim cu centim ctigurile i <text:s text:c="2"/>beneficiile. La Hyde <text:s/>Park domnul Kent Barrows M<text:span text:style-name="T13">c</text:span>Kibben, ntruchiparea distinciei, ncrezut i bine mtricat, ns<text:span text:style-name="T13">o</text:span>it<text:span text:style-name="T13"> </text:span><text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T13">d</text:span>e un oarecare J. <text:s text:c="2"/>J. Bergdoll, un nobil subaltern <text:span text:style-name="T13">n</text:span>e<text:span text:style-name="T13">t</text:span>uns i jerpelit, aa-zisul preedinte <text:s text:c="2"/>al <text:span text:style-name="T2">Companiei Gaz-aerian i combustibil</text:span> din Hyde Park, con<text:span text:style-name="T13">f</text:span>ereau<text:span text:style-name="T13"> </text:span>consilieru<text:span text:style-name="T13">i</text:span> municipal Alfred B. Davis, fa<text:span text:style-name="T13">brican</text:span>t de obiecte din nuiele <text:s text:c="2"/>de trestie i salcie i cu anul Patrick Gilgan, crciumar, despre o <text:s text:c="2"/>viitoare <text:span text:style-name="T13">mp</text:span>rire a aciunilor, oferind bani lichizi, parcele, <text:span text:style-name="T13">favo</text:span>ruri i <text:s text:c="2"/>a<text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>a mai departe. Iar n satul Douglas <text:span text:style-name="T13">i W</text:span>est Park din West Side, imediat <text:s text:c="2"/>dincolo de <text:s/>centura oraului, Peter L<text:span text:style-name="T14">a</text:span>ughlin, firav <text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>i pl<text:span text:style-name="T13">in</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T13">de </text:span>haz, <text:span text:style-name="T13"></text:span>mpreun cu Burton Stimson, puneau <text:span text:style-name="T14">la cale o</text:span> afacere sau mai multe afaceri asem<text:span text:style-name="T14">ntoare.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P9"><text:span text:style-name="T14">Dumanul, adic</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>societile de gaz a<text:span text:style-name="T14">e</text:span>ria<text:span text:style-name="T14">n ale</text:span> oraului, mprite n trei fraciuni rivale, <text:s text:c="2"/>nu <text:span text:style-name="T14">erau </text:span>deloc pregtite pentru ceea ce urma s s<text:span text:style-name="T14">e</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T14">ntmple</text:span>; C<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>nd <text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>n sf<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>rit veni <text:s text:c="2"/>vestea c se ceruser ni<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>te p<text:span text:style-name="T14">rivil</text:span>e<text:span text:style-name="T14">g</text:span>ii de la diferitele <text:soft-page-break/>organisme steti, <text:s text:c="2"/>n<text:span text:style-name="T14">jgh</text:span>e<text:span text:style-name="T14">bate </text:span>n corporaii, cele trei societi <text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>ncepur s se <text:span text:style-name="T14">sus</text:span>pecteze una <text:s text:c="2"/>pe alta de acaparare, trdare i <text:span text:style-name="T14">hoie.</text:span> Fiecare societate trimise cte un <text:s text:c="2"/>avocat c<text:span text:style-name="T14">rcota</text:span> la fiecare consiliu stesc din regiunea respec<text:span text:style-name="T14">tiv,</text:span> fr ca <text:s text:c="2"/>deocamdat vreuna din vechile soci<text:span text:style-name="T14">e</text:span>t<text:span text:style-name="T14">i s</text:span> tie cine anume se afla n dosul <text:s text:c="2"/>acestui proi<text:span text:style-name="T14">e</text:span>c<text:span text:style-name="T14">t</text:span> care era adevratul plan de aciune. nainte <text:span text:style-name="T14">ca </text:span>vreuna din <text:s text:c="2"/>societi s fi fost <text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>ndreptit s pr<text:span text:style-name="T14">o</text:span>testeze, sau s fi luat <text:s text:c="2"/>hotr<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>rea de<text:span text:style-name="T14"> </text:span>a plti o mare sum<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span> de bani, pentru ca astfel teritoriul <text:s text:c="2"/>alturat s r<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>m<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>n<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span> disponibil, inainte de a putea organiza o lupt<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T14">pe </text:span><text:s text:c="3"/>baze legale, consiliul municipal ddu dispozi<text:span text:style-name="T14">ii </text:span>ca cererea noii societi <text:s text:c="2"/>s fie satisfcut i dup singur expunere a cazului n faa <text:s text:c="2"/>consiliului i o singur dezbatere public, dup cum cerea legea<text:span text:style-name="T14">,</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>hot<text:span text:style-name="T14">r</text:span>rea nfiinrii societii lui Cowperwood se aprob <text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>n <text:s text:c="2"/>unanimitate. O dat chestiunea tran<text:span text:style-name="T14">a</text:span>t<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>, c<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>teva gazete locale, de m<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>na <text:s text:c="2"/>a doua, gazete crora Cowperwood pierduse din vedere s le dea b<text:span text:style-name="T14">a</text:span>ni, <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>ncepur s scoat ipete de indignare. Presa central de mare tiraj <text:s text:c="2"/>la nceput nu ddu prea mare atenie acestor incidente periferice; se <text:s text:c="2"/>mrgini s<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span> remarce c satele porniser pe un drum bun, urm<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>nd exemplul <text:s text:c="2"/>consiliului municipal n strlu<text:span text:style-name="T14">c</text:span>ita sa carier<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span> strdaniei de<text:span text:style-name="T14"> </text:span>a da n <text:s text:c="2"/>vileag orice <text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>nclcare a legii. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P9">Cowperwood zmbi mulumi<text:span text:style-name="T14">t </text:span>cnd citi n <text:s text:c="2"/>ziarele de diminea c fusese aprobat fiecare decret care-i acorda un <text:s text:c="2"/>privilegiu. Zile de-a r<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>ndul a ascultat cu satisfacie rapoartele lui <text:s text:c="2"/>Laughlin, Sippe<text:span text:style-name="T14">ns</text:span>, <text:span text:style-name="T14">McKibben </text:span>i Van Sickle despre propunerile car<text:span text:style-name="T14">e</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T14">li se fceau pentru </text:span>negocierea <text:s text:c="3"/>privilegiilor dob<text:span text:style-name="T14">n</text:span>dite. <text:span text:style-name="T14">Lucra cu S</text:span>ippens la planuri pentru instalarea <text:span text:style-name="T14">propriu-zis a uzinelor </text:span>de gaz ae<text:span text:style-name="T14">r</text:span>ian. Acum trebuiau emise obligaii, scoase aciuni pe pia, a<text:span text:style-name="T14">n</text:span>gajai furnizori <text:s text:c="2"/>prin contract, construite rezervoare i cisterne, i instalate <text:s text:c="2"/>conducte. Trebuia pre<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>nt<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>mpinat un nou val de protest din partea unui <text:s text:c="2"/>anumit public. De Soto se dovedi n toate aceste mprejurri de o rar <text:s text:c="2"/>eficien. mpreun cu sfetnicii lui din diferite sectoare ale <text:s text:c="2"/>oraului, Van Sickle, McKibben i Stimson, el reui s-i prezinte lui <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood propuneri succinte i acesta nu avu dec<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>t s le aprobe <text:s text:c="2"/>sau s le resping. <text:soft-page-break/>Apoi De Soto cumpr, construi i excav. Cowperwood<text:span text:style-name="T14">,</text:span> extrem de mulumit <text:s text:c="2"/>de Henry De Soto hotr<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>se s nu se mai despart de el niciodat. Iar De <text:s text:c="2"/>Soto, fericit c avea prilejul s se rzbune i s ntreprind lucruri <text:s text:c="2"/>mari, era cu adevrat recunosctor.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> N-am terminat ns cu eserocii tia, i declar lui Cowperwood <text:s text:c="2"/>ntr-o bun zi, triumftor. Ne vor da n judecat. S-ar putea chiar s <text:s text:c="2"/>se neleag ntre ei. Mi-au aruncat odat uzina n aer, acum snt n <text:s text:c="2"/>stare s fac acelai lucru i cu uzina noastr.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Dac le d m<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>na... rosti Cowperwood. Ce, noi nu putem provoca <text:s text:c="2"/>explozii? Nu-i putem da n judecat<text:span text:style-name="T14">?</text:span> Mie mi plac procesele. i <text:s text:c="2"/>str<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>ngem zdravn cu ua, i pe urm o s ne roage n genunchi s le dm <text:s text:c="2"/>pace. Ochii lui strluceau de bucurie.</text:p>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2"><text:span text:style-name="Label">Capitolul </text:span><text:span text:style-name="Label"><text:span text:style-name="T15">IX</text:span></text:span><text:line-break/><text:span text:style-name="T14">D</text:span>rumul spre su<text:span text:style-name="T1">c</text:span>ces</text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">ntre timp poziia <text:span text:style-name="T14">lui</text:span> Aileen n societate se <text:span text:style-name="T14">m</text:span>bunti<text:span text:style-name="T14">se</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>ntruc<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>tva, deoarece dei era, clar c soii Cow<text:span text:style-name="T14">p</text:span>erwood nu puteau fi <text:s text:c="2"/>adoptai imediat  nici vorb de aa ceva  totui nu puteau fi nici <text:s text:c="2"/>i<text:span text:style-name="T14">g</text:span>norai. Un <text:span text:style-name="T14">fact</text:span>or care a contribui<text:span text:style-name="T14">t</text:span> la crearea unei atmo<text:span text:style-name="T14">sfere</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T14">arm</text:span>onioase <text:s text:c="2"/>i plcute era incontestabila <text:span text:style-name="T14">dragos</text:span>te <text:span text:style-name="T14">a l</text:span>ui Frank pentru soia lui. Dei <text:s text:c="2"/>mult lu<text:span text:style-name="T14">me</text:span> o <text:span text:style-name="T14">gse</text:span>a pe Aileen cam ndrznea i lipsit de rafi<text:span text:style-name="T14">nam</text:span>ent<text:span text:style-name="T14">,</text:span> i <text:s text:c="2"/>ziceau c ncput pe mna unui om cu <text:span text:style-name="T14">o per</text:span>sonalitate att de puternic se <text:s text:c="2"/>va putea <text:span text:style-name="T14">t</text:span>rans<text:span text:style-name="T14">forma.</text:span> Asta, de pild era prerea doamnei Addison <text:s text:c="2"/>i a doamnei Rambaud. M<text:span text:style-name="T14">cK</text:span>ibben i Lord cred<text:span text:style-name="T14">eau</text:span> i ei la fel. Dac <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood o iubea, aa cum d<text:span text:style-name="T14">dea el</text:span> impresia, atunci poate c va izbuti s o s<text:span text:style-name="T14">t</text:span>reco<text:span text:style-name="T14">are </text:span>n societate.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">n felul lui o iubea ntr-adevr. i aducea a<text:span text:style-name="T14">minte</text:span> de curajul ei din trecut c<text:span text:style-name="T14"></text:span>nd, tiind prea bine c <text:span text:style-name="T14">era </text:span>nsurat, c area un cmin, soie i copii i c fa<text:span text:style-name="T15">milia ei </text:span>s<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span> va opune, clcase peste orice conveniene <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>ociale i luptase cu inverunare pentru dragostea e<text:span text:style-name="T15">i</text:span> druit fr nici o <text:s text:c="2"/>precupeire. Frank fusese de <text:span text:style-name="T15">la</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nceput alesul inimii ei i acum simea <text:s text:c="2"/>c pentru ea prezena lui rmsese singurul lucru important din via. Chiar dac uneori l certa, se necje<text:span text:style-name="T15">a,</text:span> fcea mofturi, st<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>rnea discuii, <text:s/>era bnuitoare, <text:span text:style-name="T15">l</text:span> nvinuia c se poart curtenitor cu alte femei; <text:s text:c="2"/>micile lui abateri n-o suprau prea tare  sau ce<text:span text:style-name="T15">l</text:span> puin aa pretindea.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">E drept c nu-l prinsese niciodat c-ar inela-o. i declarase c era gata s treac<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span> orice cu vederea, i a<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>a i era, cu condiia s-o <text:s text:c="2"/>iubeasc.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Eti diabolic, i spunea, n glum. Te tiu eu, nu te vd eu cum i <text:s text:c="2"/>umbl ochii n toate prile! E drgu<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>stenodactilogra<text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>a care <text:s text:c="2"/>lucreaz la tine. Cred c ea e. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Nu fi proast, Aileen ! rspundea Frank, nu <text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>i vulgar. tii bine c <text:s text:c="2"/>nu snt <text:soft-page-break/>omul s se lege de o secretar i pe urm biroul nici nu e <text:s text:c="2"/>locul cel mai indicat pen<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>ru aa ceva.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Nu m prosti tu pe mine. Te cunose eu. Orice loc i convine.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Cowperwood ncepea s r<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>d, r<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>dea i ea, nu avea ncotro. Prea l <text:s text:c="2"/>iubea mult. Atacurile ei erau fr rutate. <text:span text:style-name="T15">l</text:span> iubea, iar el sf<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>rea <text:s text:c="2"/>ntotdeauna prin a o lua n brae, o sruta cu tandree i-i optea:</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Cine e fetia mea mare i frumoas <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>i ppua mea cu prul rou? E <text:s text:c="2"/>adevrat chiar aa de mult? Dac-i a<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>a, atu<text:span text:style-name="T15">nci srut-m!</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11">C erau am<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ndoi stp<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nii de o pute<text:span text:style-name="T15">rnic pasiune</text:span> nu <text:span text:style-name="T15">m</text:span>ai ncpea nici o <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ndoial. A<text:span text:style-name="T15">tta timp ct nu intervenea nimeni i nimic ntre ei, era greu ca Frank s conceap existena unei femei mai ncnttoare ca Aileen. Nu simea niciodat acel dezgust</text:span> plin de tristee care vine dup satisfacerea dorinei<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> Atracia ei<text:span text:style-name="T15"> f</text:span>izic, era indiscutabil. Vorbea cu ea ntotdeauna pe un ton sincer, <text:s text:c="2"/>tachin<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nd-o uneori, dar cu tandree i asta pentru c Alieen nu<text:span text:style-name="T15">-</text:span>i rnea. <text:span text:style-name="T15">S</text:span>ensibilitatea i bunul-gust cu banaliti v<text:span text:style-name="T15">u</text:span>lgare sau cu a<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>re <text:s text:c="2"/>de mironosi. Dei amoreza<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>i i dei cam prostu n anumite privine, <text:s/>suporta fr s <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>e supere critica lui sever. Putea un<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>ori n felul ei <text:s text:c="2"/>vag i st<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ngaci s sugereze la nevoie <text:span text:style-name="T15">so</text:span>luii utile pentru el. <text:s text:c="2"/>Preocuprile lor se concentrau a<text:span text:style-name="T15">sup</text:span>ra societii din Chicago, asupra <text:s text:c="2"/>casei pe ca<text:span text:style-name="T15">r</text:span>e o <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ncepuser i care socoteau c le va <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nlesni succesul <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>n lumea bun. Aileen gsea c nu existase nici<text:span text:style-name="T15">o</text:span>dut o femeie cu anse <text:s text:c="2"/>at<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t de mari de reuit ca ea. Aproape c nu-i venea s cread. Frank <text:s text:c="2"/>al ei era tare frumos, generos, ndrgostit. Nu a<text:span text:style-name="T15">v</text:span>ea nimic meschin. Ce <text:s text:c="2"/>conta dac din cnd n cnd se mai uita la c<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>te o femeie? Sufletete <text:s text:c="2"/>i rm<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nea credincios  i oricum, Aileen nu-l prinsese niciodat cu <text:s text:c="2"/>ceva serios. Habar nu avea ct de uor putea Frank s mint, ce bine <text:s text:c="2"/>tia s se apere. n tot cazul el o iubea la fel de mult ca nainte, <text:s text:c="2"/>iar micile lui escapade n-aveau de ce s-o ngrijoreze. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11">Frank <text:s text:c="2"/>investise vreo sut de mii de dolari n noua societate de gaz aerian <text:s text:c="2"/>i <text:soft-page-break/>era <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ncntat de perspectivele succesului ; privilegiile aveau <text:s text:c="2"/>valabilitate douzeci de ani. El va fi atunci un om de aproape <text:s text:c="2"/>aizeci de ani i ntre timp va fi cumprat vechile societi, sau va <text:s text:c="2"/>fi fuzionat cu ele, eau i va i vndut firma cu un mare profit.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Dezvoltarea oraului Chicago i venea n ajutor. Era hotr<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t s <text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nvesteasc p<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>n la treizeci de mii de dolari n tablouri  dac bi<text:span text:style-name="T15">n</text:span>eneles gs<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>a lucruri de valoare  i s comande un portret al lui <text:s text:c="2"/>Ail<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>en acum cnd era nc frumoas. Arta ncepea din nou s-l <text:s text:c="2"/>pasioneze. Addison avea patru sau cinci p<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nze remarcabile  un <text:s text:c="2"/>Rousseau, un Greuze, un Wouwerman i un Lawrence  <text:span text:style-name="T15">g</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T15">si</text:span>te <text:span text:style-name="T15">c</text:span>ine tie <text:s text:c="2"/>unde. Se pare c proprietarul unui <text:span text:style-name="T15">ho</text:span>te<text:span text:style-name="T15">l</text:span>, un oarecare Collard, <text:s text:c="2"/>manufacturier i agent <text:span text:style-name="T15">im</text:span>obiliar, fusese posesorul u<text:span text:style-name="T15">ne</text:span>i impresionante <text:s text:c="2"/>galerii <text:span text:style-name="T15">de t</text:span>a<text:span text:style-name="T15">b</text:span>louri. Addison povestea odat de un <text:span text:style-name="T15">d</text:span>omn Davis Trask, un ma<text:span text:style-name="T15">g</text:span>nat n domeniul fier<text:span text:style-name="T15">r</text:span>i<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>i ajunsese mare colec<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>io<text:span text:style-name="T15">n</text:span>ar, <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood au<text:span text:style-name="T15">zise c </text:span>muli <text:span text:style-name="T15">o</text:span>ameni, pe care i cuno<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>tea, din Chi<text:span text:style-name="T15">cago</text:span> ncepuser <text:s text:c="2"/>s colecioneze tablouri. Acum <text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>ra m<text:span text:style-name="T15">omentul</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span> nceap <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>i el.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">ndat dup ce <text:span text:style-name="T15">o</text:span>bi<text:span text:style-name="T15">n</text:span>u privilegiile, Cowp<text:span text:style-name="T15">erwood </text:span>l instal pe Sippens n <text:s text:c="2"/>biroul lui, lsndu-i pe moment ntreaga rspundere a noii <text:s text:c="2"/>socie<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>i<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">n r</text:span>e<text:span text:style-name="T15">g</text:span>iunea n care se construiau uzinele nchi<text:span text:style-name="T15">riase </text:span>nite birouri <text:s text:c="2"/>mai mici, unde lucrau o seam de <text:span text:style-name="T15">func</text:span>ionari. Vechile societi <text:s text:c="2"/>intentaser o <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>erie de <text:span text:style-name="T15">pro</text:span>cese de interdicie, de constr<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ngere i <text:s text:c="2"/>anulare, <text:span text:style-name="T15">dar</text:span> M<text:span text:style-name="T15">c</text:span>Kibben, S<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>imson i btr<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nul genera<text:span text:style-name="T15">l</text:span> Van Sic<text:span text:style-name="T15">k</text:span>l<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span> luptau m<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>n-n m<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>n, pe baricade, cu nver<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>u<text:span text:style-name="T15">n</text:span>are<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> Situaia nu era de lo<text:span text:style-name="T15">c</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>neplcut. Poziia real<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">a</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">l</text:span>ui Cowperwood continua s fie necunoscut la <text:s text:c="2"/>Chicago. Prea nc un personaj fr importan. Numele lui nu fusese <text:s text:c="2"/>asociat, nici mcar n treact, cu toat<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span> povestea asta. Cowperwood era <text:s text:c="2"/>chiar puin invidio<text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span> pe alii mereu ridicai n slvi. C<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nd oare va <text:s text:c="2"/>ncepe s strluceasc i steaua lui? Cur<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nd, cu siguran, i astfel, <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>n iunie, Cowperwood i Aileen <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>e mbarcar<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span> pentru prima lor cltorie <text:s text:c="2"/>n strintate, hotrii s profite ct mai mult de aceast vacan, <text:s/>n tihn, veseli, bogai, sntoi.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:soft-page-break/>Cltoria a fost minurat. Addison avu ama<text:span text:style-name="T15">b</text:span>ilitatea s telegrafi<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>ze <text:s text:c="2"/>la New York ca doamna Cowperwood s fie nt<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>mpinat cu flori pe <text:s text:c="2"/>vapor. M<text:span text:style-name="T15">c</text:span>Kib<text:span text:style-name="T15">b</text:span>en i oferi cri de cltorie, iar Cowperwood, ne<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>iind <text:s text:c="2"/>dac Aileen va primi sau nu flori, trimise i <text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>l <text:span text:style-name="T15">d</text:span>ou<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span> couri enorme, <text:s text:c="2"/>aa c mpreun cu ale lui Addison fceau trei, i care, cu crile d<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>vizit respective, i ateptau la intrarea pe puntea principal. C<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>iva<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>pasageri - de la masa cpitanului <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>e strduiau s<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span> intre n relaii cu <text:s text:c="2"/>soii Cowperwood. i invita si joace cri sau s asculte muzic. <text:s text:c="2"/>Cltoria pe mare <text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T15">fu </text:span>ns greu de suportat, iar Aileen nu se simi <text:s text:c="2"/>bine. i pentru c i se prea c arta ru, rmase mai tot timpul n <text:s text:c="2"/>cabin. Era distant cu lumea de a<text:span text:style-name="T15">fa</text:span>r de c<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>iva fa de care, <text:span text:style-name="T15">de altfel, avea</text:span> <text:s/>grij s spun nu<text:span text:style-name="T15">m</text:span>ai ce trebuie<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ncepe<text:span text:style-name="T15">a s </text:span>aib impresia c</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">este o <text:span text:style-name="T15">persoan </text:span>important<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">nainte de plecare cumprase aproape <text:span text:style-name="T15">to</text:span>t <text:span text:style-name="T15">ce se <text:s/></text:span>putea <text:span text:style-name="T15">g</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>i la ca<text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>a <text:s/>Donovan din Chica<text:span text:style-name="T15">g</text:span>o. V<text:span text:style-name="T15">a</text:span>lu<text:span text:style-name="T15">r</text:span>i de <text:span text:style-name="T15">lenjerie</text:span>, lenjerie, ne<text:span text:style-name="T15">g</text:span>lijeuri, r<text:span text:style-name="T15">o</text:span>chii <text:s text:c="2"/>de strad, rochii de sear i costu<text:span text:style-name="T15">m</text:span>e de clrie<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>Avea o pung pe care o purta <text:span text:style-name="T15">la e</text:span>a plin cu bijuterii <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>n <text:s text:c="2"/>valoare de treizeci de mii <text:s/>de dolari. Avea nenumrate perechi de pantofi, ciorapi, plrii i tot <text:s text:c="2"/>felul de accesorii  i asta l fcea pe Cowperwood s se simt m<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ndru <text:s text:c="2"/>de <text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>a, vz<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nd c<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t de mult i plcea viaa. Prima lui soie fusese <text:s text:c="2"/>palid i anemic, pe ct vreme Ail<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>en era plin de via. Fredona<text:span text:style-name="T15">,</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T15">glumea,</text:span> se <text:span text:style-name="T15">g</text:span>tea i se rs<text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>a<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:span text:style-name="T15">Exist</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T15">oameni spontani, care nu simt n</text:span>evoia s se analizeze. Ail<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>en avea doar o vag noiune <text:s text:c="2"/>despre pmnt i despre milenarul su trecut. Auzise i acceptase s <text:s text:c="2"/>cread c demult de tot existaser dinozauri i reptile zburtoare, dar <text:s text:c="2"/>asta n-o impresionase prea mult. Cineva spusese, cndva, sau nc se <text:s text:c="2"/>mai spunea, c ne tragem din maimu, ceea ce cra desigur absurd, dei <text:s text:c="2"/>la urma urmei putea fi chiar adevrat. Valurile verzi care se ridicau <text:s text:c="2"/>din ocean, ca nite coline amenintoare, i <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>t<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>rneau <text:span text:style-name="T15">o</text:span> spaim i o<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>senzaie de imensitate, dar nu imensitatea din inima unui poet. Vaporul <text:s text:c="2"/>prezenta <text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>oat sigurana, i spunea cpitanul  n uniforma lui <text:s text:c="2"/>albastr cu <text:soft-page-break/>nasturi de alam  care se strduia s-i plac. Firete, avea ncredere n el. Cowperwood era tot timpul l<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ng ea; contempla</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11">acest spectacol emoionant al vieii cu un ochi bnuitor, rece, dar <text:s text:c="2"/>nu ngrijorat, circumspect, dar fr s for<text:span text:style-name="T15">m</text:span>uleze vreo prere. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"><text:span text:style-name="T15">L</text:span>a Londra, scrisorile de recomandaie date de <text:span text:style-name="T15">Ad</text:span>dison le aduser mai multe <text:s text:c="2"/>invitaii la oper, la <text:span text:style-name="T15">mas,</text:span> ntr-o smbt i duminic la curse, i aa<text:span text:style-name="T15"> mai</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>departe. <text:span text:style-name="T15">T</text:span>rsuri, docare, cabriolete le stteau t<text:span text:style-name="T15">ot</text:span> timpul <text:span text:style-name="T15">la</text:span> <text:s/>dispoziie. Au mai fost invitai la o recere pe un vapora pe Tamisa. Gazdele i <text:span text:style-name="T15">co</text:span>nsiderau pe soii <text:span text:style-name="T15">Cowperwood </text:span>ca pe nite relaii <text:span text:style-name="T15">uti</text:span>le din <text:s text:c="2"/>lumea marii finane, ca pe nite invitai <text:span text:style-name="T15">pe ca</text:span>re i tratau cu mult <text:s text:c="2"/>politee, dar att. Ail<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>en<text:span text:style-name="T15"> era curioas s </text:span>tie tot. O intere<text:span text:style-name="T15">sau</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">servitorii </text:span><text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T15">englezi, [...] </text:span>obieciuri<text:span text:style-name="T15">le</text:span> i a<text:span text:style-name="T15">junse</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">la </text:span>con<text:span text:style-name="T15">cluzia c [...]</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"><text:span text:style-name="T15">- Ascult, Aileen, noi va trebui s trim nc muli ani la Chicago</text:span>, ncerca <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>-<text:span text:style-name="T15">i</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>expli<text:span text:style-name="T15">ce</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">Cowperwood. Nu te necji.</text:span> Nu-i dai <text:span text:style-name="T15">se</text:span>ama c <text:span text:style-name="T15">oamenilor stora nu</text:span> le plac americanii ? Dac am<text:span text:style-name="T15"> tri aici nu ne-ar accepta </text:span> n orice caz nu nc<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> Nu <text:span text:style-name="T15">sntem altceva dect</text:span> nite venetici n trecere, pe<text:span text:style-name="T15"> care i primesc n</text:span> mod amabil, i <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>puse C<text:span text:style-name="T15">o</text:span>wperwoo<text:span text:style-name="T15">d care nelegea </text:span>foarte bine situaia.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">D<text:span text:style-name="T15">e cnd prsise </text:span>America, Aileen fusese <text:span text:style-name="T15">continuu rsfat.</text:span> Schimba rochie dup <text:s text:c="2"/>rochie<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">Englezii se uitau </text:span>dup ea  n Hyde Park unde clre<text:span text:style-name="T15">a</text:span> i <text:span text:style-name="T15">se p</text:span>limba<text:span text:style-name="T15"> cu</text:span> trsura; la Claridges unde <text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>rses<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>r<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>; <text:span text:style-name="T15">n </text:span>Bond Street unde i fcea cumprturile. <text:span text:style-name="T15">Engle</text:span>zo<text:span text:style-name="T15">a</text:span>icele ins, majoritatea distante, ultraconser<text:span text:style-name="T15">vatoare</text:span>, care apreciau simplitatea, o priveau u<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>or nedumerite. <text:s text:c="2"/>Cowperwood observa totul, dar <text:span text:style-name="T15">nu</text:span> spunea nimic. O iubea pe Ail<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>en, era <text:s text:c="2"/>femeia <text:span text:style-name="T15">fru</text:span>moas care-i trebaia  cel puin deocamdat. Pe<text:span text:style-name="T15">n</text:span>tr<text:span text:style-name="T15">u</text:span> moment <text:s text:c="2"/>ar fi fost deajun<text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span> dac i-ar fi con<text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>olida<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span> situaia monden la Chicago.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11">Dup trei sptm<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ni de via intens, n care tim<text:span text:style-name="T15">p</text:span> Aileen profit de <text:s text:c="2"/>toate vechile i glorioasele splendori ale Angliei, ajunser la Paris<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"><text:span text:style-name="T15">C</text:span>apitala Franei trezi n ea un entuziasm de copil.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"><text:soft-page-break/><text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>tii ce, i spuse lui Cowperwood cu gravitate, chiar a doua zi dup <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>osirea la Paris, englezii habar m-au s se mbrace; la nceput am <text:s text:c="2"/>crezut c tiu, acum ns <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>mi dau seama c cei mai elegani nu fac <text:s text:c="2"/>al<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>ceva dec<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t s-i imite pe francezi. Uite, de pild brbaii pe care<text:span text:style-name="T15"> i</text:span>-am nt<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>lnit asear la <text:span text:style-name="T2">Ca</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T5">f</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2"> des Anglais</text:span>. N-am vzut nici mcar un <text:s text:c="2"/>englez<text:span text:style-name="T15"> care s</text:span> se poat compara cu ei. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"> Draga mea, tu ai gusturi <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T15">extravagante</text:span>, <text:span text:style-name="T15">repli </text:span>C<text:span text:style-name="T15">o</text:span>wperwood, privind-o cu admiraie <text:span text:style-name="T15">pe cnd i po</text:span>trivea cravata<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> Lumea <text:s text:c="2"/>elegant de ai<text:span text:style-name="T15">c</text:span>i <text:span text:style-name="T15">este aproape prea </text:span>elegant, snt ca nite pa<text:span text:style-name="T15">i</text:span>ae i n<text:span text:style-name="T15">u m-ar mira ca</text:span> pri<text:span text:style-name="T15">n</text:span>tre ace<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ti tineri <text:span text:style-name="T15">s fie unii care s poarte i corsete.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"> <text:s text:c="3"/>E<text:span text:style-name="T15">i i ce-i cu asta?</text:span> exclam Ai<text:span text:style-name="T15">leen. Mie mi </text:span>place. Dac tot vrei s <text:s text:c="2"/>fii elegant<text:span text:style-name="T15">,</text:span> de ce s n<text:span text:style-name="T15">u</text:span> fi fo<text:span text:style-name="T15">a</text:span>rte elegant? </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"> <text:span text:style-name="T15"><text:s/></text:span>tiu, vechea ta te<text:span text:style-name="T15">o</text:span>rie, dar <text:s text:c="2"/>totul tre<text:span text:style-name="T15">b</text:span>uie <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span> aibe o msur<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> Exist o limit p<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span> care nu <text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>rebuie s-o <text:s/>depesti. E bine s f<text:span text:style-name="T15">a</text:span>ci conce<text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>ii chiar dac<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span> di<text:span text:style-name="T15">n</text:span> pricina asta s-ar<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>p<text:span text:style-name="T15">ut</text:span>ea s pari mai puin <text:span text:style-name="T15">elegant </text:span>dec<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t vrei. Nu trebuie s st<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>rne<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ti <text:s text:c="2"/>invidia oamenilor cu care trieti chiar i <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>n sensul buna al <text:s text:c="2"/>c<text:span text:style-name="T15">u</text:span>v<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ntului. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"> tii ce, spuse Ail<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>en, oprindu-<text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>e i uit<text:span text:style-name="T15">n</text:span>d<text:span text:style-name="T15">u-se</text:span> la el. <text:s text:c="2"/>Mi-e t<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>am c ai <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nceput i tu <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span> calci pe urm<text:span text:style-name="T15">ele</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>ra<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ilor mei cu idei <text:s text:c="2"/>con<text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>ervatoare. . .</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11">Se apropie de <text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>l, <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>i potrivi cravata i-l m<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ng<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ie pe pr.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Pi, cineva trebuie s <text:span text:style-name="T15">fi</text:span>e i conservator, dac n-ar fi dec<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t pentru <text:s text:c="2"/>bunul mers al familiei, ncheie el, zmbind.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Se poate, dei nu snt sigur c <text:span text:style-name="T15">a</text:span>i s <text:span text:style-name="T15">fi</text:span>i tu acela.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Ce zi minunat. Uite ce frumoase snt statuile alea de marmor alb. <text:s text:c="2"/>Vrei s mergem la muzeul Cluny sau la Vers<text:span text:style-name="T15">a</text:span>illes<text:span text:style-name="T15">,</text:span> sau la Fontainebleau? <text:s text:c="2"/>Disear mergem s-o vedem pe Sarah Bernhardt la Comedia Francez.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Ail<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>en era foarte vesel. Ce minunat era s cltoreti n sf<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>rit <text:s text:c="2"/>ca o soie legitim<text:span text:style-name="T15">!</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11">Dragostea lui Cowperwood pentru art i via, <text:s text:c="2"/>hotr<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>rea lui de a profita <text:soft-page-break/>din belug de ele renscu puternic n timpul <text:s text:c="2"/>acestei cltorii. <text:s text:c="2"/>La Londra, Paris i Bruxelles cunoscu pe cei mai mari experi i <text:s text:c="2"/>negustori de tablouri. Gustul i competena lui n privina picturilor <text:s text:c="2"/>celebre ale vechilor <text:span text:style-name="T15">c</text:span>oli c<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ptar o form definitiv, la Londra, prin intermediul unui negustor care recunoscuse n el numaidec<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t <text:s text:c="2"/>un viitor client; fu invitat mpreun<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span> cu Aileen s vad diferite <text:s text:c="2"/>colecii <text:s/>particulare unde <text:span text:style-name="T15">i</text:span>ci-colo fcu cunotin cu pictori celebri, ca de <text:s text:c="2"/>pild Lord Leighton, Dante Gabriel Rossetti, sau Whistler, crora le <text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>u prezentat, n <text:s text:c="2"/>treact, drept un strin amator de pictur. Pentru ei Cow<text:span text:style-name="T15">p</text:span>erwood nu era <text:s text:c="2"/>altceva <text:s text:c="2"/>dect un om politicos, distant i conservator, <text:span text:style-name="T15">nce</text:span>pea s neleag <text:s text:c="2"/>sufletul emo<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>iv <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>i e<text:span text:style-name="T15">g</text:span>ocen<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>ri<text:span text:style-name="T15">c al</text:span> artistului, simi imediat c nu avea <text:s text:c="2"/>aproap<text:span text:style-name="T15">e nicio </text:span><text:s/>contigen cu asemenea oameni, n orice caz <text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T15">nu n</text:span> sensul unei prietenii posibile. Totui exista un <text:span text:style-name="T15">teren </text:span>comun de nelegere. <text:s text:c="2"/>N-ar fi putut niciodat s ad<text:span text:style-name="T15">mire</text:span> ceva n mod <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>ervil; nu putea fi dec<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t un <text:s text:c="2"/>Me<text:span text:style-name="T15">cena</text:span> princiar. i astfel cutreiera galeriile de pictur<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">i </text:span>se ntreba n <text:s text:c="2"/>ct timp i va putea realiza vis<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>le mree.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Cumpr la Londra un portret semnat de Rae<text:span text:style-name="T15">burn;</text:span> la Paris un peisaj de <text:s text:c="2"/>Millet, care reprezenta m<text:span text:style-name="T15">unca</text:span> c<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>mpului, un mic Jan Steen, o scen de <text:s text:c="2"/>rzboi Meissonier i o <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>cen romantic, de curte, de Isa<text:span text:style-name="T15">bey.</text:span> i astfel <text:span text:style-name="T15">i</text:span> <text:s/>se trezi din nou interesul pentru pic<text:span text:style-name="T15">tur</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>i se form nucleul viitoarei <text:s text:c="2"/>sale colecii care ave<text:span text:style-name="T15">a</text:span> s nsemne att de mul<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span> pentru el.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">La ntoarcerea din Europa, construcia sompt<text:span text:style-name="T15">u</text:span>oasei lor reedine din <text:s text:c="2"/>Chicago constituia interesul principal at<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t al vieii lui Aileen ct i a lui Frank<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> Datorit unor castele pe carele vizitaser n Frana, <text:s text:c="2"/>stilul sugerat de Lord i adoptat de el, dup e<text:span text:style-name="T15">x</text:span>perienele fcute n <text:s text:c="2"/>strintate,<text:span text:style-name="T15"> f</text:span>u definitiv acceptat<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> Domnul Lord socotea c locuina <text:s text:c="2"/>lor nu va fi complet gata dec<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t peste un an sau poate un an i jumtate, dar, evident, timpul aici nu prea avea mare importan. P<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>n atunci puteau s-<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>i ntreasc poziia n societate i s-i <text:s text:c="2"/>pregteasc debutul n lumea bun din Chicago.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Existau, n vremea aceea, mai multe categorii de oameni la Chicago  <text:s text:c="2"/>unii <text:soft-page-break/>care din srcia cea mai neagr se mbogiser peste noapte, i <text:s text:c="2"/>care nu puteau uita lesne bisericua i convenienele sociale ale <text:s text:c="2"/>statului lor; alii, motenitori de averi mari, sau venii din<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>Est unde <text:s/>bogia nu era a<text:span text:style-name="T15">tt</text:span> de recent, puteau nelege mai bine regulile jocului, i, n sf<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>rit, cei nscui n bogie, sensibili la tendina <text:s text:c="2"/>ctre o via american mai rafinat, ncepeau s fie minai de dorina <text:s text:c="2"/>de a face parte din ea  acetia din urm alctuind noua, generaie.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Tineretul visa serate dansante la Kinsley, chermese <text:s text:c="2"/>i divertismente estivale n stil euro<text:span text:style-name="T15">pean. Dar deoc</text:span>amdat totul era doar un proiect. Prima <text:span text:style-name="T15">categorie,</text:span> dei cea mai stupid, <text:s text:c="2"/>nite vite nclate, contin<text:span text:style-name="T15">ua</text:span> s rmn n frunte, fiind cea mai <text:s text:c="2"/>bogat, banii fiind nc criteriul cel mai important. Petrecerile date <text:s/>de ei erau de o mare plictiseal; aceleasi i aceleai recepii din <text:s text:c="2"/>timpul sptminii, acelea<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>i vizite de duminic dup mas din Squ<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>edunk <text:s text:c="2"/>i Hohokus la puterea N. Singurul scop pe care l urmreau era s vad <text:s text:c="2"/>i s fie vzui. Orice tentativ de originalitate at<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t n felu<text:span text:style-name="T15">l</text:span> de a <text:s text:c="2"/>gndi ct i n purtri era, cu desv<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>rire exclus. n fond se cerea <text:s text:c="2"/>doar un mod stereotip de a g<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ndi i de a te purta  culmea banalitii. <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T15">I</text:span>de<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>a de a introduce n mijlocul lor o femeie de teatru  cum se <text:s text:c="2"/>obinuia n Est sau la Londra  nici nu le-ar fi trecut prin cap!<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>Chiar i un cntre sau un pictor ar <text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>i fost privit chiori. <text:span text:style-name="T15">E</text:span>ra <text:s text:c="2"/>foarte uor s depeti msura<text:span text:style-name="T15">!</text:span> Dac ns un prin european s-ar fi <text:s text:c="2"/>rtcit la Chicago (lucru care nu s-a nt<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>mplat de altfel niciodat) <text:s text:c="2"/>sau dac vreun magnat din Est ar fi rmas la Chicago ntr<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span> dou <text:s text:c="2"/>trenuri, atunci elita oraului s-ar <text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>i dat peste cap s-i <text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>ac pe <text:s text:c="2"/>plac.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Cowperwood a simit toate lucrurile astea din primul moment. i <text:s text:c="2"/>nchipuise ns, c av<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nd bani i putere, el, mpreun, cu Aileen i <text:s text:c="2"/>cu splendida lor cas vor constitui fermentul care va nsuflei lumea <text:s text:c="2"/>asta lipsit de via. Din nefericire ns, Aileen era prea ostentativ <text:s text:c="2"/>dornic de ocaziile care puteau s fac din ea favorita bunei societi, sau mcar s-o <text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>ac s <text:s text:c="2"/>fie acceptat<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> Ca orice om primitiv, care era nepregtit s, se apere i se afla la <text:soft-page-break/>cheremul forelor capricioase ale naturii, perspectiva <text:s text:c="2"/>unui eec o fcea aproape s tremure. <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>i d<text:span text:style-name="T15">duse</text:span> seama, de la nceput <text:s text:c="2"/>de nepotrivirea ei, ca, fire, cu un anumit gen de femeie monden<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>Soia, lui Anson <text:s text:c="2"/>Merril<text:span text:style-name="T15">l</text:span>, magnatul manu<text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>acturii, pe care o vzuse odat ntr-un magazi<text:span text:style-name="T15">n</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>din centru, i se p<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ru mult <text:s text:c="2"/>prea distant. Doamna Merrili era o persoan <text:span text:style-name="T15">di</text:span>stins i de o <text:s text:c="2"/>cultur aleas. <text:span text:style-name="T15">I</text:span> se prea c nimeni<text:span text:style-name="T15"> la Chicago </text:span>nu putea fi la nlimea ei. Fusese crescut la Boston <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>i era destul de familiarizat<text:span text:style-name="T15"> cu</text:span> buna societate londonez, <text:s/>pe care o frecve<text:span text:style-name="T15">ntase</text:span> deseori. Pentru ea, Chicago nu era altceva <text:span text:style-name="T15">dect un ora </text:span><text:s text:c="3"/>comercial sordid. Ar fi preferat de <text:span text:style-name="T15">m</text:span>ii <text:span text:style-name="T15">de </text:span>ori s triasc la New York <text:s/>sau la Washi<text:span text:style-name="T15">ngton</text:span> dar era nevoit s rmin aici. De ace<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>a a<text:span text:style-name="T15">rbora</text:span> ntotdeauna un <text:s/>aer superior fa de toi cei pe accepta s-i frecventeze, art<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nd, <text:s text:c="2"/>cu o <text:span text:style-name="T15">nclinare</text:span> dispreuitoare a capului, cu o privire obosit<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span> cu o micare <text:s text:c="2"/>a spr<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ncenelor arcuite, c<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t de mult <text:span text:style-name="T15">o </text:span>plictisea totul.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">O anume doamn Henry Huddlestone i-o art<text:span text:style-name="T15">ase</text:span> pe doamna Merrill lui Aileen.<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>Doamna Huddl<text:span text:style-name="T15">es</text:span>tone era nevasta fabricantului de spun care loc<text:span text:style-name="T15">uia</text:span> aproape <text:s text:c="2"/>de actuala reedin a soilor Cowperwood, i nici ei nu fceau parte <text:s text:c="2"/>din c<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>a mai bun societate<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> Auzise c soii Cowperwood erau oameni <text:s/>bogai, pri<text:span text:style-name="T15">et</text:span>e<text:span text:style-name="T15">n</text:span>i cu soii Addison, c intenionau s-i cons<text:span text:style-name="T15">truiasc </text:span>o somptuoas locuin care va costa dou sute de mii de dolari <text:s text:c="2"/>(preul crete totdeanna cnd <text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span> vorba de o cas n<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>construcie). Asta era <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>uficien<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span> pentru doamna Huddlestone. Depuse cri de vizit la <text:s text:c="2"/>familia Cowperwood ca vecin, iar Aileen, dornic s-i ctige simpatii, i rspunse. Doamna Huddlestone era o femeie mic de <text:s text:c="2"/>statur, nu prea ar<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>toas, deteapt n sensul monden al cuvntului <text:s text:c="2"/>i cu un remarcabil sim practic.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Apropo de doamna Merril<text:span text:style-name="T15">l</text:span>, spuse doamna Huddlestone n ziua aceea, <text:s text:c="2"/>uite-o colo  l<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ng <text:span text:style-name="T15">r</text:span>aionul de confecii. Are totdeauna un <text:span text:style-name="T2">face-</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T5"></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">-main</text:span> pe care-l ine ca acum.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Aileen se ntoarse i examin critic o femeie brun, nalt i zvelt, <text:s text:c="2"/>aparin<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nd n mod evident societii b<text:span text:style-name="T15">u</text:span>ne din Vest, foarte distant, <text:soft-page-break/>dispreuitoare i ncrezut. |</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> N-o cunoti? ntreb Aileen surprins, urmrind-o din ochi pe <text:s text:c="2"/>doamna Merrill, n voie.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Nu, se scuz doamna Huddlestone. Ei locuies<text:span text:style-name="T15">c</text:span> n districtul nordic i <text:s text:c="2"/>la noi n ora cercurile nu se prea ameatec intre ele<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">De fapt familiile importante aveau tocmai privilegiul s nu in <text:s text:c="2"/>seama de mprirea arbitrar pe dis<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>ricte i puteau s-i aleag <text:s text:c="2"/>prieteni din oricare <text:span text:style-name="T15">d</text:span>in cele trei districte ale oraului.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Aha exclam Aileen, nepstoare. Era ns vexat c doamna <text:s text:c="2"/>Huddlestone gsea necesar s-o indice pe doamna Merril<text:span text:style-name="T15">l</text:span> drept o <text:s text:c="2"/>persoan superioar lor.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> tii, cred c i face puin spr<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ncenele, insinu doamna <text:s/>Huddlestone, nu fr invidie. Lumea pretinde c<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span> brbatul ei nu e de <text:s text:c="2"/>o fidelitate exemplar. Exist o oarecare doamn Gladdens, o vecin a lor, care se pare c-l intereseaz foarte mult.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"> <text:span text:style-name="T15">Ooo</text:span>! fcu Aileen, cu pruden. Din cauza aventurii <text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>i din <text:s text:c="2"/>Philadelphia hotr<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>se s fie circumspect, i s se abin de la <text:s text:c="2"/>b<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>rfeli. Sgeile de acest fel puteau at<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t de uor fi ndreptate spre <text:s text:c="2"/>ea <text:span text:style-name="T15">!</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Cercul ei ns este totui cel mai select din ora, recunoscu <text:s text:c="2"/>interlocutoarea lui Aileen.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Dup care ambiia lui Aileen fu s-o frecventeze pe doamna Anson Merrill <text:s text:c="2"/>i s fie acceptat de ea fr, rezerve. Nu tia, dei ar fi putut s <text:s text:c="2"/>bnuiasc, c acest ideal nu se va realiza niciodat.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Mai erau ns i alte persoane care se prezentaser la prima reedin <text:s text:c="2"/>a soilor Cowperwood, sau <text:span text:style-name="T15">cu <text:s/></text:span>care acetia din urm intraser n <text:s text:c="2"/>relaii. De pild soii Sunderland Sled<text:span text:style-name="T15">d</text:span>, domnul Sledd fiind director <text:s text:c="2"/>general de micare la una din cile ferate din sud-vest, cu capt de <text:s text:c="2"/>linie la Chicago  om cultivat i de gust, cu ceva avere, iar nevasta <text:s text:c="2"/>lui o femeie ambiioas i <text:soft-page-break/>neinteresant. Mai erau i soii Walter <text:s text:c="2"/>Rysam Cotton, el <text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>iind un angrosist de cafea, dar mai ales cronicarul <text:s text:c="2"/>monden al localitii; soia lui fcuse universi<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>atea din Vassar. <text:s text:c="2"/>Apoi, soii Norrie Simms; Simms era secretarul i tezaurierul casei de <text:s text:c="2"/>economii i depuneri <text:span text:style-name="T2">Douglas</text:span> i avea mare putere ntr-un anumit grup de <text:s text:c="2"/>financiari, independent de cel reprezentat de Addison i Rambaud. i <text:s text:c="2"/>alii, printre care soii Stanislau Hoecksema, bl<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nar bogat; soii <text:s text:c="2"/>Duane Kingsland, negustor angrosist de fin<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>; <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>oii Webster Israels, <text:s text:c="2"/>fabricant <text:s text:c="2"/><text:span text:style-name="T15">d</text:span>e conserve; <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>oii Brad<text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>ord Canda, bijutier. Toi aceti oameni aveau o <text:s text:c="2"/>oarecare poziie <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>ocial<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> Fiecare locuia n case mari, triau din <text:s text:c="2"/>veni<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>uri grase i prin urmare se bucurau de consideraia <text:s text:c="2"/>concetenilor lor. Diferena dintre Aileen i majoritatea celorlalte femei era ca diferena dintre realitate i iluzie. Dar aici <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>e <text:s text:c="2"/>cuvine o explicaie. Pentru a cunoate ntr-adevr mentalitatea femeii <text:s text:c="2"/>americane de la s<text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>ritul secolului al XIX-lea, ar trebui s ne<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>ntoarcera la evul mediu cnd <text:span text:style-name="T15">b</text:span>iserica era nfloritoare i cnd poetul z<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>los i insuficien<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span> informat de realitile vieii mpodobea femeia cu <text:s text:c="2"/>un nimb mistic. De atunci fetele ca i femeile m<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ritate au fost <text:s text:c="2"/>nvate s cread c femeia era, fcut dintr-o argil superioar <text:s text:c="2"/>celei din care erau fcui brbaii, i c ele snt menite s-i ridice <text:s text:c="2"/>moralmente i c favorurile pe care le acordau brbailor erau daruri <text:s text:c="2"/>de nepreuit. Aceast aureol trandafirie <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>i romanioas, neavnd nimic <text:s text:c="2"/>comun cu morala individualist, crease totui la femei o atitudine de <text:s text:c="2"/>superioritate fa de brbat i chiar fa de alte temei. La Chicago, <text:s text:c="2"/>n atmosfera n care <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>e trezise <text:span text:style-name="T15">A</text:span>ileen, exista n parte aceast iluzie. <text:s text:c="2"/>Doamnele crora le fusese prezentat aparineau acestei luni pline de<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>iluzii. Ele se credeau fiine desv<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>rite, ca din romane i din arta <text:s text:c="2"/>religioas. Soii for trebuiau s aib o purtare exemplar, demn de <text:s text:c="2"/>concepia ideal a soilor lor, iar reputaia celorlalte femei <text:s text:c="2"/>trebuia s fie ne<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ntinat, Aileen, cu firea ei primitiv i pasionat, <text:s text:c="2"/>ar fi r<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>s de toate astea, dac bineneles le-ar fi neles. Cum ns <text:s text:c="2"/>nu le putea <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nelege, n prezena anumitor persoane devenea timid i <text:s text:c="2"/>nesigur de ea. Un exemplu n acest sens era doamna Norris Bimms, unul <text:s text:c="2"/>din sateliii doa<text:span text:style-name="T15">m</text:span>nei Anson Merrill<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:soft-page-break/>O invitaie la ceai, la dejun, la cin, sau s fie mcar <text:s text:c="2"/>nsoit n ora de doamna Merrill, constituia pentru doamna Simms cea mai mare <text:span text:style-name="T15">fericire</text:span>. Adora <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span> repete <text:span text:style-name="T15">spiritele idolului ei, s informeze lumea despre nemaipomenita sa cultur, i s povesteasc cum oamenii refuzau s cread c e nevasta lui Anson </text:span>Merrill, dei doamna Merrill nu se sfia s<text:span text:style-name="T15">-</text:span>o spun. Aceti <text:s/>cas<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>ani btrni, st<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>lpii lumii bune, din Chicago, i aveau desigur <text:s text:c="2"/>originea n Egipt i Chaldea. Doamna Simms era o femeie banal, f<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>r<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span> o <text:s text:c="2"/>personalitate bine definit, deteapt, fr<text:span text:style-name="T15">u</text:span>muic, nu lipsit de gust, dar o arivist. Fetiele <text:s text:c="2"/>Simms nvaser toate manierele i comportarea din societatea bun a <text:s text:c="2"/>timpului  s se fan<text:span text:style-name="T15">doseas</text:span>c, s<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span> z<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>mbeasc afectat, s fac reverene i <text:s text:c="2"/>a<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>a mai departe, spre marea des<text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>tare a prinilor. D<text:span text:style-name="T15">d</text:span>aca lor purta <text:s text:c="2"/>uniform, iar guvernanta era o adevrat martir. Doamna Simms era <text:s text:c="2"/>nfumurat, nu se <text:span text:style-name="T15">u</text:span>ita dec<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t la cei mai bine dec<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t ea i avea un <text:s text:c="2"/>dispre plin de condescenden pentru lumea mediocr <text:s text:c="2"/>n care era silil s triasc.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">La prima mas la care i invitase pe soii Cowperwood, doamna Simms <text:s text:c="2"/>cutase s afle ceva din trecutul lui Aileen la Philadelphia; o <text:s text:c="2"/>ntreb dac <text:s text:c="2"/>cunoate familiile Arthur Leigh, Trevor Drake, Martyn Walker sau pe <text:s text:c="2"/>Roberta Willing. Doam<text:span text:style-name="T15">n</text:span>a Simms personal nu cunotea, pe nici una din <text:s text:c="2"/>ele, o auzise doar pe doamna Merrill pomenindu-le, i asta deci i se <text:s text:c="2"/>prea o excelent garanie. Aileen, hotr<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t s se apere, gata s mint <text:s text:c="2"/>fr ezitare ca s<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>c<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>tige pa<text:span text:style-name="T15">r</text:span>tida, afirm c le cunoscuse, dei n realitate abia le vzuse i asta nainte ca lumea din Philadelphia s discute legtura ei cu Cowperwood. Afirmaia lui Aileen i fcu <text:s text:c="2"/>plcere doamnei Simms.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"> Am s-i spun lui Nellie, zise ea, referindu-se cu famil<text:span text:style-name="T15">i</text:span>a<text:span text:style-name="T15">r</text:span>itate la doamna Merrill.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Aileen se temea c dac investigaiile vor continua, va afla toat <text:s text:c="2"/>lumea c nainte de a <text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>i nevasta <text:span text:style-name="T15">l</text:span>ui Cowperwood trise cu el, c sta <text:s text:c="2"/>fusese motivul eformulat al divorului lui i c Frank Cowperwood <text:span text:style-name="T15">st</text:span>tuse <text:s text:c="2"/>la nchisoare. <text:soft-page-break/>Singura lor salvare era averea i frumuseea ei. Dar va <text:s text:c="2"/>fi oare su<text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>icient<text:span text:style-name="T15">?</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"><text:span text:style-name="T15">ntr-o</text:span> sear au fost invitai la mas la familia <text:span text:style-name="T15">[...]</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">K</text:span>ingsland, unde doamna <text:s text:c="2"/>Brad<text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>o<text:span text:style-name="T15">rd</text:span> Canda <text:span text:style-name="T15">ntr</text:span>eb, pe<text:span text:style-name="T15"> un</text:span> ton care-i pru lui Aileen foarte <text:span text:style-name="T15">semnificativ</text:span>, <text:s text:c="2"/>dac o cunoscuse la Philadelphia pe prietena ei, doamna Schu<text:span text:style-name="T15">yler Evans. ntrebarea</text:span> o sperie pe <text:span text:style-name="T15">Aileen.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"> Nu cre<text:span text:style-name="T15">zi</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">c </text:span>au aflat ce-i cu <text:s text:c="2"/>noi? M<text:span text:style-name="T15">car unii</text:span> dintre ei? <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>l ntreb pe Cowperwood n <text:span text:style-name="T15">drum <text:s/>spre </text:span>cas. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"> <text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T15">S-ar</text:span> putea, rspunse Cowperwood<text:span text:style-name="T15">, dus pe</text:span> g<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nduri, totui nu sn<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span> sigur. Eu n loc<text:span text:style-name="T15">ul tu nu</text:span> m-a frm<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nta. Dac pari ngrijorat, abia atu<text:span text:style-name="T15">nci</text:span> au s simt c e <text:s text:c="2"/>ceva. N-am fcut nici un mister din faptul c am stat la nchisoare la <text:s text:c="2"/>Philadelphia i nici de acum nainte n-am s fac. A fost o nedreptate, m-au bgat acolo fr nici un drept. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"> tiu, dragul meu, i s-ar <text:s text:c="2"/>putea s n-aib nici o importan dac au aflat. Nu vd de ce ar avea. <text:s text:c="2"/>C<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t despre noi doi, nu sntem singurii care s fi avut ncurcturi <text:s text:c="2"/>familiale.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"> Singurul lucru care conteaz e dac ne accept sau nu<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>Dac nu le place, foarte bine. N-avem <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ncotro<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> Deocamdat s isprvim <text:s text:c="2"/>cas i apoi s le oferim un prilej de a se purta cum se cuvine. Dac <text:s text:c="2"/>nu, mai snt i alte orae unde ne putem duce. Cu bani faci orice n <text:s text:c="2"/>New York  asta tiu precis. Acolo putem s ne construim un adevrat <text:s text:c="2"/>palat i s fim primii n societate i tratai de la egal la egal  <text:s text:c="2"/>dac, bineneles, avem destui bani <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>i eu o s am bani berechet, <text:s text:c="2"/>adaug el dup ce chibzui o clip. N-ai grij, cu sau fr voia lor, am <text:s text:c="2"/>s <text:span text:style-name="T15">c</text:span>tig aici milioane i apoi  ei, apoi vedem noi ce-o s mai fie. <text:s text:c="2"/>Fii linitit<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> Nu tiu dac exist pe lumea a<text:span text:style-name="T15">sta</text:span> vreun necaz pe care s <text:s text:c="2"/>nu-l poi nltura cu <text:span text:style-name="T15">b</text:span>ani. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11">Cu dinii ncle<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>ai, cp<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>ase <text:s text:c="2"/>expresia hotr<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t a unui om periculos, gata de lupt. Apoi lu<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>m<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>na lui <text:s text:c="2"/>Aileen i o str<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>n<text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>e cu bl<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ndee. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"> Fii linitit, mai repet. <text:s text:c="2"/>Chicago nu este <text:span text:style-name="T15">sin</text:span>gurul ora din lume<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> n zece <text:soft-page-break/>ani o s fim cu si<text:span text:style-name="T15">guran</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>bogai. Te rog s ai ncredere<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> Totul va merge strun<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">S</text:span>nt sigur.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Trecnd pe Michigan Avenue cu trsur, <text:span text:style-name="T15">Aileen </text:span>se uita la laminile i la <text:s text:c="2"/>casele cu<text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>unda<text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>e n <text:span text:style-name="T15">tcere.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Lmpile albe luceau <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>n ntuneric i pe <text:span text:style-name="T15">msur ce se </text:span>ndeprtau se fceau tot mai <text:s text:c="2"/>mici, aprinse. Era noapte, rcoare i pl<text:span text:style-name="T15">cut. Oh, de s-ar</text:span> putea ca banii lui Frank <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span> <text:s text:c="2"/>le aduc <text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T15">poziia n socie</text:span>tate pe care o dorea, i muli pri<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span>teni; <text:span text:style-name="T15">oh, </text:span>ce <text:span text:style-name="T15">n-ar </text:span>da! Nu-i prea <text:s text:c="2"/>ddea seama c izb<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nd<text:span text:style-name="T15">a n aceast</text:span> lupt depinde de propria ei personali<text:span text:style-name="T15">tate, de faptul</text:span> c are <text:s text:c="2"/>sau nu personalitate.</text:p>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2"><text:span text:style-name="Label">Capitolul X</text:span><text:line-break/>O prim ncercare</text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Inaugurarea casei din Michigan Avenue avu loc trziu, <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>n noiembrie, n<text:line-break/>toamna anului 1878, aproape doi ani dup stabilirea lui Aileen i Frank<text:line-break/>la C<text:span text:style-name="T15">hi</text:span>cago. Datorit cunotinelor fcute la curse, la di<text:span text:style-name="T15">f</text:span>erite<text:line-break/>mese, la ceaiuri i la recepiile date de <text:span text:style-name="T2">Clubul Union</text:span> i de <text:span text:style-name="T2">Clubul<text:line-break/>Calumet</text:span> (unde Cowperwood usese cooptat ca membru datorit proteciei<text:line-break/>lui Addison) i a oamenilor<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>inf<text:span text:style-name="T15">l</text:span>uen<text:span text:style-name="T15">a</text:span>i de M<text:span text:style-name="T15">c</text:span>Kibben i de Lord, reuir<text:line-break/>s trimit trei sute de invitaii din care dou sute cincizeci fur<text:line-break/>acceptate. P<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>n atunci, graie discreiei cu care-i conducea<text:line-break/>afacerile, nu auzise comentarii n legtur cu el i nici nu atrsese<text:line-break/>atenia privitor la trecutul lui din Philadelphia. Era bogat, amabil,<text:line-break/>cu mult farmec i personalitate<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> Oamenii de afaceri din Chicago, cei pe<text:line-break/>care i frecventa, l gseau fascinant; i foarte detept. Frumuseea i graia lui Aileen i confereau o valoare personal, dei nu<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>erau nc primii n societatea cea mai nalt<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11">Este uimitor ce impresie poate produce un om<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>pe care societtea nu l-a definit nc, dac omul procedeaz, cu tact i discernmnt. Aprea, pe atunci n Chicago o<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>publicaie monden sptm<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nal, de oarecare importan i pe care<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>Cowperwood mpreun cu M<text:span text:style-name="T15">c</text:span>Kibben o aveau la dispoziie. n general nu<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>poi face mare lucru ntr-o mprejurare dac<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>elul pentru care lupi nu e perfect serios; dar dac<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>exist, c<text:span text:style-name="T15">a</text:span> n cazul de fa, mcar <text:span text:style-name="T15">o umbr</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">de</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">res</text:span>pecta<text:span text:style-name="T15">b</text:span>ilitate, cnd e vorba de<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>o ma<text:span text:style-name="T15">re avere</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">i de un om</text:span> cu o personalitate <text:span text:style-name="T15">c</text:span>ov<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>ritoare<text:span text:style-name="T15">, totul devine</text:span> posibil. Kent<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>M<text:span text:style-name="T15">c</text:span>Kibben l cunotea <text:span text:style-name="T15">b</text:span>ine <text:span text:style-name="T15">pe Horton</text:span> Bi<text:span text:style-name="T15">g</text:span>gers, redactorul-el al revistei, n<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>v<text:span text:style-name="T15">rst de vreo</text:span> patruzeci i <text:span text:style-name="T15">cinci</text:span> de ani, cu <text:span text:style-name="T15">p</text:span>rul cru<text:span text:style-name="T15">nt</text:span>, <text:span text:style-name="T15">un om </text:span>trist, deprimat<text:span text:style-name="T15"> i</text:span> dezamgit de via<text:span text:style-name="T15">  avea, n </text:span><text:s/>nfiare, ceva de burete s<text:span text:style-name="T15">a</text:span>u de molusc<text:span text:style-name="T15">.</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">Aparenta lui </text:span>bun dispoziie <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>i interesul pentru o<text:span text:style-name="T15">ameni nu </text:span>se trezeau n el<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>dec<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>n cazuri <text:soft-page-break/>de for <text:span text:style-name="T15">major. Pe </text:span>vremea aceea, redactorul monden<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>f<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>cea <text:span text:style-name="T15">parte din</text:span> lumea bun  <text:span text:style-name="T2">de facto </text:span> i era tratat ma<text:span text:style-name="T15">i mult ca </text:span>musafir dec<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>t<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>ca simplu gazetar, dei chiar atunci exista tendina de a se cam<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>ntoarce <text:span text:style-name="T15">spatele</text:span> presei. M<text:span text:style-name="T15">cK</text:span>ibben, care lucra pentru Cowper<text:span text:style-name="T15">wood</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T15">i</text:span> inea la<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>el, i spuse ntr-o zi lui Bigger<text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>: </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"><text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>i cunoti pe soii Cowperwood,<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>nu-i aa<text:span text:style-name="T15">?</text:span> </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"> Nu, rspunse Biggers, care se lipise <text:span text:style-name="T15">n</text:span>u<text:span text:style-name="T15">m</text:span>ai d<text:span text:style-name="T15">e</text:span> cercurile<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>selecte ale oraului. Cine mai s<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nt<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>i <text:span text:style-name="T15">t</text:span>ia<text:span text:style-name="T15">?</text:span> </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P12"> Cowperwood este un<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>bancher din La Sa<text:span text:style-name="T15">lle</text:span> Street. E din Philadelphia. Doam<text:span text:style-name="T15">n</text:span>a Cowperwoo<text:span text:style-name="T15">d</text:span> este<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>o femeie splendid, t<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nr i aa mai departe. <text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>i construise o cas<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>aici, la Chicago, pe Michi<text:span text:style-name="T16">g</text:span>an Avenue. Ar trebui s-i cunoti. Cred c<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>n cur<text:span text:style-name="T15"></text:span>nd au s fac parte din lumea bun. Soii Addison <text:span text:style-name="T15">s</text:span>-au i<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>mprietenit cu ei. Dac te-ai arta amabil acum, cred c i-ar folosi<text:span text:style-name="T15"> </text:span>mai trziu. Cowperwood e un om bun i generos. </text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P12">Biggers ciuli<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>urechile. Meseria lu<text:span text:style-name="T16">i </text:span>de <text:span text:style-name="T16">gazetar </text:span>monden nu era prea bine pltit i ocaziile<text:span text:style-name="T16"> n care </text:span>putea s mai ctige c<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>te ceva pe de ltu<text:span text:style-name="T16">ri</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T16">se iveau r</text:span>ar. Cei<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span><text:s/>ce doreau s fac<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>parte din lu<text:span text:style-name="T16">mea bun,</text:span> cei care abia ncepuser s fie primii n <text:span text:style-name="T16">cercurile </text:span>selecte i<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>contau pe aprecieri amabile <text:span text:style-name="T16">din partea</text:span> redactorului-ef, trebuiau s-i<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>sub<text:span text:style-name="T16">v</text:span>enion<text:span text:style-name="T16">eze</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T16">cu g</text:span>e<text:span text:style-name="T16">ne</text:span>rozitate revista. Scurt timp dup ce <text:span text:style-name="T16">avusese loc </text:span>aceast<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>conversaie, Cowperwood primi <text:span text:style-name="T16">un formular </text:span>pentru un abonament din partea <text:span text:style-name="T16">administraiei gazetei </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">Saturday Review</text:span>. Bancherul <text:span text:style-name="T16">trimise un cec de o </text:span>sut de dolari adresa<text:span text:style-name="T16">t</text:span> person<text:span text:style-name="T16">al domnului</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T16">Horton </text:span>Biggers; dup<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>care c<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>teva<text:span text:style-name="T16"> persoane, nu din cele </text:span>mai imporianie, observar c dup ce <text:span text:style-name="T16">soii Cow</text:span>perwood luau masa la ei numai atu<text:span text:style-name="T16">nci, </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T6">Saturday Review</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T16"> relata acest eveniment monden. Soii Cowperwood preau s fie bine vzui, dar ntrebarea era de ce.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Din pcate publicitatea sau succesul <text:span text:style-name="T16">monden, </text:span>chiar moderat, ca tot ce<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>s<text:span text:style-name="T16">tr</text:span>lu<text:span text:style-name="T16">c</text:span>e<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>te isc <text:span text:style-name="T16">brfeli.</text:span> C<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>nd cineva ncepe s aib succes i se ridic<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>deasupra mulimii, amatorii de cancanuri stau la p<text:span text:style-name="T16">nd</text:span> i se<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>ntreab: cine e, <text:soft-page-break/>ce face i de ce reu<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>e<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>te? Entuziasmul lui Aileen i<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>geniul fi<text:span text:style-name="T16">n</text:span>anciar al lui Cowperwood i ndemnau s fac din recepia l<text:span text:style-name="T16">o</text:span>r<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>de inaugurare a noii case un eveniment monden cu totul deosebit, care,<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>dat fiind mprejurrile, era o ten<text:span text:style-name="T16">t</text:span>ativ periculoas. Chicago se<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>dezvolta totui extrem de ncet din punct de vedere monden, <text:span text:style-name="T16">oame</text:span>nii<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>erau foarte circumspeci, cu reacii, dup cum am mai spus, flegmatice,<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>stupide. O recepie formidabil, orbitoare ca un foc de artificii,<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>putea reui dar putea,<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>s nsemne i un fiasco. Membrii cei mai<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>circumspeci ai societii din Chicago, chiar dac nu vor fi prezeni<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>la recepie, vor auzi comentariile i vor aduce ultimele critici,<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>dict<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>nd atitudi<text:span text:style-name="T16">n</text:span>ea de<text:span text:style-name="T16">f</text:span>initiv care trebuia adoptat fa de soii Cowperwoo<text:span text:style-name="T16">d</text:span>.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:span text:style-name="T16">I</text:span>nvitaiile fur fcute peniru ora pa<text:span text:style-name="T16">tr</text:span>u i musafirii rmaser pn la<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>ase i jumtate, dup care, la nou, urm o serat dansant cu o<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>celebr orches<text:span text:style-name="T16">tr</text:span> local, de coarde, un program muzical cu arti<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>ti<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>de mare renume i apoi un supeu nemaipomenit, de la unsprezece la unu,<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>ntr-un decor luminat ca n basmele chinezeti. Supeul fu servit la<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>mese mici care ocupau trei din saloanele parterului. Galeria de<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>tablouri a lui Cowperwood se mhogise cu noi<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>achiziii procurate din strintate, iar punctul de atracie era o<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>splendid p<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>nz de G<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>r<text:span text:style-name="T17"></text:span>me, care la<text:span text:style-name="T16"> epoca aceea era la apogeul succesului su  <text:s/>reprezentnd nite cad</text:span>ne goale lenevind de-a lu<text:span text:style-name="T16">n</text:span>gul<text:span text:style-name="T16"> unei bi orientale,</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>mpodobit ca incrustaii <text:span text:style-name="T16">frumoase de piatr viu colorat. Pentru Chicago tabloul era cam ndrzne, ocant pentru publicul neiniat, <text:s/></text:span>totui inofensiv pentru cunosctori. Ddea <text:span text:style-name="T16">ntregii</text:span> colecii, care avea o<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>tonalitate mai <text:span text:style-name="T16">degrab tern</text:span>, pata de culoare necesar. Mai era i un<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>ta<text:span text:style-name="T16">blou de </text:span>cur<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>nd primit i expus, reprezentind-o pe <text:span text:style-name="T16">Aileen, pictat </text:span>de un<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>olandez, Jan van Beers, pe care<text:span text:style-name="T16">-l</text:span> n<text:span text:style-name="T16">tl</text:span>niser la Bruxelles, vara trecut.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Aileen pozase de nou ori ; p<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>nza era excep<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>ion<text:span text:style-name="T16">al</text:span> de frumoas, n<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>tonuri de pastel: pe fondul unui peisaj de var  un bazin cu bordura<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>de pia<text:span text:style-name="T16">tr</text:span>; colul unui palat olandez din crmid roie, u<text:span text:style-name="T16">n</text:span> strat de<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>lalele i un cer albastru cu nori pufo<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>i <text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>Aileen sttea pe braul<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>ncovoiat al unei bnci de piatr, cu <text:soft-page-break/>picioarele n iarba verde, in<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>nd<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>alen<text:span text:style-name="T16">e</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T16">o</text:span> umbrelu roz cu alb, tivit cu dantel; avea un trup viguros<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>cu rotunjimi armonioase <text:span text:style-name="T16">i</text:span> era <text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>mbrcat dup ultima mod,<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>parizian<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>un costum <text:span text:style-name="T16">t</text:span>aior de mtase n dungi albastru cu alb; purta<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>o<text:span text:style-name="T16"> f</text:span>lore<text:span text:style-name="T16">n</text:span>tin vaporoas garnisit cu panglic tot albastru cu alb<text:span text:style-name="T16">. </text:span>Plria arun<text:span text:style-name="T16">c</text:span>a o umbr peste privirea el voluptoas, aproape<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>animalic. Artistul prinsese foarte bine firea, elanul, ndrzneala<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>i<text:span text:style-name="T16"> b</text:span>ravada ei <text:span text:style-name="T16">izvo</text:span>r<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>te din curajul pe care i-l d lipsa de exsperien<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>sau de rafinament. Tabloul avea mult prospei<text:span text:style-name="T16">m</text:span>e, o prospeime cam<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>ostentativ, ca de altfel tot ce avea legtur cu <text:span text:style-name="T16">e</text:span>a; era fcut s<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>st<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>rneasc invidia celor mai puin nzestrai de natur<text:span text:style-name="T16">,</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>n schimb er<text:span text:style-name="T16">a </text:span>o perfect interpretare a modelului. n lumina cald a lmpilor de gaz,<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>acest portret o nfia pe Aileen deosebit de frumoas, alintat<text:span text:style-name="T16">, </text:span>indolent<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>, provocatoare, animal de ras, ngrijit, rsfat de toat<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>lumea. Muli se oprir n faa tabloului care strnea comentarii<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>optite sau cu voce tare.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P12">n dimineaa zilei n care trebuia s ai<text:span text:style-name="T16">b loc petre</text:span>cerea, Aileen se simi<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>cuprins de pani<text:span text:style-name="T16">c, de ngri</text:span>jorare, nesigur de felul n care vor de<text:span text:style-name="T16">curge </text:span><text:s/><text:span text:style-name="T16">lucru</text:span>rile. Frank<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>fusese de prere s-i an<text:span text:style-name="T16">gajeze o secre</text:span>tar, o biat fat, un fel de <text:span text:style-name="T16">roab care trimisese </text:span>toate<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>invitaiile, nregistrase r<text:span text:style-name="T16">spunsurile, fcuse</text:span> comisionale i fusese <text:span text:style-name="T16">c</text:span>onsultat n <text:span text:style-name="T16">toate chestiunile </text:span>de<text:span text:style-name="T16"> </text:span>amnunt. Fadette, camerist<text:span text:style-name="T16">a ei franuzoaic, se zbtea n chinurile pregtirii celor dou toalete <text:s/>necesare</text:span> ; u<text:span text:style-name="T16">n</text:span>a care <text:span text:style-name="T16">t</text:span>re<text:span text:style-name="T16">b</text:span>ui<text:span text:style-name="T16">a</text:span> s<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span> fie <text:span text:style-name="T16">gata pentru ora dou</text:span>, iar celalt pentru ase. Sub<text:span text:style-name="T16">reta scotea din </text:span>dou n d<text:span text:style-name="T16">o</text:span>u minute cte un <text:span text:style-name="T6">m</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">on</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T6"> Dieu</text:span> <text:span text:style-name="T16">sau un </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T6">par</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">bleu</text:span>, cut<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>nd de zor c<text:span text:style-name="T16"></text:span>te un artico